title: southern corn bread dressing(for small turkey or large hen)
directions: The day before making the dressing, cube loaf of white bread. Toast to a good brown in oven.
Leave, uncovered, overnight to dry.
Bake cornbread.
When cool, crumble and let set overnight. Do not mix together.
Saute onion, mushrooms, celery and margarine together until tender; let cool.
Add water chestnuts, pepper, sage, salt and chopped giblets, if desired.

title: chicken and hot rice(from the files of james n. heiskell)
directions: Brown cut up fryer in about 1/3 cup fat.
Drain and pour off all but about 1 tablespoon of fat.
Add long grain rice and coat with grease; brown until light golden.
Add garlic powder, onion powder, tomatoes and salt.
Mix well and add chicken and 3 cups boiling water.
Cover and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: sundae cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
While still warm, poke holes in cake and cover with Eagle Brand milk.
Then pour on ice cream topping. Place in refrigerator to cool, then frost with whipped topping. Use your imagination.
Ex: Chocolate cake and caramel ice cream topping.

title: peppermint delight
directions: Line the bottom of a Pyrex pan with 1/2 of the crumbs.
Whip whipping cream.
Add small marshmallows.
Mix nuts and peppermint candy through together and spread over wafer crumbs.
Put other half of wafers on top.
Let it set in refrigerator overnight.

title: graham cracker torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cracker crumbs with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored and add to the cracker mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla, stirring to blend.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Turn into a greased 9-inch square pan and bake about 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares and serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: easy barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and let come to a boil.
Serve over chicken, beef, pork, etc.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together.
Serve with fresh vegetable platter.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Beat egg; add applesauce and oil.
Combine dry ingredients and nuts and add to applesauce mixture.
Stir just until blended. Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and sprinkle on top with powdered sugar.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Next, cream in butter, then add eggs, one at a time.
Then add flour and vanilla.
Next, fold in nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
While hot, pour 1 (7 to 10 ounce) jar of marshmallow cream on cake.

title: holiday egg nog
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs at high speed on electric mixer. Gradually pour in sugar and salt.
Beat three or four minutes. Pour into gallon pitcher and add milk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Using a wire whisk, stir well.
Add 7-Up and stir.
Then chill for at least an hour to let the flavor mix.

title: daddy's homemade ice cream
directions: Mix eggs and sugar until smooth and light yellow.
Add vanilla, condensed milk and evaporated milk and pour into container.
Fill to line with whole milk.
Freeze.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Cut green apples into wedges.
Sprinkle with lemon juice. Triple recipe for party.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil water and 2 tablespoons butter.
Add instant potatoes. Combine onion and 3 tablespoons butter; microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Add to potatoes and water mixture.
Add seasonings and milk.
Heat.

title: meat loaf
directions: Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate until congealed.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Stir together and bring to a boil. Boil for 6 minutes, then take it off the heat and add strawberries. Pour into baked pie shell and refrigerate. When serving, top with Cool Whip.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix the eggs, sugar, oil and brown sugar. Sift flour, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda.
Add to the egg mixture. Mix well. Add zucchini, vanilla and nuts. Bake in greased 9 x 13 pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Pour liquid smoke over meat and sprinkle both sides generously with celery salt, onion salt and garlic salt.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning uncover and sprinkle with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Do not drain.
Cover securely with foil and place in shallow pan.
Bake 5 hours at 250°. Remove foil and add barbecue sauce.
Reseal and bake another hour.

title: chili dip
directions: In a large sauce pan, saut onion in butter.
Add chili and soup.
Transfer to a slow cooker to keep warm during serving. Just before you are ready to serve the dip, add cubes of sharp Cheddar cheese.
Stir just enough to mix in but not thoroughly melt.
This is great to dip with chips, use for Frito chili pie or serve on hot dogs.

title: apple lumpy cake
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and oil together in a large bowl until creamy.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon and mix together well.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Spread in a prepared 10 x 14-inch pan.
Can also be baked in a large tube cake pan.
Bake at 350°, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Leave plain or frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: poke cake
directions: Bake cake according to package in 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cool, poke holes all through the top of cake with butter knife or fork.
Pour orange soda evenly over top of cake.
Mix pudding and milk together until well blended. Fold in whipped topping until smooth.
Spread over cake and store in refrigerator until serving time.
Cake is also good with cherry or strawberry soda with whipped topping and fresh fruit.

title: grandma's sauerkraut and meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together except sauerkraut and form into 2-inch
meatballs.	Layer
sauerkraut
and	meatballs
in large soup pot.
Add
can (or jar) of water for each can or jar of sauerkraut added.
Bring to
a
boil, then	simmer	for 2 1/2 hours.
Serve with fluffy mashed potatoes.

title: fat-free carrot cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Puree pears; beat with brown sugar and egg whites.
Add to flour mixture with orange rind and orange juice, until just moist.
Don't overbeat.
Fold in chopped strawberries and shredded carrots.

title: steak and cheese sub
directions: Take steak and cut it up and put on roll.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Put in microwave for 1 to 3 minutes, then take it out and eat.

title: feta chicken
directions: Thaw chicken breasts.
Soak in lemon juice.
Roll in flour and oregano.
Saute in olive oil or bake at 375° until done.
Sprinkle with crumbled cheese.
Broil until warmed through and golden.

title: cream puffs and eclair mix
directions: Put water, salt and butter in pot; let come to boil.
Turn heat low.
Pour flour in pot.
Mix until mixture leaves side of pot.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Flour will break into pieces.
Keep beating until mixture comes to a ball.
Cook pudding and cool.
Take 1 teaspoon flour and small bowl of water to wet fingers.
Shape and put on cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown at 350°.
After cool, use a catsup squeezer to fill shells. Put pudding at end of shell.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on cream puffs and chocolate icing for eclairs.

title: easy german chocolate topping
directions: Combine coconut, brown sugar, chopped nuts, butter and milk in a large bowl.
Spread topping over cooled cake.
Broil 6 inches from heat 2 to 3 minutes or until bubbly and golden.
Cool completely.

title: ida's chili
directions: Brown beef in a large skillet with oil.
Remove.
Lightly brown onion, celery, carrots and garlic.
Add oregano, cumin, bay leaves, flour, tomato paste and chili powder.
Cook about 2 minutes.
Add beef and stock.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to a simmer and add red pepper and salt to taste.
Cook until beef is tender.

title: carrot bread(makes one loaf)
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
In another bowl, beat eggs with remaining ingredients.
Stir the egg mixture into dry ingredients.
Place batter in lightly oiled bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: "abc" sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then add marshmallows on top and broil until brown.

title: homemade baby wipes
directions: Separate paper towels; stack together.
Cut paper towels in half; then cut to fit container.
Place large pieces in container. Make a mixture of water, baby bath and baby oil.
Pour over paper towels.
Let set for a few minutes and drain off extra.
Place extra pieces in smaller container and add mixture.
Containers need to be airtight.

title: best chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add water, oil and vinegar; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
This cake only needs powdered sugar on top.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Take sausage meat out of skin and break up.
Brown with onion. Drain fat.
Add green pepper, pizza sauce and mushrooms.
Simmer about an hour.
When almost done, cook the noodles.
Grease a glass dish (8 x 11 1/2-inch or 9 x 13-inch).
Line bottom with noodles, then half the meat mixture, then half the cheese.
Repeat layers. Bake until cheese is melted good, about 30 to 35 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash and dry spinach.
Combine spinach, eggs, onion, bacon, and sprouts.
Set aside.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook equal parts of broccoli and cauliflower to half done. Salt to taste.
Toast 4 slices of bread and melt 1/2 stick of butter; crumble toast and add to butter for topping.

title: quiche
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a Pyrex pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 or so minutes.
Easy, good and quick.

title: sue's spicy meatballs with sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into balls and brown in oil. Remove meatballs and drain on paper towels.
Pour 1 jar spaghetti sauce in pan.
Add meatballs; simmer 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rice and oyster dressing
directions: Saute chicken livers in 1 tablespoon butter.
Dice and set aside.
Melt 1/2 cup butter; stir in onion, celery and pepper. Saute until tender.
Combine oysters, livers, parsley, rice, salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until fluffy.
Add next 4 ingredients.

Line pie pan with pastry and sprinkle with pecans. Bake in very hot oven (450°) 10 minutes; reduce temperature to moderate (350°) and bake 35 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 1 (8-inch) pie.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar. Add vanilla and flour. Stir potato chips in by hand. Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until light golden. When cool, sift powdered sugar on all sides of cookie. Yield: 8 dozen.

title: black magic cake
directions: Put all into large bowl.
Beat until smooth.
(Batter will be thin.)
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion in skillet.
Stir in chili beans.
In large salad bowl, tear lettuce.
Add tomatoes and Doritos.
Stir in hamburger mixture.
Pour dressing over; sprinkle cheese on top.
Serves 12.

title: divinity
directions: Cook 2 1/2 cups sugar and Karo in pan until forms ball or crackles.
Beat egg whites and 1/2 cup sugar.
Keep beating as you add the syrup mixture.
May add nuts and cherries.
Spoon out on wax paper.

title: coral salad mold
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
Heat tomato soup and cheese and add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Add mayonnaise and stir until well blended.
Add vegetables.
Pour into mold.
Chill.
Unmold and serve with cold meats.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut two cans of biscuits into fourths.
Then roll in cinnamon and sugar and place in tube pan.
Bring to a boil 1/2 cup margarine and 1 cup brown sugar and pour half over biscuits in pan.
Cut remaining two cans of biscuits and roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Place in pan.
Pour rest of margarine and brown sugar over biscuits.
Raisins, nuts and apples are optional.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Mash and add salt and pepper.
Add margarine, bouillon cube, onion, egg and sour cream.
Pour into lightly greased one-quart casserole.
Combine bread crumbs, shredded cheese and dash of paprika.
Sprinkle over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry daiquiri
directions: Place all ingredients except whipped cream in blender.
Mix at high speed until smooth.
Pour into glass; top with whipped cream.

title: cream cheese hazelnut pound cake
directions: In large bowl with an electric mixer, beat the cream cheese and the butter until the mixture is light and creamy.
Add the sugar, a little at a time, beating, and beat the mixture until it is combined well.
Add the vanilla and the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
In a bowl, stir together the flour and mace; stir the mixture into the cream cheese mixture and stir in the hazelnuts.

Pour batter into buttered and floured 10 x 4 1/2-inch tube pan with a removable bottom or a Bundt pan. Bake cake in the middle of a preheated 300° oven for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Cool.
Sift confectioners sugar over cake.

title: fudge
directions: Cook, stirring occasionally, for about 20 to 25 minutes until a small amount dropped into cold water forms a firm mass.
Remove from heat.
Add and blend in margarine and vanilla.

title: low sugar strawberry pie
directions: Add cornstarch to 2 c. boiling water.
Then add jello to the water.
Cut and slice strawberries.
Then arrange them in the bottom of the crust.
Pour mixture into the crust.
Chill 2 hours.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Blend shortening, margarine and sugar until creamy.
Blend egg yolks into mixture; add baking soda to buttermilk.
Stir buttermilk and flour into mixture alternating into egg mixture. Beat egg whites until stiff, then add vanilla and fold into cake mixture, then fold in coconut (optional).

title: easy lasagna rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese. Squeeze spinach dry and add eggs.
Add spinach mixture to cheese and mix.
Place portion of mixture onto cooked lasagna noodles and roll up.
Line roll-ups in Pyrex baking pan.
Cover with sauce. Sprinkle 1 small package shredded Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lamb's pie
directions: Season ground meat with salt, pepper, onions and garlic powder.
Brown and drain.
Prepare mashed potatoes.
Mix drained ground meat and mashed potatoes.
Spoon in dish.
Cover top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ratatouille vegetable stew
directions: In Dutch oven, cook onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add the undrained tomatoes and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Discard bay leaf.
Remove and set aside 2 cups of the sauce mixture.
Slice the eggplant in half lengthwise, then crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange half of eggplant, zucchini and pepper over sauce in pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with 1 cup reserved sauce.
Arrange remaining vegetables atop; sprinkle with more salt and pepper.
Pour over remaining sauce.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes.
Uncover; simmer 15 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
Nice with rice.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: easy orzo side dish
directions: In a large skillet, brown bacon until almost crisp.
Drain off excess fat.
Add onion and cook until tender, but not brown.
Add chicken broth and water; bring to a boil.
Stir in orzo and parsley; return to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 15 minutes or until orzo is tender and most of liquid is absorbed. Serves 4.

title: red beans and rice
directions: In heavy 3-quart saucepan, put first 4 ingredients and saute for 3 minutes. Add broth and bring to a boil; add rice and cook 10 minutes. Add beans, ham, hot sauce, bay leaf and garlic. Cover and simmer for 15 to 25 minutes or until rice is done.

title: aunt harriet's thanksgiving date pudding
directions: Pour the one cup of boiling water over half of the dates and add the soda.
Let this mixture stand while you mix the next batch of ingredients.
Sift (mix) flour, sugar and baking powder.
Mix into the date, soda and water mixture and add beaten egg, butter and 1/2 cup of nuts.
Blend well and spread mixture in a greased 10 x 15 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spread over the top a sauce made by mixing the remaining 1/2 pound dates, 1/2 cup nuts and the 2/3 cup of boiling water.
The sauce should be mixed while the cake is baking.
The topping will remain moist and keep the cake moist.
Serve slices with whipped cream.

title: sweet and sour fish sauce for dipping egg rolls
directions: Combine garlic and sugar; mash together.
Squeeze juice into garlic-sugar and add 1/2 cup water and chili paste.
Stir in fish sauce a little at a time to taste.
If too salty, add water and sugar.
If too fishy, add more lemon or lime juice.
Serve in individual bowls.

title: pepper steak
directions: Preheat oil in skillet.
Add meat and brown at 325°.
Remove meat.
Add onion and peppers; cook until tender.
Dissolve cornstarch in water; add soy sauce, sugar, garlic, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into skillet with vegies, stirring until sauce is thickened.
Add meat and bean sprouts.
Cook 7 minutes.
Serve over rice or fine egg noodles.

title: spicy pumpkin loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Put all ingredients in a large bowl; mix with electric mixer or by hand. After thorough mixing, spread batter in prepared pan.
Bake for 60 to 65 minutes, or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove pan from oven; place on wire rack to cool for 10 minutes.
Remove loaf from pan; cool completely on wire rack. Tightly wrapped in aluminum foil, loaf keeps well in refrigerator or freezer.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: minted baby carrots
directions: About 1 hour before serving, peel and cook carrots 20 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Drain carrots.
Stir in mint jelly, butter and mint, chopped.
Cook over medium heat until jelly and butter melt.
Serve hot.

title: cheese and vegetable chowder
directions: In a skillet, cook the garlic and onions in the butter over moderately low heat, stirring for 10 minutes, or until the onions are softened.
Add the bacon and the mushrooms; cook the mixture over moderate heat, stirring, for 3 minutes.
In a bowl, toss the Cheddar with the cornstarch; add the mixture to the stock, a little at a time, over low heat, stirring.
Stir the mixture until it is smooth.
Stir in the Worcestershire sauce, half and half, broccoli, carrots, onion mixture and salt and pepper to taste. Heat the chowder over moderately low heat until it is hot, but do not boil.
Makes about 7 cups, serving 6.

title: cream puffs
directions: Boil water.
Add Crisco, flour and salt; stir vigorously using fork, until a paste.
Cool thoroughly.
To paste, add 1 egg at a time.
Stir with fork vigorously until smooth.
Drop by teaspoon onto a Crisco greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 or 12 minutes, until golden brown on top.
Wait until cold.
Cut off tops and fill with your favorite (cold) pudding.
Put back tops. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: surprise raspberry jam
directions: In a large saucepan combine first 3 ingredients.
Cook and stir over high heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 25 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Skim off foam if necessary.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Place in blender and blend until creamy.

title: oatmeal pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Combine oil and water and add to dry ingredients; mix together.
Handle as little as possible. Press into two pie pans with fork.
Prick with fork.

title: falafel
directions: Place beans and liquid in blender and puree.
Put in bowl; add all ingredients except 3/4 cup wheat germ.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Add enough wheat germ so balls will hold together.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes (place on cookie sheet).
Serve in heated pita bread (2 or 3 balls) with lettuce, tomato, alfalfa sprouts and tahini dressing.
Makes 20 to 24 balls.

title: sugar delight cookies
directions: Beat together well:
powdered and white sugars and margarine. Add rest of ingredients, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 minutes.

title: pig outs
directions: Take flat cookie sheet or jelly roll pan and cover with foil. Spread saltine crackers on pan to entirely cover pan.
In saucepan, melt and boil butter and sugar for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers and bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips over entire pan.
It will have a glossy look.
Let cool and then break into pieces.
This is a delicious treat for kids and kids at heart.

title: italian beef
directions: Put onions, green peppers and beef bouillon mixed with water in crock-pot.
Add meat. Add enough water to cover meat.
Cook all day.
Meat just falls apart.
Fill hoagie roll with meat, onion and green pepper.
Tastes great with Mozzarella cheese sprinkled on top.
Pour au jus sauce in a bowl to dip.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Make well in center.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to dry ingredients, stirring.
Pour into greased loaf pans (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: unleavened bread
directions: Stir water into flour and salt.
Place on a floured board and knead the dough a few times.
Wrap the dough in plastic wrap.
Let it stand for five minutes.
Heat an oven to 350° or an electric frying pan to medium hot.
Pinch off small balls of dough and flatten them with your hands.
Bake in an oven for ten minutes or in an ungreased frypan on both sides until lightly browned.

title: fanny mae fudge
directions: In large bowl, combine oleo, nuts and vanilla; set chocolate chips aside.
In large pan, cook sugar and Carnation milk.
Boil 6 minutes.
Stir so it won't stick.
Remove from heat and pour over ingredients in the bowl.
Pour in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: episcopal pickles
directions: Drain pickles and slice across like hamburger pickles, about 1-inch thick.
Place in enamel dishpan or pot with ice for 1 hour. Remove and pat dry with paper towels.
Into the crock, put a layer of pickles, then a layer composed of sugar, cloves and garlic. Continue until all ingredients are used.
Pour vinegar over all. Cover and keep in a cool spot (any air conditioned area is fine) for a week.
After that pickles may be bottled or left in crock indefinitely.
I store them in gallon jar that the pickles came in. These are delicious.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Saute meat and onion in butter until brown.
Mix soup and sour cream in a separate bowl, add to meat mixture.
Simmer until the meat is tender.
Add mushrooms the last 5 minutes.
Cook noodles according to directions.
Serve sauce over noodles.
Serves 4. Cooking time: 45 minutes.

title: june cook's baked beans
directions: Mix all together and bake in pan 1 hour at 350°.
This recipe can be doubled and is good.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions.
Drain and chop into bite size pieces; set aside.
Melt cheese, milk and margarine in a double boiler until smooth.
Add crushed crackers to the cheese mixture.
Mix cheese sauce and vegetables together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Spread into a greased casserole and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix and bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350.

title: spanish delight
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion; drain. Add cooked noodles and other ingredients. Put layer of meat mixture in casserole dish; cover with 1/2 the cheese. Add another layer of meat mixture and top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until the cheese is melted.

title: omelette sandwich
directions: Butter both sides of bread.
Layer in pan.
Add Swiss cheese, ham and Cheddar cheese.
Add second layer of bread.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Pour over sandwiches.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: eggplant-chicken-ground meat dressing
directions: Boil eggplant and chicken and take chicken off bones after cooked.
Brown ground meat.
In pot put 2 tablespoons of oil; brown onion, bell peppers, celery and boiled eggplant.
Add boiled chicken and cooked ground meat.
Add 1 cup of liquid; cook until all liquid is gone.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Turn off heat and cook rice.
Stir all ingredients together until well mixed.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Bring jello and sugar to a boil.
Add pineapple.
Cool.
Cream milk and cream cheese.
Add Dream Whip.
Add to pineapple mixture. Refrigerate.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Add mayonnaise, salt and garlic salt to taste.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix and bake ingredients for 30 minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix together.
Let stand 1 hour before serving.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind tomatoes.
Put in colander and let drain overnight. Chop and add cabbage, all peppers and onions.
Boil together vinegar, celery seed, sugar and mustard seed.
Add the chopped vegetables and boil 15 minutes.
Put in jars and seal while hot. Makes 12 pints.

title: biscuits on creamy chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Rinse peas.
Heat peas, chicken, soup, sour cream, 1/2 cup milk, salt and pepper just to boiling point in 3-quart saucepan, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat; keep warm while preparing biscuits.

title: coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour an 8 x 1 1/2-inch round pan.
Heat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and shortening until crumbly. Reserve 1/4 cup of this mixture.
To remaining crumbs, add baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Add milk and eggs.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Top with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 32 to 35 minutes.
Mix sweetened condensed milk and cream of coconut.
Pour over warm cake after pricking cake with fork.
Let soak into cake. Refrigerate.
Spread Cool Whip over top; sprinkle with coconut.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Mix the ingredients (except cheese). Pour 1/2 of mixture into pan.
Then add the cheese.
Pour remaining mixture on top of cheese.
bake at 400 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: congar bars
directions: Pour melted shortening over sugar.
Add eggs; sift dry ingredients and mix well.
Add chocolate chips and vanilla. Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or when toothpick comes out clean.

title: old settler's beans
directions: Do not drain cans.
Place all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Brown beef.
Cook bacon and break into small pieces.
Mix thoroughly.
Do not cover.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: lemon pies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; cook until it begins to thicken. Add the juice and grated rind of 2 lemons.
Beat egg yolks and add some of the hot mixture.
Return it to the double boiler and cook until thickened.
Add the butter and cool.
Pour the filling in baked shells; cover with beaten egg whites.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar per egg white.
Bake about 15 minutes in 325° oven.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: meat casserole (beef)
directions: Preheat oven at 325°.
Cut onions, celery and pepper coarsely, cook beef in 1 tablespoon of butter until brown and transfer to casserole.
Cook vegetables until limp, in remaining butter, stir in mushroom soup and water, salt and pepper and mix with beef. Cover and bake 30 minutes.
After 30 minutes, remove cover and sprinkle with noodles and bake 10 minutes longer, cut back on onions, if you need to.
Serves 4.

title: stew fried corn
directions: With sharp knife, cut off corn from cob.
Put in frying pan with grease and sugar.
Allow it to stew until the liquid stews out and the corn begins to fry.
As it starts to brown, stir so it won't stick to the pan.
Do not overcook.
It must be moist. Remove to serving dish and place slices of side pork on top.
Serve hot.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on side panel.
Rinse with cold water. Drain and chill.
Mix mayonnaise with lemon juice, salt and pepper.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl with an electric mixer.
Pour mixture into a graham cracker pie shell.

title: raisin jumbles
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add sour cream, vanilla, extract, salt, cinnamon and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add raisins. Mix remaining dry ingredients well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: orange fruit salad
directions: Mix drained cans of fruit together, then add rest of ingredients.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Chill.

title: christmas eve buffet supper
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over moderate heat.
Stir in onion, green pepper and strained mushrooms.
Cook until onion is soft (about 5 minutes), stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Return to heat; stir in milk gradually, continuing to cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in cheese, lemon juice, mustard and Worcestershire sauce until cheese melts.
Break lobster and crab meat and add, with shrimp, to sauce.
Heat mixture to boiling point.

title: pineapple rings
directions: Cream potatoes with sugar, margarine and milk.
Add vanilla and raisins.
Place pineapple rings on baking sheet.
Drop potato mix by spoonfuls on rings.
Top each ring with marshmallow.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Fry hamburger add onion and peppers.
Add rest of ingredients, except spaghetti. Mix the spaghetti with the spaghetti sauce. Bake at 300 degree for 45-60 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: *You can use frozen peas and onions and add carrots if desired.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix lightly, but well.
Sift flour, spices, soda and baking powder.
Add to zucchini mixture and blend well.
Add nuts. Pour batter into 2 (8 x 4-inch) greased and floured pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: steakie-roastie
directions: Put steak in roasting pan.
Fill with water until just covering steak.
Mix soup in with water.
Chop onion up and add it and all other ingredients to the water.
Cover.
Bake in oven at 275° for about 4 hours.
Check occasionally after 2 1/2 to 3 hours to make sure the water is still there.
If the water gets too low, add a little.
Also check the steak with a fork and when it falls apart easily, it's done.
The water and soup mixture makes the gravy.

title: yummy squares
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put into well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool, then cut into squares.

title: pecan balls
directions: Mix flour, butter, pecans, 8 tablespoons sugar and vanilla. Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Roll into 1-inch balls; then roll in confectioners sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sour cream chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients until batter is smooth.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan or angel food cake pan for 60 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: fresh pineapple pina colada
directions: Put all in the blender over the crushed ice and blend one minute.
Makes one serving.
This drink can be made without the rum, if desired, and is just as good.
Do not blend too long, as the ice will melt.

title: cheese, broccoli soup
directions: Bring 6 cups water to a boil in a 3-quart Dutch oven; add broccoli and onion.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Add cheese and seasonings, stirring until cheese melts. Stir in milk, half and half and butter; cook over low heat until thoroughly heated.
Combine flour and cold water, stirring until smooth.
Gradually add to broccoli mixture, stirring constantly. Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring occasionally. Yield:
2 1/2 quarts.

title: play dough
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly, until the mixture forms a ball (about 3 minutes).
Drop on wax paper and knead out lumps.
Store in airtight container.

title: kathy's very berry holiday punch
directions: Add juices and 7-Up together in your favorite punch bowl.
Do not add water.
Stir in berries.
Add 2 cups ice.
Garnish with silk poinsettias to float.

title: spinach artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 400.
Blend first 5 ingredients.
Fold in remaining ingredients leaving some chunks of artichoke hearts. Spread in 9X13 deep dish casserole pan.
Top with parmesan cheese. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.
Serve with Tostitos, crackers, or crusty bread.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer salad beginning with lettuce, adding in order: celery, onions, water chestnuts, chicken and English peas.
Mix sugar and mayonnaise for top layer or sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Can refrigerate overnight.
Add bacon bits and sliced eggs before serving.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Parboil carrots.
Mix juice and brown sugar.
Pour over carrots.
Cook in a 325° oven for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix sugar and pineapple.
Bake cake mix and cool completely. Cool about 15 minutes.
Using a fork, poke holes in cake.
Pour mixture over cake.
Mix pudding; spread over pineapple.
When cool, spread with Cool Whip.

title: buckeyes(peanut butter candy balls)
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter and powdered sugar; chill for 1 hour.
Roll in balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip balls into chocolate and dip with toothpicks.
Let cool to set.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions and margarine in skillet for 15 to 20 minutes over medium heat.
Place 1/2 onions in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with 1/2 crackers and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, in 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots about 1/8-inch slices.
Cook in salted water until tender for about 15 minutes.
Drain; let cool.
Place half in bowl.
Separate onion slices into rings.
Arrange on top of carrots.
Place green pepper slices on top of onions.
Place remainder of carrots on top.
Mix tomato bisque, vinegar and all other ingredients until smooth.
Pour over carrot mixture and let stand overnight.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° until firm.
If you desire, you may add coconut.

title: beef mushroom quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake pie crust 12 to 15 minutes. Remove from
oven.
Reduce
oven	temperature to 350°.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture into
baked pie shell.
Cover edges of pie shell with aluminum foil
to
prevent burning.	Bake for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sugar, water, salt, vinegar and oil.
Add to vegetables and mix well.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: cole slaw
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar, oil, salt, dry mustard and celery seed to a boil and stir until thoroughly mixed.
Pour this mixture over shredded cabbage and onion.
Cool and let set for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Add meat; brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add soup; simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through.
Do not boil.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve plain or over noodles or rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: loaded potato soup
directions: Chop (you can leave peeling on) and boil potatoes until tender.
While potatoes are boiling, in separate pan, mix ingredients and cook until mixture thickens.
Drain potatoes and pour milk mixture over potatoes, and add salt & pepper to taste. Cook for 30 minutes on low heat.

title: sage's favorite yellow rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: the dream loaf
directions: In large skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
When it foams, add the onion, bell pepper, green onion and garlic.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Uncover and cook, stirring often, for another 4 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are lightly
browned. Remove from heat and cool to room temperature.
Position a rack in the middle of oven and preheat to 350°.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Cook together bacon and onions until onions are transparent. Mix together mustard, flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Then stir into bacon and onions.
Add vinegar and bean liquid.
Bring to a boil.
Add beans and simmer 10 minutes.
Yields 4 servings. Preparation Time:
15 to 20 minutes.
Note:
can be served hot or cold.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Grease 2 loaf pans.
Mix 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar and soda. Heat milk 2 minutes in microwave.
Add water to make lukewarm. Add liquid to flour mixture; mix.
Add 3 cups flour and mix.
Put into loaf pans.
Sprinkle with cornmeal.
Cover with dish towel. Let rise until over top of pans.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and flour.
Add milk, vanilla, butter and coconut.
Pour into two ungreased 9-inch pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Forms own crust.

title: braunschweiger spread
directions: Have braunschweiger and cream cheese at room temperature.
Put all ingredients into blender and blend thoroughly.
Chill until ready to use.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and add to creamed mixture.
Add flavoring.

title: sweet dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, let set 5 minutes.
Stir in milk, sugar, salt, eggs and shortening.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time.
Add enough flour to handle easily.
Turn out onto floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Roll up into a ball and place into a greased bowl and roll over, greased side up.
Cover with a damp cloth and place in a warm, draft free area.
Let rise until doubled in size, about 1 to 2 hours.

title: picnic take along hamburgers
directions: Brown, crumble and drain ground beef.
Mix in mayo, sweet relish and yellow mustard.
Mix all together in large bowl and refrigerate.
Spoon mixture on hamburg rolls to take to picnic; no grill, no condiments needed.

title: margarita pie
directions: In medium bowl, combine pretzel crumbs and brown sugar.
With fork, stir in butter until blended.
Press mixture onto bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate; refrigerate.
In small bowl, sprinkle gelatin over 1/4 cup lime juice; let stand 5 minutes to soften.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
Microwave chocolate and margarine in large bowl on High 2 minutes or until margarine is melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir sugar into chocolate until well blended.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and nuts until well blended.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in large baking pan.
Cover with oil and toss thoroughly.
Bake at 200° for 20 minutes.
Remove and let stand 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter to soften.
Add sugar, gradually, and cream until fluffy.
Add syrup and salt.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each is stirred in.
Fold in pecans. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Lower to 325° and bake 40 minutes. Cool before serving.

title: corn chowder
directions: Mix butter, bacon and onion in saucepan, then add flour, milk, parsley and dill weed.
Drain potatoes and put everything together.

title: crunchy peanut butter swirl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees F.
Grease bottom of 13x9 inch pan. In small bowl, blend all filling ingredients except peanuts.
Beat at medium speed until smooth.
Stir in peanuts, set aside.

title: garbage dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve with nacho chips or Doritos.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crust ingredients with fork and bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: chocolate whoopie pies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Sift together flour, cocoa and salt.
Add alternately with sour milk.
Dissolve soda in hot water and add last.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 18 minutes.
Make sandwiches from 2 cookies filled with filling recipe.
For filling, it will need to be doubled for this batch.

title: layered pudding delight
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with 7 graham crackers.
Fix pudding as on package.
Beat at lowest speed of mixer for 2 minutes.
Add Cool Whip to pudding.
Spread pudding mixture over crackers. Layer rest of crackers on top, then spread pie filling over all. Chill 3 hours.

title: dilly cheese ring
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine margarine, cheese, dill weed and garlic powder.

title: pork picatta
directions: Pound pork tenderloin slices until 1/4-inch thick.
Mix bread crumbs, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Coat pork with flour, dip in egg and water mixture and then crumb mixture.
Cook a few pieces of pork, turning once.
Cook about 12 minutes.
Repeat for remaining pork.

title: angel food delight cake
directions: Break cake in small pieces and put in square bowl.
Mix pie filling with milk.
Add sour cream; beat until thick.
Pour over cake, then add 1 can of cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: sage sticks
directions: Sift flour, baking powder
and salt into bowl.	Stir in sage and cheese.
Cut
in
margarine with pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle
water
over	top;
mix
lightly until dough holds together and leaves sides of bowl.
Roll out on lightly floured pastry
board
in
x
5-inch
rectangle. Divide into 3 x 1/2-inch strips.	Twist and place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at
425° for 5 to 6 minutes or until light golden
brown.
Great snacks.
Makes approximately 3 1/2 dozen.

title: crackers
directions: Blend cashews with 3/4 cup water until very smooth.
Add sesame seed and coconut and continue blending.
Add all other ingredients and blend until smooth.
Pour onto an 11 x 17-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and score to desired cracker size.
Continue baking until lightly browned.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Marinate brisket overnight in liquid smoke.
Next morning, line large pan with foil or use large roaster.
Put meat and liquid smoke in pan and add barbecue sauce.
Sprinkle with celery seed, onion salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover; bake 5 to 6 hours.
Uncover and bake 1 hour to brown at 300°.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and cover with boiling water.
Let set 5 minutes, then drain well.
Add onions and other ingredients; boil for 5 minutes and seal while hot.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking pan.
Spread peaches over butter.
Mix sugar, milk and flour well.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown crust forms on top.

title: "sugar free" angel dessert
directions: Tear cake into small chunks.
Add drained pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill in freezer for 1/2 hour.
Simple but good!

title: chicken ala king
directions: Saute mushrooms and green pepper in butter.
Blend in flour; add salt and pepper to taste.
Allow to cook for a minute and then slowly add milk and chicken broth, stirring constantly.
Allow to boil for about a minute.
Add the chicken and pimiento; heat the mixture but do not allow it to boil.
Serve over toast.
Serves 6.

title: mexican chicken(king ranch casserole)
directions: Boil chicken in salted water until tender.
Bone and cut into small pieces.
Put tortillas in hot chicken stock to wilt; cut in quarters.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift flour.
Add sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add butter, milk and yeast to flour, sugar and shortening mixture.
Mix and place in refrigerator.
Make out biscuits as needed.
Do not allow to rise before baking.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.
This dough will keep for 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Mix well, cook over high heat while stirring 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and oats.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper and cool.

title: eggplant souffle
directions: Peel and slice eggplants.
Cook in 2 quarts boiling water with salt, bay leaf and cloves for about 20 minutes or until tender. Drain and discard bay leaf and cloves.
Mash eggplants in bowl and add butter, eggs, milk, seasonings, grated cheese and unbuttered bread crumbs.
Stir well.
Place in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle top with buttered crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven (350° to 375°) until firm and brown on top, 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve at once. Serves 6.

title: pumpkin log
directions: Mix ingredients and bake on greased and floured jelly roll pan at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Place on towel covered with powdered sugar.
Roll long side with towel.
Wait 15 minutes more.
Unroll and spread with Cream Cheese Filling.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook 40 minutes at 350°. When mixing if the casserole feels too stiff/dry, add more chicken broth to desired consistency.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Boil until soft. Drain and put half of the potatoes in a 3-quart dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup and sour cream well.
Space spoonfuls of mixture over potatoes, leaving half for second layer.
Grate all of the cheese and spread a good layer of cheese, then repeat, potatoes, mixture and cheese.
Top well with cornflakes.
Melt butter or margarine and pour over cornflakes or spoon over cornflakes.
If more is needed, melt more.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese blintzes
directions: Combine flour and salt (sift).
Add water; mix until smooth. Add 4 eggs; beat well.
Add milk; mix to thin batter.
Cook slowly until pancake is lightly browned on bottom and "set" on top.
Turn on foil with browned side up.
Mix cheese and 1 egg.
Add sugar to taste.
Beat (not too much).
Put spoonful of cheese in center of each pancake on browned side; fold.
Brown in small amount of hot oil.
If you wish, serve topped with sour cream.

title: vinegar cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into balls and roll in Angel Flake coconut.
Place in an airtight container in refrigerator (if you have room) or in a cool place.
These keep well.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Saute mushrooms and green pepper in butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Let bubble.
Slowly stir in chicken broth and cream, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Add chicken and pimento.
Heat through.
Serve over rice.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter and Cheez Whiz together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, covered.

title: good ole home cooked easy dressing
directions: Beat eggs.
Add buttermilk.
Add sugar.
Grease bottom of black skillet and sprinkle some corn meal in bottom of skillet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Butter bottom and sides of BIG roaster container.
Saut celery and onions.
Dump this in the roaster container.
Crumble corn bread in roaster.
Salt and pepper.
Add poultry seasoning.
Add soup.
Add broth.
It should look moist and soupy.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pasta with tuna and peas
directions: In 3 tablespoons oil, brown garlic and onion.
Add tomato sauce, peas, seasoning and 2 cups of water.
Simmer for 7 to 8 minutes.
Stir in tuna with the water.
Remove from heat.
In the meantime, cook macaroni according to package directions and drain. Add to tuna and pea mixture.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: almond crunch
directions: Mix up and bake in 12 x 8-inch pan at 350° until crispy for 5 to 10 minutes.
Reserve 1/2 cup topping after baking.
Stir a couple of times while baking.

title: quiche-a-roni
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni, using 2 1/2 cups water and cook as directed on package.
Cool.
Spoon Rice-A-Roni into a 10-inch buttered quiche pan or pie plate and mold up sides to form a shell.
In a small frying pan, saute onions and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter.
Combine onions, mushrooms, cheese, half and half, eggs, nutmeg, salt and pepper; pour into shell.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until set.
Cool 5 minutes and cut into wedges.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rancher's short ribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving pieces.
Place on cookie sheet.
Brown in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Drain grease and place in large baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ribs. Cover and bake for 2 hours at 350°.
Turn pieces one time.
Serve with sauce.

title: chutney cheese roll
directions: Mix well.
Shape into a roll.
Wrap in foil and chill. Freezes well.

title: veggie pasta
directions: Put veggies in large skillet with a very small amount of olive oil (1 tablespoon). Cook on medium heat (covered) until veggies are tender, about 10 minutes. Add 2 or 3 tablespoons of basil pesto; add tomatoes and cook on medium for about 8 minutes. Add 1/2 tablespoon minced garlic. Add whipping cream and cook on medium heat just long enough to get the cream hot. Serve over any kind of pasta.

title: steak fingers
directions: Trim excess fat off of steak. Pound steak to 1/8-inch thickness, using a meat mallet. Cut into 4 x 1-inch strips. Combine flour, salt and pepper. Combine egg and milk; beat well. Dredge steak strips in flour mixture. Dip strips in egg mixture and dredge again in flour mixture. Heat about 2-inches of oil in a large skillet to 375°. Fry steak fingers in hot oil until browned. Drain on paper towels. Serve immediately. Yields 4 servings.

title: all purpose ragu
directions: (This freezes well for later use.)

title: garlic rump roast
directions: Preheat oven at 500°.
Wash rump roast and dry with a paper towel.
Line iron skillet with aluminum foil.
Gather sides of foil to prevent splattering.
Sprinkle garlic salt in bottom of pan. Lay fat side of roast on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle generous amount of garlic salt all over roast.
Cook 10 minutes per pound plus 10 minutes.
Let set in oven one hour after turning oven off.
Do not open oven door until hour is up.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, flour and salt in a saucepan. Stir in water gradually.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add small amount of hot mixture to slightly beaten egg yolks.
Stir and return to first mixture. Cook 2 minutes longer.

title: seven layer brownies
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt the margarine.
Sprinkle with crumbs, then sprinkle with	coconut
flakes, next sprinkle with butterscotch bits, then chocolate
bits.
Pour
condensed
milk over all.
Sprinkle with chopped
nuts.
Do
not stir, ingredients should be layered.	Bake about
25 minutes in a 350° oven. Do not overbake.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Fry hamburger and onion together until brown.
Add salt to taste and chili powder.
Add soup and Mexicorn.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Mix cornmeal with water until thin.
Pour hamburger mixture into a baking dish.
Spread cornmeal mixture over pie. Bake in 350° oven until brown on top.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Be sure to dissolve all of the sugar.
Add pineapple juice.
Chill.
Add 7-Up type beverage just before serving.

title: white bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast into warm water; stir until dissolved.
Combine sugar, salt, water and shortening.
Stir in 8 cups flour.
Add yeast and enough (8 to 10 cups) of flour to make stiff dough that leaves the bowl when stirred.
Knead for 5 to 10 minutes until smooth.
Place in greased bowl; cover and let rise until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
Knead dough back and allow to rise again. When dough has doubled, bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes around 4 loaves.

title: orange-cream fruit salad
directions: Drain fruits and chop apples.
Combine.
In small mixer bowl, combine pudding mix, milk and orange juice.
Beat 1 to 2 minutes. Fold in sour cream and add to fruit mixture.

title: barbecue duckling
directions: Thoroughly defrost duckling.
Remove giblets, neck and excess fat.
Quarter the duckling.
Place in salt water for at least 2 to 4 hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Thoroughly rinse pieces and place on broiler pan which has been coated with cooking spray.
Place in oven for 1/2 hour, turning once.
Drain fat.
Reduce temperature to 325° for 1 hour, turning every 15 minutes.
Place barbecue sauce and water in 8-quart pot.
Mix thoroughly.
Add duckling.
Cover. Cook over very low heat for 2 hours and 15 minutes.
Delicious over hot rice or pasta.
Enjoy!

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and syrup to soft ball stage; remove from heat.
Beat in chocolate and nuts.
Add vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Turn into 8 x 8-inch buttered pan.
Yields 25 servings.

title: caramel ritz
directions: Combine Ritz bits, peanuts, butter, sugar and corn syrup. Boil for 5 minutes and then add vanilla and baking powder.
Bake on a cookie sheet or shallow pan at 250° for 1 hour.
Turn every 15 minutes.
Pour out on waxed paper.
Break apart and cool. Store in an airtight container.

title: cooked icing
directions: Cook and cool flour and milk.
Beat oleo and Crisco; add sugar and vanilla.
Beat all together and add flour mixture. Cream in bowl.

title: pickled green beans
directions: Boil 30 minutes.
Put in can and turn upside-down to seal.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crumble Oreo cookies in blender or processor.
Soften cream cheese and beat.
Add 3 cups milk.
Add pudding and beat again. Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer pudding, bananas, and dirt (Oreos) in an 8 1/2 inch plastic flower pot (without a hole in the bottom). Repeat layers 3 times.
End with dirt (Oreos) on top.
Chill in refrigerator or harden in FREEZER!
A layer of ice cream may be added if desired.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute onions in butter until golden brown; add potatoes and 1 1/2 cups of water.
Cook until tender.
Set aside to cool.
Add butter to flour.
Stir in half and half, spices, clams, cooked potato mixture and evaporated milk.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes and add a pat of butter to each steaming mug of chowder.

title: celery stuffing
directions: Combine bread crumbs, onions, celery and seasonings.
Add melted butter, milk, broth and eggs. Toss lightly to blend. Stuff loosely into cavities of bird.
Makes 6 1/2 cups stuffing. Enough for 12 pounds. Ready to cook turkey.

title: six-week bran muffins
directions: Mix cereal with
sugar,
flour, soda and salt in a very large bowl.
Add eggs, shortening and milk.
Store in container and use as desired.
Batter will last 6 weeks.

title: chocolate walnut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate over warm water, stirring constantly.
Add walnuts and stir until coated.
Drop in clusters on waxed paper. Cool until set.
Makes 12 large clusters.

title: lori's peanut clusters
directions: Melt morsels together in a double boiler until very soft.
Mix well and stir in peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper or tinfoil.
They will harden in about 1/2 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender, drain well.
Mix other ingredients with squash.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spinach ring with mushrooms
directions: Scald milk and pour over beaten eggs and season. Stir in spinach.
Pour into greased 1-quart mold.
Set in pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 30 minutes until firm.
Turn out and fill center with mushrooms sauteed in butter.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook your macaroni shells; drain and rinse.
Cut up the following:
cheese, onion, pepper, tomatoes, celery, olives, salami and pepperoni.
Mix with the pasta.

title: succulent sweet and sour chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the Russian dressing, apricot preserves and soup mix; pour over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: waffles
directions: Self-rising flour can replace plain flour, salt and baking powder.

title: pecan crisp cookies
directions: Melt butter, add sugar, then egg; beat well.
Add vanilla and flour.
Stir well.
Add pecans, refrigerate for 1 hour.
Slice in thin slices, place on greased pan.
Do not let touch.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until begins to brown around edges.

title: strawberry tart
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add water and bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add jello.
cool.
Stir in berries and place in your favorite baked pastry.

title: monkey bread
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in very large bowl with a seal, then add quartered biscuits to bowl.
Seal and shake it around to coat the biscuits with the cinnamon mixture.
Put the biscuits into the Bundt pan.
Pour melted butter over biscuit pieces.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Let cool 5 minutes, then turn out onto a plate.
Pieces can be picked off individually with the fingers to eat.

title: tex-mex chicken
directions: Cook chicken pieces until tender in 5 to 6 cups water; drain. Remove meat from bones and cube, discarding skin and bones.
Crush tortilla chips and spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add chicken.
Blend remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Pour over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in tight container.
Add 1/3 cup to one cup of hot water.
Adjust to your taste.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: You can add chocolate chips, nuts or raisins.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: kindergarten thanksgiving soup
directions: Bring beef broth to a boil in a soup pot. Add potatoes, carrots, celery and onion. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Add alphabet macaroni. Simmer 5 more minutes. Serves 6.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Mix together cranberries and sugar.
Let set until sugar is dissolved.
Combine with Jell-O and then add nuts and pineapple. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set until thick.
Serves 25.

title: polka daters - bars
directions: Mix dates and hot water, cool.
Beat butter until creamy.
Add eggs, flour and soda.
Add vanilla and 1/2 cup chocolate chips to date mixture.
Spread in greased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 cup chocolate chips and add chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut in squares.
Makes about 30 bars.

title: greek spinach pie
directions: Wash and trim spinach, dry completely and chop.
Brown scallions in 1/2 cup olive oil until tender.
Combine spinach, parsley, dill, beaten eggs and cheese.
Add cooked scallions, season and mix well.

title: broken glass candy
directions: *Must be oil of, etc.; regular flavoring will not work.

title: wine cake(italian kitchens)
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl and beat for 5 minutes or until batter is very smooth.
Butter an angel food cake pan generously.
Add batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Place right side up on a cake dish for 5 minutes.
Then turn over on cake dish.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: croissants(crescent rolls)
directions: Soften
yeast
in
warm water.
Combine sugar, salt and milk in a bowl; cool to lukewarm.
Beat in 1/2 cup flour.
Add yeast and
beat
well.
Beat
in remaining flour.
Turn dough onto floured
surface;
allow
to rest 5 to 8 minutes.
Knead until smooth
and elastic.
Put into greased bowl; grease top of dough. Cover, let rise in warm place until doubled.
Chill in refrigerator 2 hours.

title: chile relleno casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer chiles, cheese until all are used (about 3 layers).
Combine rest of ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Pour egg mixture over chiles and cheeses.
Let set for 24 hours in refrigerator.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and pour on tomato sauce.
Bake for 10 more minutes.
Serves 12.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube pan.
Cover bottom of pan with waxed paper.
Preheat oven to 325.
Cream together butter and sugar. Add one egg at the time to the mixture, beating after each one. Add flavorings and baking soda.
Beat well.
Alternate flour and sour cream in 3 to 4 additions, beginning and ending with flour. Pour into pan.
Bake at 325 for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: apricot yogurt fizz
directions: Blend apricots, yogurt and dried milk.
Put in tall glass and add club soda.

title: zesty baked chicken
directions: Discard chicken skin; rub pieces with salt and pepper. Arrange in casserole dish.
Mix lemon juice, tarragon and bouillon.
Pour over chicken and turn.
Add mushrooms.
Let stand at room temperature for 1/2 hour.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour, turning often and basting with marinade.
Cook until chicken is tender and cooked through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pepper relish
directions: Whin the ole hens lays a surplus uv aigs put them gently in a crock uv lime watah...1 pound uv lime 'n 1 gallon watah...they will keep fur sum time this way iffin you'll put the crock in a cool place lak the cellar.

title: 6 week bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl or Tupperware.
In separate bowl, mix together eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Add to dry mixture and mix well.
Store in refrigerator in covered container.
Fill muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican style chicken
directions: Cook chicken; remove from bone.
Cut tortillas into 1-inch strips.
Mix soups and salsa together in bowl.
In cake pan, layer in the following order:
tortilla strips, chicken, sauce mix. Keep layering until you run out.
Cover with cheese.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: puppy chow
directions: You will need 1 large paper grocery bag.

title: pumpkin cookies or bars
directions: Mix and sift flour, salt, baking soda and spices.
Beat eggs, then add sugar gradually and beat well.
Add oil, dates or raisins and nuts and then mix.
Add sifted ingredients, alternately with the pumpkin to the egg mixture, mixing just enough to keep the batter smooth.
Spoon our cookies into a greased cookie sheet.
Or for bars, pour into a greased pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake in a preheated 350° oven about 15 to 20 minutes for cookies or 30 minutes for the bars.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from the pan and cool on a cooling rack.
Frost if desired.

title: parthenon pizza("a greek-style pizza")
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray 4 individual casserole dishes with cooking spray.
Steam broccoli and spinach in same 2-quart saucepan for about 10 minutes.
Cut each pizza crust in half and press into casserole dishes.
Spread spaghetti sauce over crust. Mix cheeses and garlic together.
Add spinach/broccoli and mix thoroughly.
Pour equal amounts into each dish.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: eggplant salad
directions: Slice the eggplant lengthwise and then in 1/2-inch half moon slices.
Cut the pepper into julienne strips.
Peel the onions and slice into thin rounds.
Chop the tomatoes.
Pour olive oil into a large skillet.
Saute the onions and pepper until they are just wilted (about 5 minutes).
Add the garlic and eggplant; cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until the eggplant is cooked (about 10 to 15 minutes).
Add the sugar, oregano and pepper.
Stir and cook 2 minutes more.
Remove skillet from stove and mix in tomatoes and lemon juice.
Mix and place in serving bowl. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with stuffing.
Place 1/2 of chicken pieces in bottom of baking dish.
Spoon 1/2 can of cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 can of cream of chicken soup on top of chicken pieces.
Add 1/2 stuffing.
Pour 1 cup chicken broth over stuffing.
Repeat procedure for second time.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until bubbling.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese; let sit until soft.
Mix with sausage; add Bisquick.
Mix well and roll into balls.
Bake at 350° to 400° until brown.

title: diabetic sugar-free instant cocoa mix
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Place 3 heaping teaspoonfuls in cup and add hot boiling water.
Stir well.

title: pepper steak
directions: On medium heat, brown beef cubes in oil.
Add garlic salt, salt, soy sauce and 1/4 cup water.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes; add green pepper (diced) and onion.
Cook 10 minutes.
Stir in cornstarch and water.
Add tomatoes and cook until tender.
Serve over rice.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Blend sugar and butter; add eggs and blend well.
Add vanilla, salt, vinegar and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: taco salad
directions: Fix ahead.
Place ingredients in a bowl in layers.
Press down lightly.

title: heart sandwich cookies
directions: You will need a 3-inch heart shaped cookie cutter.

title: coconut punch
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Add ice and serve.

title: mirza qasemi(eggplant dish)
directions: Bake eggplants in 350° oven until cooked. This occurs when eggplants swell and the skin bursts. Remove from oven and cool slightly. Peel, cutting hard tops off. Cut into small pieces.

title: nut rolls
directions: Combine flour, butter and salt with a pastry cutter.
In another bowl, add sour cream, egg yolks, vanilla and yeast which has been dissolved in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients and work through with hands until dough is formed. Cover with cloth.
Refrigerate for 6 hours.
Form dough into small balls.
Pass each ball in sugar before rolling out and fill like a jelly roll.

title: brisket
directions: Paint meat with mixture (liquid smoke, garlic powder, onion salt and celery salt).
Wrap in foil.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Paint with 3 tablespoons Lea & Perrins Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Bake fat side up at 225° for 6 to 8 hours.
Slice thin.

title: potato salad
directions: Scrub potatoes and boil in salted water until soft.
Peel and slice into a bowl with alternate layers of onion, celery and eggs. Mix with the following dressing and refrigerate for 8 hours before serving.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: With electric beater, mix margarine and sugar until creamy. Add eggs, then oatmeal.
Add flour, gradually.
Add cinnamon, cooked raisins, applesauce and the nuts last.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet that has been oiled or greased.
Very moist and good.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and eggs.
Fold in sour cream. Sift dry ingredients and add.
Add vanilla.
Spoon half the batter into a greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Cover with a mixture of 1/2 cup chopped nuts, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 2 tablespoons brown sugar. Cover with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Let cool until just warm and remove from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Better the second day!

title: spam biscuits
directions: Mix all of the ingredients, except rolls.
Slice top from rolls; scoop out center.
Fill rolls with mix.
Replace top.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes at 350°.

title: jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple with juice in saucepan; sprinkle in Jell-O and stir until melted.
Let cool.
In large container, mix all remaining ingredients well, then mix in jello mixture.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour or longer.

title: chiffonade dressing(makes about 8 ounces)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a glass jar and shake thoroughly. An excellent dressing for mixed greens.

title: whipped icing
directions: Combine flour and milk in pan and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Cool.
Combine butter, sugar and vanilla and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat cooked milk mixture into butter mixture.
Beat on high speed until frosting resembles whipped cream.
This frosts 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add 1 cup cool water.
Let set until cool.
Add pineapple and pie filling.
Let congeal.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, nuts and sugar and spread over the top.

title: giant apple cookies
directions: Cream peanut butter, oleo and sugar together.
Beat in vanilla and eggs; add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add oats and apples.
Stir by hand.
Drop 1/4 cup mixture on cookie sheet and flatten.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: ann landers' meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Put into loaf pan (cover with two strips bacon if you like that flavor).
Pour tomato sauce over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: grandma's one bowl applesauce cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients into a bowl.
Blend in butter; add molasses, egg and applesauce.
Beat well.
Stir in raisins.
Bake in a greased and floured 8-inch square pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes; cool.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar or pour on glaze, using 1 1/2 tablespoons lemon juice and 3/4 cup confectioners sugar.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute green pepper in margarine.
Add seasonings, then water and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Bring to boil.
Add rice; stir well.
Cover and cook 20 minutes on low heat or until rice cooks dry.

title: beef breakfast rolls(serves 10)
directions: Combine ground beef, soup mix, catsup and thyme.
Separate refrigerator biscuits.
Flatten biscuits with hands.
Sprinkle wheat germ on half the biscuits.
Place 2 tablespoons beef mixture on top of wheat germ.
Top with another biscuit and press edges together.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve immediately or store in refrigerator and serve cold.
May be frozen and reheated.

title: quick spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Season with salt, pepper and chili powder.
Add soups and cheese.
Sprinkle in some Italian seasoning.
Simmer until hot and serve over plate of spaghetti.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and drain.
Cook onion and celery in the margarine. Cook broccoli according to directions and drain.
Mix all together and pour in casserole dish.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken; chop up and cover the bottom of casserole dish with chicken. Put Veg-All on top of chicken. Bring broth, soups, pepper, salt and eggs to a boil. Pour this over chicken. Mix flour, milk and butter and stir well. Pour this on top for crust. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: cheesy biscuit pizzas
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place biscuits on 2 greased cookie sheets.
Press each biscuit into a 5-inch round.
Spread 1 tablespoon pizza sauce on each round.
Top with shredded cheese and pepperoni.
Bake at 400° for 9 to 12 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Yields 10 pizzas.

title: fig pie
directions: Place figs in pie shell.
Mix other ingredients and pour over figs.
Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350° for 30 minutes more.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: In large container, combine jello with boiling water, stir until dissolved.
Fold in all at once - strawberries with juice, drained pineapple, bananas, nuts.
Pour 1/2 mixture in to 12x8x2 pan. Freeze until firm, (1 1/2 hours).
Spread with sour cream. Gently spoon on rest of mixture. Chill.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Take milk and pudding mix, beat by hand until blended.
Fold in Cool Whip and vanilla.
You need 1/2 box graham crackers.
Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Cover with half the pudding.
Layer 2 is graham crackers and rest of pudding.
Top with graham crackers.

title: old-fashioned corn dogs
directions: You will need wooden skewers (optional).

title: peach custard noodle pudding(side dish for chicken, turkey or veal)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Boil noodles according to package directions.
Beat eggs with 1/2 cup sugar and add milk and vanilla; mixing until well combined.
Drain noodles and pour into a buttered rectangular baking dish (10 x 13-inches).
Pour milk-egg mixture over noodles.
Arrange peach slices over top of noodles.

title: e-z pancakes
directions: Mix this all together and if batter needs to be thinner, add more cream and water.
Cook at 375° on electric griddle.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix well, folding in Cool Whip.
Pour into butter pie crusts. Garnish with orange slices.
A very good summer dessert.
This recipe makes 2 pies.

title: hot spicy cider
directions: Simmer on stove for 30 minutes all the ingredients.
Pour into a heatproof serving bowl.
Garnish with apple slices; sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Break tortillas into quarters. Mix the meat, taco seasoning, salt, tomatoes and tomato sauce. Cook until the meat is done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender with diced onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Add soup, sour cream, pimento and carrot.
Add two-thirds of margarine and two-thirds of stuffing to ingredients.
Place in greased casserole; top with remaining dressing and melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Strawberries should be at room temperature.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar with pectin in bowl.
Add in strawberries and juice.
Stir 3 times every 10 minutes for 30 minutes.
Add in rest of sugar. Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: aunt nancy's snickerdoodles
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Cream butter and sugars. Add to butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture to sugar mixture.
Add Rice Krispies and oatmeal.
Mix by hand.
Roll into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with thumb. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: squash onion casserole
directions: Slice summer squash and cook in small amount of water; add 3 tablespoons butter and 3/4 cup or 1 cup crumbs or crackers.
Add salt, pepper, beaten eggs, onion and milk.
Mix some cheese in the mixture.
Place the rest of cheese and bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: brown sugar dressing
directions: Mix and chill ingredients.
Use for fruit dip, using fresh and canned fruit.

title: graham delights
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Place grahams on foil.
Boil sugar, margarine and butter for 2 minutes.
Add nuts and pour over grahams.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Cool before taking off foil.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend in blender on high speed exactly 1 minute.

title: cheese ball
directions: Thoroughly mash garlic into salt until you can't see it.
Mix cheeses, parsley, paprika, 1 cup pecans and salt-garlic mixture; roll into several balls, then roll balls in remaining pecans.

title: dirt cake
directions: Combine ice cream and Cool Whip. Add crumbled Oreos.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.

title: scotch lobster
directions: Drop lobster tails into large pot of boiling salted water. Return to boil and cook 4 to 5 minutes (no longer). Drain and pour cold water over tails and drain again. With scissors, cut underside of each tail and remove the meat and slice into bite size pieces.

title: jelly
directions: Rub sugar cubes on skins of mandarins to remove peel oils. Combine juice, sugar and sugar cubes.
Stir over low heat until all sugar has dissolved.
Follow directions for making jelly on pectin container.
After mixture reaches jelly stage, if needed, carefully add food coloring until jelly is desired color.
Too much food coloring will muddy the color of the jelly.
Pour hot jelly into sterilized jars, seal.

title: cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour cherry pie filling in baking pan; spread evenly.
Pour cake mix over filling; do not stir.
Add pecans and coconut.
Place margarine in small saucepan; heat on low until margarine is melted.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until browned.
Yields 12 servings.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions.
As soon as removing from the oven, use a wooden spoon handle and poke holes in the cake.
Pour can of sweetened condensed milk over the top.
Follow with can of caramel topping.
Frost with cream cheese frosting and sprinkle with nuts.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Put oil in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and eggs.
Beat until creamy on low speed of mixer.
Sift flour again with salt, soda and baking powder.
Add small amount of flour mixture at a time to egg and sugar mixture, beating after each addition.
Remove from mixer and add apples and nuts by hand.
Bake in paper-lined 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: mama mia casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook noodles until tender. Drain. Rinse with cold water.
In a large kettle, brown hamburger and onion.
Drain off grease. Add corn, tomato soup, tomato paste and seasonings.
In greased casserole dish, alternate layers of noodles, meat mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine berries, sugar and water. Boil until all berries pop. Add Jell-O and marshmallows. Stir until marshmallows melt; cool. After cooling, add apples, celery and nuts.
Chill.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions putting the food coloring in the water to boil.
Drain pasta.
In blender, blend remaining ingredients and pour over mostaccioli.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 3 days before serving.
Has a delicious sweet sour taste.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Heat oven to 350°.
Saute green onions until tender. Stir in flour, salt and mustard.
Gradually add milk and bring to a boil. Simmer 3 minutes.
Add macaroni, shrimp, mushrooms, pimentos, etc.
Mix well.
Put in baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 30 minutes.

title: mardi gras slaw
directions: Mix all of the vegetables and sprinkle in the salt.
Squeeze by hand until the cabbage "weeps".
Drain the liquid and add remaining ingredients, mixing by hand or with a wooden spoon.
Add freshly ground pepper to taste.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt margarine and brown sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time.

title: hot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook elbow macs and drain.
In bottom of casserole, put cut up onion, half can of soup, half can of tomatoes, salt and pepper. Put half the macaroni, then repeat again, cutting up cheese and milk.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Cook fettucini.
Drain.
Stir in butter and toss until evenly coated.
Heat cream slowly in medium size saucepan; remove from heat.
Measure 3 tablespoons of cream into cup.
Beat eggs and add to 3 tablespoons cream and blend well.
Beat this mixture into cream in saucepan.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly, just until mixture begins to thicken.
Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Gently fold into noodles.

title: heavenly seven layer salad
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, layer lettuce, tomatoes, mushrooms, peas, cheese and onions.
Spread dressing over top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with bacon and additional cheese.
Serves 8.

title: roast eye of round
directions: Let roast stand outside the refrigerator until it reaches room temperature.
