Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Preheat oven to 500° and bake 5 minutes per pound.
Turn oven off and do not open oven door for 2 hours.
Roast will be pink.

title: cheese sauce
directions: In 4-cup glass measure, place butter.
Microwave on 70% power for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until melted.
Blend in flour, salt and milk; stir well.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes; stir. Microwave on High for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until thickened.
Stir in cheese until melted.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs; beat well.
Dissolve baking soda in hot water, then add to mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients; beat well.
Add chocolate chips last.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sweet sour basting sauce
directions: Blend first 9 ingredients until smooth.
Brush on meat while it broils, barbecues or roasts.
Garnish with pepper strips and pineapple.
Yields 1 cup.

title: ranch potato salad
directions: Cube and boil potatoes.
Add celery and onion.
Mix dressing; mix mayonnaise and water.
Add to potatoes and toss to coat.

title: banana fruit punch
directions: Stir water and sugar over low heat until dissolved.
Add juices and bananas.
Freeze in 1 gallon container.

title: vermont cheese ring
directions: In a blender or processor, blend oil, vinegar and spices.
On a plate, arrange cheese in a circle, alternating the two cheeses to make a ring.
Pour olives on top and in center of ring.
Pour the oil and vinegar mixture on top of all.
To serve, place cheese on toasted bread with olives and marinate mixture.

title: deviled egg pate
directions: Peel
eggs
and
cut them in half lengthwise.
Mash the yolks and
add
anchovies,
mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, parsley
and
lemon juice.	Mix into paste and refill the whites. Serve slightly chilled.
Use as part of antipasto or as canapes.

title: orange glaze chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt (if desired) and pepper. Coat chicken. In a skillet, heat oil on medium. Brown chicken. Spread marmalade on top of chicken.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Add orange juice and simmer 10 to 15 minutes until chicken juice runs clear.

title: easy chocolate pie(makes 8 servings)
directions: Microwave marshmallows and 2 tablespoons of milk in medium bowl on High for 45 seconds.
Stir well, then cool in refrigerator for 15 minutes, then stir in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Pour 2 cups of milk into a large bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk for 2 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute or until it thickens.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust.
Arrange cookies over pudding. Spread marshmallow mixture on top.
Refrigerate for 4 hours until set.
Serve with chocolate topping.

title: coconut candy
directions: Mix candy, coconut and nuts. Add milk and mix well. Pour mixture into baking dish and cook in oven for approximately 30 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and add sugar and flavorings. Mix well and drop on wax paper. Let dry; turn over to dry on other side. Very good.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Saute onion.
Brown ground beef in skillet and add salt to taste.
Drain grease.
Add tomato paste to beef and onion and mix well.
Cook noodles in boiling salted water and drain.

Layer ingredients in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish in the following manner: noodles, Mozzarella and cottage cheese, ground beef mixture. Repeat layers in order to have two layers each of noodles, cheese and beef.
Cover and microwave until hot in center (approximately 10 minutes) or bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mary lou's jello salad
directions: Dissolve red hots in 1/2 cup boiling water (red hots usually don't dissolve entirely).
Use red hot-water plus boiling water to make 2 cups.
Dissolve jello.
Set until slightly thickened.
Break up cranberry sauce with fork.
Add celery, diced apples and pecans to jello mixture.
Spread half of jello mixture in a 9 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch pan.
Set until firm.
Spread with sour cream and top with remaining jello.
Set until firm.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaf.
Yields 12 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Place ingredients in a saucepan and slowly bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 stick butter.
Beat with mixer until smooth.

title: deluxe chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together thoroughly.
Spoon out on cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add taco mix and tomato sauce; let simmer 10 minutes.
Cook rice.
Cut lettuce and tomatoes up.
Heat Ro-Tel dip in microwave.
Place rice on plate first; add meat, corn chips, lettuce and tomatoes.
Place Ro-Tel dip on top.
Enjoy! Yields 4 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil, eggs and carrots; add all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peach and nectarine cobbler
directions: Preheat over to 375°.
Butter 2 8 or 10-inch round baking dishes.
Combine the flour and plain sugar in a bowl or a food processor.
(All ingredients should be cold.)
Add 1 cup chilled butter, cut into small pieces.
Process for about 10 seconds or until mixture resembles coarse meal.
(To mix by hand, combine the dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Use a pastry blender or 2 table knives and cut in the butter until the mixture resembles coarse meal.)
Add ice water a few drops at a time just until dough holds together, without being wet or sticky.
Test the dough by squeezing a small amount together.
If it is too crumbly, add a bit more water.

title: pasta with broccoli and garlic
directions: Saute broccoli and garlic for 5 minutes.
Cook linguine al dente.
Add cooked broccoli to pasta and sprinkle with Romano cheese.

title: granny's chicken and dressing
directions: Boil chicken breast adding salt while cooking.
Cook until tender.
Set aside broth.
Boil 6 eggs.
Using receipt on the package, cook cornbread.
Saute celery, onions in oleo.
Crumble cornbread in large bowl.
Mix in chopped boiled eggs, and onions. Add chicken broth that was set aside, chicken (cut up).
Add pepper and salt to taste.
Mix in remaining 6 eggs (beaten).
Add can chicken broth if needed.
Do not get too soupy or too dry.
Pour mixture into greased baking dish and cook at 350 degrees for about 45 min.
It can be mixed up the day before, covered and refrigerated overnight.

title: shake and bake for chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Cut in shortening until mixture is crumbly.
Stor in tightly covered container.
Makes nearly 3 cups.
Dip chicken in milk and then in coating mix. Arrange in a shallow pan and bake at 350° until chicken is tender.

title: ham potato casserole
directions: Make a thin white sauce using the margarine, flour and milk. In a slightly greased 2-quart casserole, alternate layers of potatoes, ham and cheese in that order.
Pour white sauce over the mixture.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: my own dried apple stack cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer (except dry ingredients; add them last).

title: bite-size cheese balls
directions: Combine cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, shredded carrot and chopped nuts.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in pecans.
Cover and chill.
To serve, place pretzel into each.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: crappie deluxe casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13 in. baking dish with butter.
Sprinkle garlic powder.
Layer Crappie fillets in dish and salt & pepper.
Chop green onions finely and sprinkle over fillets.
Spread cheese over fish and onions.
In a small bowl, combine sour cream and soup; mix well.
Spoon mixture over fish.
Sprinkle crushed crackers over the top.
Bake at 300 degrees for 1 hour 45 min.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Sprinkle sliced cucumbers with salt.
Cover with parchment paper or foil and place weights on top.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Drain liquid from cucumbers; measure and set aside.
Measure white vinegar and water so that, combined in equal parts, you will have the same amount from cucumbers.
Mix 3 liquids and add sugar (1 1/2 tablespoons sugar for each cup of liquid).
Adjust dressing to suit your taste and pour over cucumbers.
Garnish with watercress.
Serves 6.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Cook peas according to package and drain well.
Combine all ingredients.
Place in a 2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Cover top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: squash patties
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, mash squash.
Add onion, eggs, cheese, salt, and pepper.
Mix well.
Add flour until dough is pasty.
Fry in oil until brown.

title: fish balls
directions: Grind the fillets.
Fry onions in oil until tender and combine with ground fish.
Add rice, water, lemon juice, salt and pepper (to taste).
Mix thoroughly.
Shape mixture into small balls with wet hands and then roll in bread crumbs.
Cook in hot oil until delicately browned.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put eggs in a medium bowl.
Dip each chicken breast
in eggs until well coated.
In another bowl, combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese; mix well.
Roll each chicken breast in the dry mixture until well coated.
Place evenly in an 8-inch baking dish.
Melt butter and pour on top of chicken. Bake in oven for 30 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, water and marshmallows until dissolved; let cool. Cool; add other ingredients.

title: best ever pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into pie shells.
If not sweet enough to your liking, add more brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes three 9-inch pies.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown roast in margarine.
Add all ingredients; simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Cover; check often to see if liquid has evaporated.

title: orange cake
directions: In large bowl of electric mixer, let egg whites warm to room temperature (about 1 hour).
Measure flour.
Sift about 2 cups flour once on a sheet of waxed paper.
Fill cups lightly to overflowing.
With spatula, cut off excess to make 1 3/4 level cups.
Sift flour with salt; set aside.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate until serving time.

title: lobster newburg
directions: In medium saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in flour; cook 1 minute.
Add lobster, salt, paprika and sherry.
In small bowl, combine beaten egg yolks and cream.
Gradually add yolk mixture to lobster mixture; blend well.
Cook over very low heat until thickened, stirring frequently.
Serve over toast points or patty shells.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix, chill and serve.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Boil sweet potatoes and mash.
Put sugar and vanilla flavoring to taste in.
Roll in balls.
Roll in crushed corn flakes.
Put marshmallow in center.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Can be frozen.

title: amazin' raisin cake
directions: Mix the first 10 ingredients at low speed.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Pour into three 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, until done.
Fill and frost with whipped topping.

title: orange glaze
directions: Mix ingredients and spread on ham about 30 minutes before removing from oven.

title: banana split cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Make crust of cracker crumbs and 1 stick margarine.
Press on bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Bake until firm.
Mix 1 stick melted margarine with icing sugar and Philadelphia cheese.
Spread over cracker crust.
Next spread drained pineapple over icing layer and cover with sliced bananas to cover.
Spread Cool Whip over all.
Either add nuts, cherries and drizzle syrup over top or sprinkle some of cracker crumbs (take from mixture).
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Dissolve sugar and syrup in heavy frying pan, stirring until tan in color.
Add peanuts and continue stirring.
Remove from stove and add baking soda.
Pour mixture on greased cookie sheet. When cooled, break into bite-size pieces.

title: mexicali chili dip
directions: Combine sour cream with Bleu cheese, lemon juice and chili sauce.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Makes 1 cup.
Delicious with fish sticks.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to cream mixture, alternating with apples. Stir in pecans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour
in tube pan.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes after reaching boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Let melt, then add oats, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: funny face sandwiches
directions: Spread bread with peanut butter.
Make a face using the "fixings!"

title: mom's pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 30 minutes. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: poor man's delight
directions: Boil noodles; drain and set aside.
Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in butter.
Add hamburger and brown.
Add cream corn and tomato sauce.
Cook for about 20 minutes.
Add Parmesan cheese.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Saute onion and celery in shortening until transparent.
Add 1 tablespoon tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat to cool.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Spread some cheese on top of potatoes.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then before serving, sprinkle bread crumbs or rest of cheese on top.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Shoo Fly Pie and
Apple
Pandowdy
makes your tummy say yummy and your mouth say howdy.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and bacon; drain.
Put in large pot. Add beans; cover and simmer.
The longer, the better.
Add balance of ingredients.
This freezes very well.
Makes large batch.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Mix noodles and sour cream.
Set for 10 minutes.
Put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle crushed garlic over noodles. Sprinkle salt over noodles.
Pour spaghetti sauce over noodles.

title: warm spinach salad
directions: Remove bacon from frying pan and dice bacon pieces.

title: cheese ring
directions: Grind the first 3 ingredients together.
Cook the the remaining ingredients.
Put vinegar in while dressing cooks.
May curdle but will be alright.
Cook until smooth and pour over cheese.
Mix.
Grease cheese ring well.
Pour mixture in ring. Cook for 30 minutes or more, until brown, at 350°.

title: oyster cracker tidbits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Stir in crackers.
Pour oil over cracker mix and stir from bottom, mixing well.
Pour crackers into baking pan and heat in 225° oven for 5 minutes; stir and heat for another 5 minutes.
Store in airtight containers and will keep several weeks.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Night before, brown and drain sausage.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over sausage in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cover and refrigerate either overnight or a minimum of 2 hours. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: butter chews
directions: Cream the butter, add sugar, and beat well.
Then blend thoroughly with the flour.
Pat mixture into a greased cake pan and bake in a moderately hot oven, 375° for 15 minutes, or until a delicate brown.
Now add the brown sugar to the beaten egg yolks and blend in well.
Add chopped nuts and coconut, then fold in the beaten egg whites.
Pour over baked mixture and return to the oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into 1 in. squares and dust with confectioners sugar.
Makes 35 squares.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Brown rice in margarine. Add chopped onion and saute for a short time.
Meanwhile, heat water with beef bouillon cubes until cubes are dissolved. Add salt.
May cook on top of stove or in oven.
If cooking on top, bring rice mixture to a boil and turn to lowest setting after stirring once with a fork.
Keep covered until done (approximately 30 to 40 minutes).
If cooking in oven, use 350°.

title: easy cheesy corn bake
directions: Combine all items, except cheese.
Place in baking dish; top with cheese.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: *stuffed cabbage
directions: In a large pot of boiling water, add cored cabbage and simmer. Remove leaves of cabbage as they soften.
Allow to cool and carefully remove large rib of each leaf.
(Or cut out core of cabbage, wrap tightly in plastic wrap and microwave on High for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cabbage will turn bright green and yield to pressure.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Unwrap and rinse under cold running water.)

title: dump salad
directions: Dump all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well. Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: egg brunch casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Place in a well-greased, 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer bacon (cooked, drained and broken), cheese and parsley flakes over the bread.
Beat eggs and milk until fluffy.
Pour over the top of everything.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until eggs are set.

title: herb stuffing mix
directions: Slice bread into 1/2-inch cubes.
Spread bread cubes evenly in a large shallow baking pan.
Toast bread cubes in a 300° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden, stirring once.
Remove from oven.
Cool slightly.

title: mississippi spice muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix in applesauce and spices.
Sift together salt, baking soda and flour. Add to applesauce mixture and beat well.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in greased mini muffin pans at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.
Batter will keep indefinitely in refrigerator.
Baked muffins freeze well.

title: potato croquettes
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Divide mixture into 8 portions.
Shape into croquettes.
Roll in cracker crumbs.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours.
Combine butter and paprika.
Drizzle over croquettes. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.

title: pralines
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and Karo to boil. Turn to a low medium heat.
Cook 15 minutes, stirring constantly. Add nuts. Spoon onto a buttered cookie sheet. Cool; wrap in Saran Wrap. Enjoy.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Stir in Eagle Brand milk and 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Drain crushed pineapple.
Add to mixture.
Add the Cool Whip and blend all together.
Add pecan pieces and mix.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crusts and chill.

title: easy fresh asparagus dip
directions: Mix all together except asparagus. Chill. Serve with asparagus.

title: spicy chili mac
directions: In skillet, brown meat and onion.
Drain fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, undrained beans, tomato sauce, seasonings, 1/2 cup water and 1 1/4 teaspoons salt.
Bring to boiling, add macaroni.
Cover and simmer over low heat, stirring often, for 15 to 20 minutes, or until macaroni is done.

title: fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips with condensed milk in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir in the other ingredients. Spread evenly into wax paper or buttered pan.
Chill about 2 hours and cut into squares.

title: corn pudding
directions: Add sugar, flour, salt and pepper to the corn.
Then add the beaten eggs and the melted butter.
Last stir in the milk.
Mix well.
Pour into a well-greased (use butter) casserole dish.
Bake in a 400° oven for approximately one hour or until light brown on top.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Pinch 1/2 angel food cake into large pieces into a large bowl, cover with 1/2 fruit.
Cover with 1/2 pudding, then repeat with remainder of angel food cake, fruit and pudding.
Top with whipped cream and garnish with nuts or fruit.

title: butter sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks, add sugar.
Add cooled milk and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients. Fold in the butter. Bake at 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan.
Freezes well and needs no frosting.

title: chicken marengo
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and thyme; brown in oil. Set aside.
Saute onion and garlic in same pan.
Add chicken and rest of ingredients.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: praline bars
directions: Break graham crackers into 3 sections. Line a 10 x 15 jelly roll pan with crackers. Bring butter and sugar to a boil in a saucepan. Boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour evenly over crackers. Sprinkle with pecans. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Cool. Remove from pan with spatula and cool on waxed paper.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Scramble cooked hamburger.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour over cooked noodles.
Add salt and pepper as desired.
Mix well.

title: passover carrot-nut cake
directions: Grind carrots and walnuts with the fine blade of a food grinder or use a food processor.

In a small mixer bowl, beat egg yolks until light (about 5 minutes); gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating until thick and lemon colored (about 5 minutes longer). Blend in walnuts, carrots and vanilla; stir in matzo meal.
Wash beaters thoroughly.
In a large mixer bowl, beat egg whites to stiff peaks (tips stand straight).
Fold some of the egg whites into matzo mixture to lighten, then fold matzo mixture into egg whites.
Turn batter into ungreased 8 or 8 1/2-inch springform pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes or until tests done.
Good for Seder meal.

title: play dough
directions: Mix 2 1/2 cups flour, salt and alum.
Add the water and oil and stir.
Knead and add about 1 cup more flour; add coloring to desired shade.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoon into hot grease and fry until golden brown.

title: lemon-lime punch
directions: Run warm water over the container of sherbet for about 2 minutes.
Gently squeeze the container as the water runs over it. When sherbet breaks loose, remove the lid, gently squeeze sherbet into punch bowl.
Pour lemonade over the sherbet.
Never chop up the sherbet.
Prepare about 30 minutes before serving.

title: western ranger cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugars.
Mix well and add eggs.
Sift flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spicy hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef and onions. Drain. Add cumin and pepper to beef and stir. Put beef in large saucepan and add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: dill crackers
directions: Pour 2 bags of the oyster crackers into a large bowl.
Slowly add canola oil mixing carefully with a spoon.
Mix Ranch dressing and dill weed; stir well into cracker mixture.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup of hot water.
Beat milk and sugar until it stand in peaks (beat milk first, then add sugar). Add jello; mix well.
Pour into crumb crust and chill.
Makes 2 large pies.

title: quick sesame ginger chicken
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Set aside.
Place chicken between 2 sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap and flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using meat mallet.
Brush half of soy sauce mixture over chicken, both sides.

title: corn bread cake
directions: Mix with mixer.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook until done, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fluff's filling(a pennsylvania dutch recipe)
directions: Rip bread into bite sized pieces.
Pour potatoes over.
Mix in onion.
Mix eggs, flour, salt, water and parsley.
Pour over bread/potato mixture.
Put dabs of butter in bottom of casserole. Add a little broth from whatever meat you're making.
Pour potato mixture into pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally during baking.

title: country fair casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions and drain well. Combine ground beef, onions and seasonings in a heavy skillet, stirring to crumble.
Saute until lightly browned.
Drain off pan drippings. Stir in cream of celery soup, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in macaroni and remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: better than sex cake or pigging out cake
directions: In a bowl, mix the vanilla instant pudding according to directions. Add pineapple. Blend in Cool Whip; refrigerate.

title: low-fat carrot cake and molasses icing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 13 x 9-inch pan with foil.
Spray with cooking spray.
Combine first 7 ingredients in bowl.
Beat sugar, pineapple, oil and vanilla in mixer bowl until smooth. Beat in dry ingredients until just combined.
Stir in carrots. Beat egg whites in small bowl to stiff peaks.
Fold into carrot mixture, 1/2 at a time.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 40 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack. Invert cake onto wax paper.
Remove pan and foil.
Ice with Molasses Icing.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Place on greased pan.
Cut dough in a circle.
Place a teaspoon of preserves and fold over and seal.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: veggie delight
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; toss in fat-free dressing (Italian or Spring Garden).
You may also use your own fat-free dressing.
Two cups has only 150 calories.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Combine peas, celery, pepper, tomato, garlic, 2 onions, mushrooms, pimento and salad dressing.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours, stirring once in awhile.
Drain and spoon into lettuce lined bowl.
Garnish with bacon bits and onions.

title: croquettes
directions: Make a white sauce of first 3 ingredients.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Make it into the shape you require.
When cold, cover with egg and bread crumbs.
Fry 3 to 4 minutes, until light brown.

title: texas sweet potato bread
directions: Mix the liquids, except the water together.
Then mix the flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon, and nutmeg together.
Combine with liquid mixture.
Add potatoes, nuts, and water.
Place in a bundt pan or 3 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken divan
directions: Rub oil on chicken breasts.
Salt, pepper and paprika chicken (to taste).
Place chicken breasts in pan with dots of butter on each piece.
Bake 15 minutes at 300°.

title: english country herb stuffing(a rich dressing to be eaten with turkey or chicken.)
directions: Melt the butter in a skillet. Fry the onion and bacon for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Add bread crumbs. Stir and cook for another minute. Stir in remaining ingredients, adding a little milk, as necessary, to bind the stuffing to a moist consistency.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, then dice.
Cook chopped onions until tender.
Add to bacon; add beans, mustard, sauces, sugar and cloves.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: vegetable garden pasta medley
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pasta, in a large bowl, tossing well.
Cover; let stand at room temperature.
Cook pasta according to package directions, omitting salt and fat.
Drain. Combine pasta and vegetable mixture in a large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Serve immediately.
Makes 12 servings.

title: mac 'n cheese soup
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain and set aside. Chop broccoli and onion. Combine broccoli, onion and water in 4-quart pan. Bring to boil and cook 2 minutes. Do not drain. Stir in cooked macaroni, cheese sauce from package, milk, cheese soup and ham. Return to boil, stirring occasionally. Yields 6 servings.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into 9-inch shallow baking dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned. Sprinkle with green chilies.
Serve with tortilla chips, crackers, etc.
Makes 2 cups.

title: favorite holiday cheese ball
directions: Mix together cheeses, worcestershire sauce and onion.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers.

title: rocky road
directions: Melt chocolate bars.
Beat smooth.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Butter an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Pour mixture into pan. Chill.
Cut when firm.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions.
Let stand overnight in salt water. Drain well.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Boil syrup well.
Drop in cucumber and onion slices and let boil once good.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all together in blender. Store in refrigerator for short periods of time only.

title: the danvillian
directions: Layer ham, turkey and cheese on a hoagie roll.
Heat in microwave.
Add lettuce, tomato and mayonnaise.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix egg yolks and flour together in medium size pot or pan. Cook over low heat.
Pour in milk, stirring constantly.
Add margarine, flour and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool.

title: guacamole
directions: Cut avocados in half, remove pits and scoop the flesh out of their shells into a large bowl.
Immediately add the lemon juice, not pepper sauce, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Toss well.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix all but soup and water.
Form into balls.
Brown in frypan.
Pour soup mix over and boil slowly one hour.

title: zippy corned beef salad
directions: Combine beef, potatoes, pickles, onions, egg and olive.
In another bowl, combine mustard, oil, vinegar, garlic powder and pepper.
Pour over beef mixture; toss.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.
Serve beef mixture on salad greens torn into bite size pieces.
Sprinkle cheese over top before serving.

title: devil's food cake
directions: In small saucepan, melt chocolate.
Pour into large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Cream with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients. Beat on low speed for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When cool, frost with Marshmallow Fluff Icing.

title: peas and onions
directions: Cook peas and onions in
small amount of boiling water. Add 1 tablespoon margarine and
teaspoon salt.
Mix cornstarch with milk.
Add this to	the
vegetables
and
bring to boil.
Serve hot.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all but 1 cup pecans.
Make into ball.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Next day, roll in remaining pecans. Great for holiday parties.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump can of applesauce into pan. Dump can of pineapple on top.
Spread cake mix over top.
Melt margarine on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over margarine.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken with carrots and onion until completely cooked, about 1 hour.
Remove chicken and continue vegetables with 8 ounces of egg noodles for 5 minutes.
Drain mixture and set aside.

title: cap'n crunch peanut butter candy
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add peanut butter.
Stir in cereal.
Coat well.
Drop in clusters on wax paper.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat together butter and sugar; add eggs and dry ingredients. Roll thin.
If you like chocolate chips or peanut butter chips, punch them in cookies after you get them on cookie sheet, then sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until done.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine lemon juice and grated lemon rind. Gradually stir into Eagle Brand milk. Add egg yolks and stir until well blended.
Pour into chilled crust. Add cream of tartar to egg whites. Beat until almost stiff enough to hold a peak.
Add sugar gradually, beating until stiff but not dry.
Pile lightly on pie filling. Bake in slow oven at 325° until lightly browned, about 15 minutes. Cool.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add flour, soda and salt and mix together.
Add chips.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° until bubbly on top, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
This will make 3 layers.
Let cool; slit layers in half to make 6 layers.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Crust:
Melt butter and mix with cracker crumbs.
Press in pan.
Add 1 cup crushed nuts before pressing in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes in salted water; drain well.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, eggs, onions and cheese.
Pour mixture over broccoli in 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chocolate earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover bottom of pan with nuts and coconut.

title: oreo like cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla in mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt; add alternately with milk to creamed mixture until ingredients are combined.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 12 minutes, or just until set (do not overbake). Cool 1 minute; remove from sheet.
Cool completely.
Prepare filling.
Spread bottom of 1 cookie with about 1 tablespoon filling.
Cover with another cookie.
Repeat with remaining cookies and filling.
Makes about 15 cookies.

title: aunt mary's key lime pie
directions: Separate eggs, reserve whites.
Add canned milk in steady stream to egg yolks that have been creamed.
Add salt.
Add lime juice and rind.
Whip altogether.
Whip egg whites until foamy. Add 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar and whip until whites hold peaks, but are not dry.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, a tablespoon at a time, beating all the time.
Pour first mixture into baked shell and top with meringue.
Sprinkle with finely grated rind.
Bake until meringue is golden.
Watch it.

title: thai dried salty beef(side dish)
directions: Will also need paper towels.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cut in shortening until well blended.
Slowly add milk, using only enough to make soft dough but not sticky.
Turn dough onto floured board. Knead a few strokes.
Roll 3/4 inch thick.
Cut with cutter or glass or square with knife.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes until done.
Butter tops and serve.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Pour butter mixture into egg mixture.
Add flour. Mix well.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 10 x 13-inch pan.
Spread Marshmallow Creme over hot cake.
Pour icing over Marshmallow Creme.

title: vodka slush
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in the freezer for 12 hours.
Mix with a spoon and keep frozen.

title: hennie's salad dressing
directions: Mix and use over green salad, avocado or most other salads.

title: date with dates(no extra sugar in this recipe!)
directions: Wash the apricots well in warm water, then chop.
Put into a saucepan with the dates and water.
Heat gently for 15 minutes or until soft; remove any pits.
Place in a blender or food processor along with the raisins and nuts and whiz to a puree.
Press the mixture into a lightly greased cake pan, making it about 1/2-inch deep.
Chill, then cut into 24 squares.

title: white fruit cake - 10 pounds
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in large pan.
Separate egg yolks and whites.
Add yolks (one at a time) to creamed mixture.
Add sifted flour and grape juice alternately.
Roll chopped fruit in additional flour until pieces separate.
Add fruit and mix well. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Batter should be almost pouring consistency.
If not, add additional grape juice.
With nonsalted shortening, generously grease tube cake pan and line with Kraft brown paper.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours for a 10 pound cake.
(If recipe is halved for 5 pound cake, bake for 4 hours.)

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Coat each chicken piece evenly with flour mixture.
Roll each chicken piece in melted butter.
Place chicken in single layer, skin side down, in a greased shallow baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven about 1 hour, turning once at the end of 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: granny's homemade kraut
directions: Chop cabbage fine using sharp knife.
Take stone jar, layer cabbage, layer salt, alternating until jar is almost full.
Press down with a plate.
Weight plate down with a rock and cover with cloth.
Let it set until fermented, about 2 weeks.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk until it forms a soft ball in water. Remove from heat, add peanut butter and marshmallow.
Cool and beat until creamy.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix chopped pecans and coconut; pour in pan.
Mix German chocolate cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour batter evenly on top of nuts and coconut. Do not stir.
Mix softened butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar; beat until smooth.
Pour on top of cake batter.
Do not stir. Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients for 4 minutes. Save 3 tablespoons of the strawberry juice for the frosting. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix sour cream and mayo.
Add remaining ingredients (excluding bread).
Cover and chill at least 4 hours.
Cut out top of bread. Remove soft insides.
Put dip inside.
Serve with bread around bread bowl.
Also good with veggies.

title: baked vidalia onion with country ham and shiitake mushrooms
directions: In a mixing bowl, blend butter, brown sugar, vinegar, glaze or bouillon, rosemary and thyme.
Place each mushroom cap on a 12 x 12-inch square of foil and top with one-fourth of the butter mixture.
Top each with an onion and draw the foil from 4 corners to top center.
Seal well.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes, or until soft.
Remove onions and mushroom mixture to serving plates and reserve juices.
Combine reserved cooking juices from onions in saucepan and gently heat with ham, chives and tomatoes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Divide sauce among onions and serve.
Makes 4 appetizer servings.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon in crust.
Refrigerate until chilled, at least 5 hours.

title: cabbage and tomato soup
directions: Place all ingredients, except lemons and sour salt in pot.
Let cook 2 hours.
Add sour salt, brown sugar, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Let simmer one more hour.
Taste for any needed seasonings.

title: southern goulash
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef until done, drain and transfer to a large pot or Dutch oven. Add tomatoes, rice, pepper, onion, salt, pepper and bay leaves. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Remove from heat and cool. Place in refrigerator overnight. Reheat the next day and serve.

title: pizzeles
directions: Mix ingredients, adding milk if needed for right consistency. Drop by spoonful.
Cook with pizzele cookie/waffle iron as directed.

title: great-grandmother's sugar pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except pie crust in large bowl; mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, eggs and butter.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Mix gently and pour in greased casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and bake in 350° oven until bubbly and brown on top.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: apple or peach crisp
directions: Fill an 8 x 8-inch pan with a layer of fruit.
Sprinkle fruit with sugar, vanilla, cinnamon and cold water.
Mix together until crumbly the flour, margarine and sugar.
Sprinkle mixture over fruit and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Line a 15 x 10-inch baking pan with waxed paper.
Spray with nonstick cooking spray.
Set aside.
In small skillet, bring to a boil syrup and pecans.
Reduce heat to low; simmer uncovered without stirring 12 minutes.
Pour praline mixture onto waxed paper.
Spread to form single layer.
Let stand until hardened, about 45 minutes.
Break into pieces.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Butter an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
In heavy medium-sized saucepan, melt chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Spread mixture in the prepared pan.
Cover and chill several hours or until firm. Cut into squares.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds of candy.

title: cora's jumbo raisin cookies
directions: In saucepan, bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes the raisins and water.
Remove and let cool to room temperature.
(Do not drain.)
In a large bowl, sift together all dry ingredients. In separate bowl, cream shortening and gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add the eggs, then the cool raisins with any liquid.
Then add the dry ingredients, blending well.
Add the vanilla and nuts last.
Drop by tablespoon about 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and salt in 2-quart casserole dish. Cook in microwave over 19 minutes on High power. Stir every 5 minutes. Beat egg whites. Add syrup. Beat for 12 minutes. Add vanilla and nuts. Drop from teaspoon.

title: grandma liebrand's pancakes
directions: Mix together and fry on hot griddle.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together butter, sugar and almond extract.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with strawberries to creamed mixture.

title: betty's fudge
directions: In a saucepan, mix the ingredients and bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 more minutes, stirring.
Remove from heat.
Stir in a 12 ounce package of semi-sweet chocolate chips until melted.
Add a 7 ounce container of fluff, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 cup chopped nuts.

title: veggies "n" sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and stir, allowing mixture to bubble well.
Add liquid from can or the liquid from fresh veggies (approximately 1 cup liquid).
Season.
I use salt, pepper, garlic and onion salt.
Pour over veggies.
Really good over fresh carrots (sliced and cooked).

title: healthy bread
directions: Boil raisins and water together for 5 minutes.
Cool and combine with other ingredients.
Grease a loaf pan and pour mixture in it.
Bake for one hour at 350°.

title: pork chops with rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place rice in a large baking dish; mix. Add soup, water, soy sauce and onion.
Add drained vegetables. Place pork chops, seasoned with salt and pepper, on top.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Serves 6.
Also can be used with chicken breasts.

title: oriental baked sea trout
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sprinkle fish lightly with salt inside and out.
Combine orange juice, soy sauce, ginger and garlic. Tear off sheet of heavy-duty aluminum foil large enough to wrap fish.
Layer half of onion slices lengthwise down center of foil. Place fish on onions.
Pour sauce on top and inside cavity of fish.
Top with remaining onion and carrots.
Wrap.
Place packet on baking sheet.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground chuck in a frypan; drain.
Add chili beans (2 cans of water) and tomato soup (2 cans of water).
Add finely chopped onion and flour and pepper.
Cook slowly for about 2 1/2 hours.

title: banana freeze punch
directions: Mix water and sugar and boil for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Add bananas and fruit juices and mix well.
Pour into large container and freeze.
Remove from freezer a few hours before serving, just long enough to become slush.
Place in punch bowl and add ginger ale.
Serves 50.

title: dill pickled okra
directions: Use small, tender pods of okra; cut with as much stem as possible.
Wash and drain.
Prick okra and pack into clean jars. Place a small bunch of green dill in each jar with okra.
Boil water, vinegar and salt together until salt is dissolved.
Fill jars with boiling hot brine.
Put on caps, screwing the bands until tight.
Process jars 5 minutes in boiling hot water baths.

title: red punch
directions: Mix ingredients together and add ginger ale just before serving.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Sift flour and	soda
together.
Cream butter or margarine and sugar until well
blended.	Add
eggs, one at a time, beating well on high speed of mixer after each addition until light and fluffy.
Using low speed of mixer, mix in lemon rind or add vanilla to buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients alternately with
milk to creamed mixture.
Mix only until flour is moistened.
Pour into
greased
10-inch tube pan or greased Bundt pan.
Bake
at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
May be frozen. Serves 16 to 20.

title: lorna doone lemon delight
directions: Mix together crushed cookies, margarine and walnuts.
Press in a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Beat pudding and milk.
Spread on cream cheese mixture. Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: brownie pie
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in cookie crumbs, nuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly in lightly buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Spread top with sweetened whipped cream.
Chill well 2 to 3 hours.
Trim with curls of shaved unsweetened chocolate or ground nuts.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with crackers or chips of your choice.

title: laurel's corn
directions: Drain corn and add butter. Mix, heat and eat.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: In a large skillet, saute onions in margarine until tender. Add soups, stirring until well combined and creamy smooth. Slice or cube Velveeta into soup mixture and stir until cheese melts. Add broccoli and rice; stir well and remove from heat. Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: layered banana pineapple dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press evenly onto bottom of a 13 x 9-inch dish or pan.
Arrange banana slices over crust.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in milk and add pudding mixes.
Beat until well blended and spread over banana slices.
Spoon pineapple over pudding mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until ready to serve.

title: quick spice cake
directions: Combine Miracle Whip and sugar.
Combine all dry ingredients to first mixture with combined water and molasses.
Bake in greased 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: play clay
directions: Boil water.
Add powdered alum, oil and salt.
Pour over flour.
Mix and put on low heat.
Stir until it feels like clay. Add desired food coloring.
Store in airtight containers.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In oblong (14 1/2 x 8 1/4 x 2-inch) pan, layer, in order, chicken, Veg-All and eggs.
In a pan, heat broth, butter and soup; pour over layers.
Mix well the flour, milk, baking powder and salt; pour evenly over ingredients in pan.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: date-orange bars
directions: Boil dates, sugar, flour and water until thick, then let cool. Spread 1/2 of batter in greased 9 x 13 pan or smaller.
Cover with candy orange slices (which have been sliced lengthwise in 3 pieces).
Spread date mixture over orange slices.
Spread on remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut in small bars.
These bars freeze well.

title: holiday sweet potatoes
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and 1/2 cup butter.
Place in greased baking dish.
Combine brown sugar, flour, 1/3 cup butter and pecans; sprinkle over potato mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Blend margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add oats and corn flakes.
Sift dry ingredients; add to mixture.
Add chips, nuts and coconut.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: egg custard
directions: Bake in uncooked pie shell at 350° (if desired, add 7 teaspoons of chocolate).

title: black walnut pudding
directions: Mix altogether and boil for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate cinnamon cake
directions: Boil first four ingredients.
Let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheesy chicken soup
directions: Cook all the veggies in the chicken broth until done. Add salt and pepper. Add cream; let come to a boil. Slowly add the thickened mixture to the broth. Add chicken and cheese. Heat and serve. Good with hot bread and a salad.

title: dinner in a pumpkin
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add ground venison; cook until brown, stirring frequently.
Drain; mix in soy sauce, brown sugar, mushrooms and soup.
Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in cooked rice; spoon into pumpkin shell. Replace top.
Bake at 350° for an hour.
Serve from pumpkin.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers and melt marshmallows.
Mix with chopped fruits.
Mix marshmallows in milk in double boiler and pour over fruits, nuts and wafers.
Pack in a lined tube pan.

title: key lime cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool completely.
Poke holes in top and dust with powdered sugar.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Mix eggs, butter, brown sugar, buttermilk and jam.
Add soda and spices to flour.
Mix these together; add nuts and cherries. Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: skillet pork chop supper
directions: Brown pork chops; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer 1 hour or until tender.
You can do more carrots, potatoes and pork chops if you want.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Beat dry cake mix, butter and eggs in large mixing bowl at low speed until crumbly.
Press lightly in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan. Beat 2 eggs with 3/4 cup sugar, 2 teaspoons vanilla and cream cheese until smooth and fluffy.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until set.
Mix sour cream, 1/4 cup sugar and remaining 1 tablespoon vanilla.
Spread over cheese; cool.
Spread cherry filling over sour cream mixture.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Serves 16 to 18.

title: busy-day casserole
directions: Combine everything in a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt cheese and milk.
Add soup, eggs, almonds and pimiento. Pour asparagus in casserole.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Pour melted margarine over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mushrooms on the coals
directions: Clean mushrooms, cut caps in spiral design.
Place in a double thickness of aluminum foil; add butter, garlic powder and lemon juice.
Seal and cook over hot coals 12 to 15 minutes or until desired degree of doneness is reached.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add hot water.
Mix in sugar, pineapple and lemon juice.
Refrigerate until slightly thick, then fold in the large container of Cool Whip.
Break cake into chunks. Alternate layers of cake and Cool Whip.
Mix in large, foil lined bowl.
Set overnight.
Unmold and frost with small container of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: chicken-broccoli divan
directions: In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, arrange broccoli; top with chicken.
Combine soup and milk; pour over chicken and sprinkle with cheese.
Combine butter and bread crumbs; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: baked beans deluxe
directions: Brown and drain ground beef, onion, celery, green pepper and Worcestershire sauce.

title: fabulous ham and cheese souffle
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Spread half of bread cubes evenly in dish.
Add ham and both cheeses, then cover with remaining bread cubes.
Mix milk, eggs, onion salt and mustard. Pour evenly over bread cubes and refrigerate overnight.
Combine cornflakes and margarine for topping.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Serves 10 but can be halved.
A good brunch dish.
Also good with smoked turkey instead of ham.

title: 7 layer bar
directions: Melt butter in oblong glass dish, then add cracker crumbs to butter and press down. Pour Eagle Brand milk on top of cracker crumbs. Sprinkle chocolate chips and then butterscotch chips. Add nuts. Bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: magic cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in pan. Mix all the rest and pour in pan. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: consomme rice
directions: Brown unwashed rice in butter/margarine.
Add consomme, water and salt.
Pour in pan/casserole dish and cover.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.
Stir once with fork.
If too dry, add a little water.

title: bean-and-corn burritos
directions: Saute onions in a little margarine for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add garlic powder, tomatoes, cumin, beans and chilies.
Stir often. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add corn and cook 2 minutes more.
Place a tortilla on a plate. Mound the chili mixture (about 3/4 cup) onto the tortilla.
Top with about 1/4 of the cheese.
Roll tortilla and put seam side down.
You may microwave about 30 seconds to melt cheese.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick melted margarine and graham crackers.
Put in Pyrex dish.
Beat with mixer for 15 minutes the eggs, 2 sticks margarine and sugar.
Spread over graham crumbs.
Add sliced bananas.
Top with pineapple, then Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: banana punch (slush)
directions: Mix sugar with 3 cups water and boil for ten minutes.
Let cool.
In another container, put bananas, lemon juice, pineapple juice and orange juice.
Mix well.
Add to cooled syrup and freeze. Take from freezer one hour before using.
Use a wooden spoon to break frozen mix apart and stir into a slush.
Do not let mix thaw completely.
Add 6 cups of water and ginger ale; stir and enjoy.

title: oven-fried catfish(tenn. river)
directions: Beat milk and egg in one bowl, combine cornmeal and seasonings in another shallow bowl.
Dip each fillet into egg and then into cornmeal, coating thoroughly.
Place in single layer in baking dish coated with oil.
Dot fillets with oleo.
Bake at 500° about 12 minutes, or until flaky.
Serves 4.

title: hawaiian coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, oranges and pineapple; toss gently, and set aside.
Combine mayonnaise and remaining ingredients; stir well. Pour dressing over cabbage mixture, toss gently.
Cover and chill at least 6 hours.
Yields 6 servings.

title: wine chicken
directions: Mix the cream of mushroom soup, sour cream and wine together. Pour over chicken, sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° for 1 3/4 to 2 hours.
This recipe is good for feeding a large group, it can be made ahead and reheated.

title: baked chicken parmesan
directions: Mix together bread crumbs, cheese, salt and parsley; spread the mixture in a shallow pan.
In a medium pan melt butter.
Add garlic, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir well and add 6 teaspoons of the butter mixture.
Cool so that you can dip chicken pieces in to coat well.
Roll chicken in crumb mixture, ensuring that each piece is well coated.
Bake in a large shallow pan for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Pour leftover butter mixture over chicken and baste twice during cooking.

title: sauerbraten stew
directions: Using powdered nonfat gravy mix, mix with water as directed. Add gingersnaps.
Cook slowly 5 minutes. Add cooked, sliced carrots, wine vinegar, chopped onion, brown sugar and bay leaf. Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Serve wide noodles, if desired.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add boiling water to lemon jello.
Mix all ingredients together, stirring well, then pour in a mold or whatever dish desired.
Let the mixture partially jell, then stir one time. Replace container in the refrigerator and leave until completely jelled.
Can be served on lettuce or as is.
This is a good salad to use with meats.

title: doughnuts
directions: Heat fat or oil, 3 to 4 inches deep, to 375° in deep fat fryer or kettle.
Measure 1 1/2 cups of flour and the remaining ingredients into large mixer bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in remaining flour.
Turn dough onto well floured cloth covered board; roll around lightly to coat with flour.
Roll dough gently 3/8-inch thick.
Cut with floured doughnut cutter.
With wide spatula, slide doughnuts into hot fat. Turn doughnuts as they rise to surface.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes, or until golden brown on both sides.
Carefully remove from fat; do not prick the surface.
Drain.
Serve plain, sugared or frosted. Makes 2 dozen doughnuts.

title: flako eclairs
directions: Heat water to full boil in medium size saucepan.
Stir in pie crust mix until mix leaves sides of pan.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Stir soda into butter, then add sugar and syrup.
Mix nuts and popcorn then other mixture.
Pour into shallow baking pan. Cook 1 hour on 225°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 3/4 cup of the cheese, the green onion, sour cream, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cover and reserve.
Heat remaining ingredients except olives to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered 5 minutes. Spoon about 1/4 cup beef mixture onto each tortilla; roll tortilla around filling.
Arrange in ungreased oblong baking dish.
Pour sauce over enchiladas.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cook uncovered in 350° oven until bubbly.
Garnish with olives.

title: crunchy chicken and rice
directions: Combine cheese and rice; mix well.
Add chicken, peas and 1/2 can of onions.
Mix carefully.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole, sprayed with vegetable spray.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; top with onions.
Cook 5 more minutes until onions are brown.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Break margarine up and grease baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together thoroughly.
Pour in peaches. Stir slightly. Bake in oven at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
When crust is golden brown, take out and serve with a scoop of ice cream.

title: angel yeast rolls
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until thoroughly mixed.
Add buttermilk and dissolved yeast.
Work together with large spoon until all flour is moistened.
Cover bowl and refrigerate until ready for use.

title: delicious whole wheat bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: In a cup, mix first 3 ingredients together.
In mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Add honey/water/yeast mixture and an additional 2 1/2 to 3 cups flour.
Knead 10 minutes.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Break and cook spaghetti; drain.
Cut bacon into small pieces; cook in frying pan until crisp.
Add steak, mushrooms and onions. Cover; cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Combine with spaghetti.
Add salt, oleo, tomato puree, pimentos, pepper and mustard.
Put mixture into a 1-quart casserole dish and heat for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: quick sauerbraten
directions: Brown round steak in oil; add other ingredients and simmer for 2 hours.
Remove bay leaves and garlic; thicken with 3 tablespoons water and 2 tablespoons flour.
Serve over hot buttered noodles.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon; add eggs and oil.
Beat with a wooden spoon.
Add nuts and apples; batter will be thick and hard to mix after apples are added.
Spread batter in greased and floured 10-inch skillet or other cake pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
A single batch baked in large pan can be cut into bars.
Double the recipe and bake in 9 x 11-inch pan or 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake double batch at 350° for one hour.
Double batch serves 8 to 10.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Cook beans according to package directions.
Drain and place in casserole.
Add mayonnaise and sour cream; mix.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese and paprika on top.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: lemon bars
directions: Blend together the first 3 ingredients (flour, brown sugar and margarine).
Spread over the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan; bake at 275° for 10 minutes.
In a mixing bowl, mix next 8 ingredients. Spread over the pastry and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: elizabeth's french bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine water, salt, sugar and yeast and stir to combine ingredients.
Cover 5 or 10 minutes.
Mix in flour with spoon.
Put dough on well-floured surface.
Shape in oval, cut in half, stretch and twist.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Cover with dish towel and let sit in warm place for 20 minutes.
Make 1/2-inch slashes across top.
Spray salted water on top.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: lasagne no. 1
directions: Prepare noodles by package directions.
Brown ground chuck. Add seasonings to taste.
Add tomato paste and 1 or 1 1/2 cans of water.
Stir in tomato paste and water; let simmer.
(You may season more here.)
Oil bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Layer noodles to cover bottom.
Add 1 layer of meat sauce, then layer some Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Continue layering and end with cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: eggplant "stuff"
directions: Peel
eggplant; cut in 1-inch chunks.
Boil in slightly salted water
until
transparent.
Drain.
In large bowl fork blend 2 eggs.
Add drained eggplant and mix to coat eggplant. Add 1
cup bread crumbs, herbs and mix.
In a bread tin layer eggplant,
top with a layer of sliced mushrooms, tomatoes and cheese.
Repeat layers
(eggplant,	mushrooms,
tomatoes
and cheese).
Bake covered
at
350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.
Slice using a spatula.

title: scotch sours
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Serve over ice or straight up!
Use lemonade can as a measure.

title: asparagus frittata
directions: Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add chopped garlic, onion and asparagus.
In a bowl mix eggs, chicken broth and cheese.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour cake pan.
Beat eggs.
Add oil and grated carrots; set aside.
Cream sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Add nuts; mix well.
Add eggs, oil and carrot mixture.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300°.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream the first 5 ingredients together. Add vanilla and sour milk. Next, add dry mixture to creamed mixture. When mixed, lastly add 3 cups of finely grated and well drained zucchini. Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Sprinkle 1 cup of chocolate chips and some chopped walnuts over the top. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: cece's meat dip
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and garlic until beef is lightly browned and onion is tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, catsup, oregano and sugar.
Cover; simmer gently for 10 minutes.
Spoon excess fat off.
Remove from heat and add cream cheese and Parmesan.
Stir until cream cheese has melted and is well combined.
Use corn chips for dippers.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water and add frozen berries.
Stir until berries soften and jello starts to thicken.
Gently spread mixture on top of cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: lentil soup
directions: Rinse lentils in cold water; drain.
In heavy 5-quart Dutch oven, combine lentils and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Lower heat and simmer, uncovered, for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove bone; cut meat from bone and return meat to soup.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix all and let stand 20 minutes. Pour into 2 small or 1 large greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar and lemon juice, pour over bread while warm for glaze.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Slice chilies and wash to remove seeds.
Fill chilies with Monterey Jack cheese.
Put them in a 2-quart baking dish.
Pour other ingredients over.
Sprinkle the top with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: moist golden cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, corn meal, sugar, soda and salt.
Mix buttermilk and eggs.
Stir buttermilk mixture and butter into corn meal until blended.
Grease 8-inch square pan. Pour batter into pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden on top and wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cheese danish
directions: Separate each biscuit in half.
Dip in melted butter.
Mix cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar together and roll each biscuit in it. Place on cookie sheet.
Make a thumbprint in each biscuit.
Mix cream cheese and 1 tablespoon sugar together and place a little into each thumbprint.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
Serve with preserves, if desired.
Refrigerate leftovers. Makes 20.

title: sensational celery
directions: Spray frypan with cooking spray.
Heat on medium until sliced celery dropped into pan will sizzle gently.
Dump in all celery slices.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for about 4 minutes.
It is important that the celery remains crisp and green.
Add pepper and sprinkle of salt.
People will never guess what they are eating, but they will enjoy it.
Double quantities for 4 servings.

title: baked cheddar macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain and set aside. In a sauce pan add, melted butter, flour, salt and pepper. Stir until smooth then add milk slowly and cook mixture over medium heat. Cook until thick, stirring constantly. Add cheese and cook until melted. Mix the sauce and macaroni together. Pour into greased 8 inch baking dish. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Slice cucumbers.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over cucumbers.
Chill.

title: diabetic deep dish apple pie
directions: Combine liquid sweetener, cornstarch, salt, lemon rind, lemon juice, nutmeg, cinnamon, apple slices and 1/2 cup water.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Open crescent rolls and place on pizza pan or deep cookie sheet to form crust.
Layer with hash browns and sausage.
Mix together eggs, milk, salt, pepper and Parmesan. Top with Mozzarella. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into well-greased dish.
Sprinkle with paprika or cracker crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes in 425° oven.
Serves 4.

title: wassail punch
directions: Mix all
ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove cinnamon and cloves.
Serve
warm in punch cups.
Yield: 1 1/2 gallons.

title: pizza meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, eggs, onions, salt and enough Minute oats to hold mixture together (about 3/4 cup).
Form into meatballs and place in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Flatten slightly.
Pour over can of pizza sauce.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes. Take from the oven and add favorite pizza toppings.
Onions can be added to toppings instead of meatball mixture with rings of peppers, mushrooms and olives.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and return to oven until cheese is melted (8 to 10 minutes).
Makes about 38 to 40 meatballs.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs gently with electric mixer (low speed).
Slowly add sugar.
Beat in oil, water and pumpkin.
Sift flour and cinnamon and blend with pumpkin mixture.
Grease 2 loaf pans (9 x 5 x 3 1/2-inch).
Pour in batter and bake at 300° for about 1 1/4 hours.

title: dessert delight
directions: Mix pineapple and oranges with softened cream cheese.
If too stiff, add a little of the juices.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.
Better the next day.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients in oleo, then put into boiler and add cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Heat thoroughly.

title: lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown meat; spoon off excess fat.
Add garlic, tomatoes, tomato paste and salt.
Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles; drain and rinse. Combine remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella cheese.
Place half the noodles in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread cottage cheese mixture.
Add half meat sauce and half the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Skin, halve lengthwise and bone chicken breasts.
Sprinkle chicken with onion salt and lemon pepper. Prepare long grain and wild rice mix according to package directions.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Grease heavy roasting or baking dish.
Put rice, soup and water in.
Salt and pepper the chicken and place in with soup and rice mixture.
Cover and place in a 325° preheated oven for 2 hours and no peek!

title: bar-b-que roast beef
directions: Mix seasonings together, rub generous amount of seasoning into meat, sprinkle liquid smoke on all sides, wrap beef tightly in heavy duty foil. Wrap from side to side and fold two ends. Put in brown paper bag. Place in pan that has been sprayed with Pam. Cook at 200° for 24 hr.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well.
Roll in 1/2 to 1-inch balls and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: quick supper casserole
directions: Cut franks in 1-inch pieces.
Combine with corn.
Mix soup and milk and pour over the franks and the corn.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle with paprika.
Cook, uncovered, at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Clean hog head and cook in clear water.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Drain off liquid from carrots and English peas.
Use the water you cook head with and mix all ingredients together.
Simmer about 1 hour.

title: oatmeal caramelitas
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine flour, rolled oats, brown sugar, soda, salt and melted margarine.
Blend well to form crumbs. Press 1/2 of crumbs into the bottom of an 11 x 7-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with chocolate pieces and pecans.
Blend caramel topping and flour; pour caramel mixture back and forth over chocolate and pecans to cover.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer or until golden brown.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Cut into bars.

title: wiggly fruit
directions: Mix gelatin with 1/4 cup juice in bowl.
Measure another 1/2 cup juice and bring to a boil.
Add hot juice to gelatin mixture, stirring until all of the gelatin is dissolved.
Add remaining juice and chill until it begins to set.
Add fruit; stir and chill until firm.

title: chunky chicken and pasta soup
directions: In Dutch oven, heat oil and stir-fry chicken.
With slotted spoon, remove chicken.
Add onion, pepper and garlic to the pan and stir-fry until onion is tender.
(If necessary, add more oil.) Return chicken to pan; add all remaining ingredients, except pasta.
Simmer the soup, covered, for 5 minutes.
Raise heat so soup boils.
Add pasta.
Lower heat; cook gently, 12 to 17 minutes, until pasta is tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve with crusty bread.

title: canned ham
directions: Boil ham for 1/2 hour.
Put ham in roasting pan.
Add 1 1/2 cups water (about 1 inch in pan).
Sprinkle on top of ham the nutmeg, cinnamon and maple syrup.
Cover top of ham with brown sugar.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and soup mix together.
Chill until soup mix is soft.
Add onion, water chestnuts and spinach to mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill at least 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with King's Hawaiian bread.

title: cranberry cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Heat on low until candy has melted.
Stir.
When melted serve hot!
Better than apple cider. Great for fall parties.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and potatoes.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift flour, baking powder and spices.
Add alternately with milk. Fold in floured nuts and raisins.
Do not overbeat.
Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.

title: chili rellenos dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill at least one hour.
Drain excess liquid.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Warm milk and add shortening and salt.
Heat until shortening is melted.
Let cool.
Set yeast in large bowl and add sugar and water.
Set for 30 minutes.
Beat eggs and add to milk mixture. After yeast has risen, add milk and egg mixture.
Stir in flour and knead dough.
Let rise for 45 minutes.
Roll out and cut into doughnuts.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Fry in hot shortening.
Glaze or roll in sugar.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat all ingredients for 20 minutes.
Put in a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: sliced orange dessert
directions: Peel oranges.
Be sure to remove all the white part.
Slice oranges into 1/3-inch slices.
Arrange slices overlapping on a serving platter.
Sprinkle walnut halves over orange slices.
Heat sugar, Amaretto and water in a saucepan until sugar dissolves and syrup thickens slightly.
Remove from heat and cool.
Pour over oranges.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until serving time.

title: sugar-free dream pie
directions: Beat whipped topping mix, 1 cup milk and vanilla.
With mixer on low speed add remaining milk and pudding mix to blend.
Turn mixer to high and beat 2 minutes.
Spoon into pie shell and chill 4 hours.

title: chocolate harmony cupcakes
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Stir, cover and let stand for 15 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips in top of double boiler over hot water; remove from heat.
Beat butter and sugar together until creamy.
Blend in chocolate and add egg; beat well.
Add oats. Blend sifted flour, soda and salt; add to mixture and blend well. Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: potato lefse
directions: Make potatoes the day before and cool.

title: dutch baby pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425.
Place margarine in oven pan & place in the oven while it preheats.
Blend eggs, milk & flour in blender for 30 seconds.
Pour in hot pan of melted margarine.
Bake for 25 minutes or until curled on the edges.
Great with syrup or fresh fruit & whipped cream.

title: date cookies
directions: Mix dates, butter, sugar and eggs in small saucepan and simmer for 10 minutes.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour over Rice Krispies.
Shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: mexican chicken salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, picante sauce, garlic, chili powder in a bowl.
Mix chicken, tomatoes, cheese, onion and bell pepper in a large bowl,
Pour sauce over other ingredients and serve with chips.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute bell pepper, onion and celery in 1/2 stick oleo or butter. Cook vermicelli, drain and mix with all other ingredients. Top with grated cheese (optional) and bake at 350° about 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
If consistency is too thick, sprinkle about 1/4 cup broth over casserole.
Serves 8 or 10.

title: tamale pie
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain off excess fat.
Add tomatoes, corn, cornmeal and seasonings; simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in olives.
Turn into 8-inch square dish.
Sprinkle cheese over meat mixture.
Carefully spoon topping over cheese, spreading batter out to edges.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until top is lightly browned.

title: pecan delights
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the first four ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until all sugar is dissolved.
Gradually add milk and mix well.
Continue cooking until candy thermometer reads 248° (firm ball stage).
Remove from the heat; stir in vanilla until blended.
Fold in the pecans.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto a waxed paper-lined cookie sheet.
Chill until firm.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts; cut up in small pieces.
Mix broth, soups and tomatoes in bottom of baking dish.
Layer chips, then chicken and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute onion in melted margarine for about 5 minutes.
Add parsley and zucchini.
Cook until tender.
Add salt, basil, pepper, oregano and garlic powder.
Blend, stir and cool.
When cool, mix zucchini mixture with the beaten eggs and cheese.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch pan.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Allow to set 10 minutes before serving.

title: stained glass fruit salad
directions: Chill fruit a day before. Slice bananas into pineapple juice. Mix all ingredients gently. Chill well.

title: pumpkin dessert nog
directions: Place pumpkin, milk, honey and cinnamon in blender jar; blend. Add ice cream and rum.
Blend until smooth.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Serve at once.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: hawaiian bread dip
directions: Cut bowl shape out of Hawaiian bread (save that bread for dipping). Mix ingredients. Pour in the Hawaiian bread. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate curls
directions: Over hot, not boiling, water, combine chocolate morsels and vegetable shortening; stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Pour into foil-lined 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Chill until firm (about 2 hours).
Remove foil from chocolate block.
Make chocolate curls using one of the following:
vegetable peeler, cheese slicer, cheese plane, lemon zester or butter curler.
Place curls on cookie sheet; chill until ready to use.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: dave's gooey butter cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Spray or grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press mixture into bottom of pan.
Set aside.
Beat remaining ingredients 6 minutes and pour over the cake mixture in the pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 50 minutes, depending on oven and area.
Immediately upon removing from oven sprinkle with powdered sugar.
This may be served cold or warm.
Rich, but delicious.

title: banana custard delight
directions: Custard:
Mix eggs, sugar and salt.
Gradually pour milk into eggs, stirring constantly.
Cook over simmering, not boiling water, stirring constantly until mixture coats a silver spoon.
Stir in vanilla.
Cool.

title: red beans and rice
directions: In a large Dutch oven, bring all ingredients, except sausage, to a boil.
Simmer 4 to 5 hours, until beans are soft and liquid is thick.
Stir in sausage for the last 30 minutes of cooking. Adjust seasonings.
Serve over hot rice.

title: pineapple-ham spread
directions: In bowl, combine pineapple, mayonnaise, brown sugar and mustard.
Add ground ham; mix well.
Spread bread with softened butter. Spread ham mixture on 8 slices of bread, top with lettuce leaves and remaining bread slices.

title: turkey cutlets oriental
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over cutlets.
Marinate at least 1 hour.
Saute cutlets about 3 minutes each side or microwave about 2 minutes on each side on High roast.
Serve with rice.

title: green chiles and cheese rice
directions: Prepare rice with butter according to basic recipe package directions except at end of 20 minutes simmer, stir in 4 slices cheese, cut in thin strips, and diced chiles.
Cover and let stand until desired consistency.

title: two flavor fudge
directions: Combine sugars, milk and butter in a saucepan.
Bring to a full boil over moderate heat.
Stir frequently.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add Marshmallow Creme, butterscotch and chocolate.
Stir until melted and mixture is smooth.
Blend in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.
