title: salad dressing
directions: Place in blender or processor and blend until smooth.

title: chicken crab divan
directions: Arrange artichokes on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large skillet, saute chicken in butter for 15 minutes.
Add crab. Cook 5 minutes.
Add sherry.
Allow to evaporate.
Season with salt and pepper.
Remove chicken and crab.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 375° to 400° for about an hour, until golden brown.
I add some of the liquid from the kernel corn to the mixture, but not all from both cans.
This requires a 2-quart casserole dish and bake uncovered.

title: connie's cream cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together all ingredients and put in greased and floured glass pan (13 x 9-inch).
Bake for about an hour.

title: ethel's no cook divinity
directions: Mix frosting mix, corn syrup, vanilla and water in small mixing bowl; beat on high speed with electric mixer until it reaches peak, 5 minutes.
Transfer to large bowl and gradually mix in powdered sugar.
Add nuts and drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
When outside of candy feels firm, turn over and let dry for 12 hours.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Prepare spaghetti according to package directions.
Mix the remaining ingredients with the spaghetti.
Make ahead and cool in the refrigerator.
Keeps several days.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain.
Add the rest of ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Place in large oblong pan and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish and top with Ritz crackers and melted butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: rebecca's favorite fruit salad
directions: Combine all fruits, then fold in dry pudding mix. Serve in pretty glass bowl. ENJOY!

title: quick italian supper
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and garlic.
Drain.
Add tomatoes, seasonings and paste.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Place in casserole.
Top with quartered biscuits and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese (or whatever cheese you happen to have).
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: clam spread
directions: Drain clams; save juice.
Melt butter and saute onion, garlic and clams.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1/2 hour, until bubbly.
May be frozen.

title: ginger punch(lebouroudjee)
directions: Cut pineapple into 1 inch chunks and whirl, a portion at a time, in a blender with 2 cups water.
Pour puree through a wire strainer into a large bowl, squeezing pulp to remove all juice; discard pulp.
(If using pineapple juice, mix it with 2 cups water in the bowl.)
Whirl ginger in blender with an additional 2 cups water.
Pour through wire strainer into pineapple juice, squeezing liquid from pulp.
Add lemon juice and sugar to taste to the juice.
Pour into a pitcher, cover, and chill about 2 hours or as long as overnight.
Stir and pour over ice to serve.
Makes 7 to 8 cups, or about 10 servings.

title: cream of avocado soup
directions: Puree the first four ingredients in a blender.
Add 1 cup light cream, salt and pepper to taste and a dash of cayenne.

title: orange and cinnamon spiced nuts
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Spread nuts in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake, stirring occasionally, for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly toasted.
In a small bowl, stir together sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
In small mixer bowl, beat egg whites at high speed, scraping bowl often, until soft peaks form (1 to 2 minutes).
Continue beating, gradually adding sugar mixture, until stiff peaks form (1 to 2 minutes).
By hand, fold in nuts and orange peel.
In same jelly roll pan, melt butter in oven (4 to 6 minutes).
Spread nut mixture over butter.
Bake, stirring every 10 minutes for 25 to 30 minutes or until nuts are brown and no butter remains.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container.

title: vegetable casserolegroves, texas
directions: Grease 2 qt. casserole.
Mix all vegetables, sour cream, cheese and soup well.
Pour into casserole.
Crush Ritz crackers. Melt butter and mix crackers into butter to make crumb topping. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in saucepan.
Stir constantly while bringing to a full, rolling boil.
Boil for about 3 minutes then add peanut butter and remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and oats.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper and let cool.

title: strawberry-jello salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water as directed on package.
Chop up frozen strawberries and add in place of cold water.
Add well drained pineapple.
Take half of mixture and place in dish; put in refrigerator for at least 1 hour or until firm.
Frost with sour cream and pour the remaining jello mixture on top.
Replace in refrigerator.
Better to sit overnight.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and taco sauce thoroughly.
Spread mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Top with shredded cheese and lettuce.
Sprinkle tomato and onion over top and serve with tortilla chips.

title: hot dip
directions: In 8 x 8-inch baking dish, layer ingredients in order given. Bake in oven until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: banana peach rice pudding
directions: Drain peaches.
Reserve a few peach slices for garnish; coarsely chop remaining peaches.
Slice bananas.
In medium bowl, stir rice pudding, peach yogurt, chopped peaches and all but 12 slices of banana.
Spoon pudding mixture into 4 dessert bowls. Garnish with mint leaves and reserved peach and banana slices. Makes 4 servings.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Cover sliced cucumbers with water and salt.
Let stand 7 days. Drain and wash cucumbers.
Cover again with water and alum.
Let stand 2 nights.
Drain well.
Cover with vinegar and turmeric. Let stand 1 night.
Drain well.
Cover with sugar, layer of cucumbers and layer of sugar mixed with small amount of pickling spice.
Put in jars.
Sugar preserves them.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until done and then drain.
Mix soup and cheese together.
Mix well.
Mix rice and broccoli with soup.
Pour in dish.
Crush Town House crackers.
Mix with butter.
Sprinkle on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in water 5 minutes. Bring milk to scalding and add butter, salt and sugar. Thoroughly drain crumbs and add to hot mixture. Pour over the eggs; add vanilla and mix well. Pour into greased baking dish. Place dish in pan of hot water. Bake in slow oven (325°) until firm, about 50 minutes. Serve warm. Serves 8.

title: double chocolate snack cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour square pan, 8 x 8-inch. In small mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla; beat until smooth. Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake 40 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Cut into squares.

title: garlic-oregano lamb with vegetables - skewered
directions: In a large bowl, mix the yogurt, oregano and garlic. Add the lamb cubes and stir to coat the meat well. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: fresh layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer in 9 x 12 dish the first 7 ingredients.
Mix mayonnaise and Miracle Whip with sugar.
Spread on top as frosting.
Top with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.
At serving time, garnish with more bacon and parsley.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan (or spray with cooking spray).
In a medium saucepan, combine Karo syrup and sugar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Using a large bowl, pour syrup mixture over Rice Krispies.
Stir until cereal is evenly coated.
Press mixture into pan.
Melt together chocolate and butterscotch chips.
Spread over cereal.
When topping has hardened, cut into bars.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Combine the ingredients and drop by spoonfuls into a heavy skillet containing a thin layer of hot oleo.
Spread out and flatten as you turn them with a spatula.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.
I have used a little canola oil for frying.

title: herbed vegetable cheese casserole
directions: Cook
peas
and
corn in small amount of water, about 3 minutes;
drain.
Mix together cracker crumbs, melted oleo and herbs.
Place
1/2 of vegetables in buttered casserole, then a layer
of
sliced tomatoes and sprinkle 1/2 of cracker mixture on top
of
tomatoes.	Top with remaining vegetables, cheese, tomatoes and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.	Serves 8.

title: tina's taco casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and seasoning; drain well.
Pour warm margarine into biscuit dough and stir.
After placing drained beef mixture in large casserole pan, spread biscuit mix over top to edges of pan.
Bake until crust is golden brown.

title: pumpkin crisp
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch glass pan with nonstick spray.
Mix pumpkin, milk, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and eggs.
Pour into pan. Pour dry cake mix over the mixture.
Pat nuts evenly into dry mixture.
Spoon melted butter evenly over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool and top with whipped topping.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion, chili powder, tomato sauce and jalapeno peppers.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours.

title: light and fruity pie
directions: Make Jell-O with 2/3 cup boiling water.
When dissolved, add ice cubes and stir until thickened. Remove unmelted ice cubes. Using wire whisk, blend in Cool Whip, then whip until smooth. Chill until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust. Chill 3 hours. Garnish.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Top with dressing.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sour cream apple squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar and butter until crumbly; stir in nuts.
Press 2 2/3 cups of mixture into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
To remaining mixture, add cinnamon, soda, salt, sour cream, vanilla and egg; blend well.
Stir in apples; spoon evenly over base.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: fancy pants hamburgers
directions: Form 8 thin hamburger patties. Press 2 patties around 2 slices of the cracker cut Cheddar cheese, sealing the cheese with meat. Spray frying pan with nonstick spray. Saute hamburgers quickly on both sides; remove from heat. Pour 1 can over patties. Place slice of cheese over. Pour second can and seasonings and remainder of cheese. Simmer 20 minutes over low heat. Serve with steamed/boiled rice.

title: cheese pennies
directions: Combine butter and cheese and mix well. Add rest of ingredients, except pepper and pecans. Add a few grains of cayenne pepper; mix thoroughly. Divide into 4 pieces. Roll each into a cylinder (silver dollar size). Wrap in foil and freeze. To serve, partially defrost roll; cut slices 1/4-inch thick. Top with pecan halves, if desired and bake on a greased cookie sheet at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from pan while warm to prevent breaking. Yield: 3 dozen.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except chips and cheese.
Place layer of chips in bottom of casserole.
Pour chicken mixture over chips. Sprinkle with cheese.
Continue to layer until all ingredients are gone.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lazy fruit pie
directions: Place fruit in pie dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over fruit. Stir. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Top with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: chili con carne
directions: Melt shortening in skillet; add onion, garlic and beef.
Brown slightly.
Add seasonings, soup and kidney beans; bring to boil. Cover, simmer slowly 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking (may cool, chill and reheat at serving time).
Makes 6 servings.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Mix all ingredients well, then roll into finger shapes and bake until light brown at 350° or less.
Bake approximately 8 to 10 minutes.
While hot, roll in 4x sugar.
Place cookies on ungreased cookie sheet when baking.
Yield: approximately 70 to 75 cookies.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Put in a pan.
Mix well.
Place biscuits on top.
Bake at 350° until bread is done.

title: ham and macaroni twist casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 12 x 8-inch baking dish, combine hot macaroni, ham and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Divide broccoli spears into 6 small bunches.
Arrange bunches of spears down center of dish, alternating direction of flowerets.
In small bowl, combine soup, milk, 1/2 cup cheese and seasonings; pour over macaroni mixture and broccoli.
Cover.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Top with remaining cheese.
Sprinkle onions down center of cheese.
Continue baking, uncovered, for 5 minutes, or until onions are golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: spears peanut clusters
directions: Melt chips and almond bark in a double boiler.
When melted and blended thoroughly, add peanuts gradually, stirring together. Drop from a tablespoon on waxed paper, or into individual petit four cups.
Cool and store covered in refrigerator.

title: cheddar potato gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend onion recipe soup mix, beer and water; set aside.
In 2-quart rectangular baking dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray, layer half of the potatoes, soup mixture and cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake 1 hour.
Remove foil and continue baking an additional 5 minutes or until top browns slightly.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown rice in butter.
Put all remaining ingredients in greased casserole, cover tightly and cook 1 hour in a 350° oven. Stir several times while cooking.
Add chopped, cooked pieces of chicken, if desired.

title: french onion soup
directions: Thinly slice onions.
Saute onions until clear.
Add beef bouillon.
Bring to boil and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Ladle into ovenproof crocks.
Add 1/2-inch slice of toasted French bread and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Place crock under the broiler until the cheese is melted and browned.

title: danish apple cake
directions: Combine breadcrumbs, melted margarine, sugar and cinnamon. Layer 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread applesauce over crumbs.
Layer remaining 1/2 of crumb mixture over applesauce. Chill.
Serve with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: crustless ricotta pie
directions: Combine spinach and onion and microwave at High 4 to 6 minutes, stirring after half the time.
Drain well.
In medium mixing bowl, beat eggs with fork.
Stir in Ricotta, salt, pepper, nutmeg and flour.
Blend in spinach and onion.
Spread mixture in 9-inch pie plate with rubber spatula.
Sprinkle with paprika. Microwave on High for 4 minutes, rotating every 2 minutes.
Reduce power to Medium and cook 3 to 11 minutes longer, until center is set.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: michigan rocks
directions: Mix in order the butter or oleo, brown sugar, eggs, baking soda in a little hot water, vanilla, cinnamon, flour, dates, walnuts and grapes.
Drop from teaspoon on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: jambalaya
directions: Heat oil in heavy 12-inch skillet or Dutch oven over moderate heat. Add onions, green pepper and garlic. Saute 5 minutes. Add ham and rice. Stir until rice is coated with the oil, about 1 minute.
Add thyme, salt, red pepper, tomatoes and broth.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid has been absorbed.
(Check after 15 minutes and add up to 1/4 cup water if mixture seems too dry.)

title: blueberry salad
directions: First Layer:
Prepare 2 packages red raspberry Jell-O according to directions.
Let gel.

title: skillet fried green tomatoes
directions: Mix together with salt and pepper to taste.
Roll tomatoes in mixture and fry until golden brown.
Serves 4 people.
May substitute yellow squash for green tomatoes.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage about 15 minutes.
Drain.
Alternate layers of cabbage, salt and pepper, grated cheese and stuffing.
Blend soup and milk; pour over casserole.
Dot top with butter.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° with lid on.
Remove lid and bake 5 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 6.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In a bowl, combine juice, ketchup, honey, vinegar, mustard and salt.
Pour over the chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer or until tender.
Remove pork chops to a serving platter and keep warm.
Strain pan juices into saucepan. Combine cornstarch and water.
Add to pan juices.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Serve immediately over pork chops.

title: hot dog chilli sauce
directions: Brown beef and drain. Add salt, pepper, chili powder, paprika, ketchup, onion and garlic salt. Stir well. Simmer about 15 to 20 minutes. Good on hot dogs or to make chili beans.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Take out of oven and sprinkle with your favorite stuffing mix on top.
Bake in oven for 10 minutes.

title: cannelon of beef and pork
directions: Soak bread in cold water until soft.
Drain bread, pressing out all the water.
Mix ingredients thoroughly together.
If desired, an egg may be added.
Shape as a loaf.
Place on oiled rack in a roasting pan.
Lay 2/3 strips of bacon across the top. Sear 20 to 25 minutes at 475° to 500°, then cover and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 400°.

title: chinese barbecued spareribs
directions: Layer spareribs in shallow pan; dust with salt and pepper. Bake 30 minutes in
hot (450°) oven.
Meantime, in saucepan, stir together onion, tomato sauce, vinegar, soy sauce, honey, salt, pepper, mustard, Tabasco sauce, bay leaf, garlic and water.
Bring to boil. Pour over ribs.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 1 hour. Baste twice with pan drippings.
Garnish.
Cut scallions and/or small pickles.
Delicious!

title: vermicelli in ricotta sauce
directions: Cook garlic in butter and olive oil for 1 minute over moderately low heat.
Add milk, cream, salt, red pepper and black pepper Bring to a simmer (not boil).
Remove pan from heat.
Add Ricotta and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Whisk until smooth.
Cook over moderately low heat until heated through.
Toss sauce with vermicelli and garnish.

title: old-fashioned dark fruit cake(5 pounds)
directions: Mix fruit, nuts, molasses and fruit juice.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add fruits, then dry ingredients.
Bake in slow oven (300°) with a pan of water on floor of oven.
I use a tube pan for baking and test for doneness after about 1 hour.
This recipe has become a tradition for the past 40 years.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all the ingredients thoroughly and leave in refrigerator overnight if possible.
Form into 1-inch balls and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes approximately 50 balls.

title: beulah's pound cake
directions: Place 1 cup flour and 1 cup sugar in sifter.
Top with 1 more cup flour and 1/2 cup sugar.
Sift into bowl and add milk, eggs and vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer for 20 minutes at medium speed.
Place 1/2 cup broken walnuts into bottom of greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Mix margarine, wafers, orange concentrate, sugar and nuts.
Form into small balls and roll in coconut.
These will keep in refrigerator for at least 2 weeks.

title: fat free pineapple cake
directions: Mix pineapple juice, included, to cake mix, and that is all. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Then let stand in oven for 30 more minutes.

title: hard candy (cinnamon)(cinnamon flavoring red coloring)
directions: Mix first three ingredients in a large saucepan. Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil without stirring until drops of syrup form hard brittle threads in cold water.
Remove from heat.
After boiling has ceased, stir in flavoring and coloring.
Pour into lightly buttered cookie sheet.
Cool.
Break into pieces.
Put into bag and shake with the powdered sugar.

title: aunt hazel's filled peppers(yield:  6 servings)
directions: Boil pepper in salted boiling water for 10 minutes.
Cut a lid off each pepper.
Let drain and cool; remove seeds.
Brown beef and garlic cloves in oil or margarine for about 10 minutes; drain. Add salt and pepper and pour into a pot with the crushed tomatoes (and onion if desired).
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add crushed herbs to your taste.
Serve with boiled potatoes or rice.

title: peanut butter melt away cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in saucepan over low heat until it bubbles.
Take off heat and add next 4 ingredients.
Beat until smooth; pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix together and pour into pie crust.
Top with crushed crackers, 1 stick melted butter and 1/2 cup shredded cheese.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes at 350° until bubbly.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill well.

title: italian supper casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown ground beef; add Sloppy Joe mix and tomatoes.
Whip cream cheese.
Make two layers:
Noodles, meat and cream cheese.
Then garnish with sliced olives.
Bake about 15 minutes in 400° oven.

title: my rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast in water (100° to 115°), about 10 minutes. Add all except the flour and mix well.
Add flour, stir and knead as dough becomes stiff.
Knead until smooth, about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: maggie's sweet potato pie(club member: renee evans)
directions: Blend with a mixer. Bake in bought pie crust at 350° until crust is golden brown.

title: south of the border mini meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients, except salsa, in a large bowl.
Blend well and form in 1-inch balls.
Brown meatballs on all sides. Drain fat.
Add salsa and cook for an additional 10 minutes or add meatballs and salsa to a casserole.
Place in a warm oven until ready to serve.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and crumble.
Set aside after draining on paper towel.
Beat eggs.
Add milk, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Layer bread crumbs, sausage and cheese in a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Cover with egg mixture and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until set and lightly browned.
I serve cranberry sauce with this.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then mix all together and pour into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: my children's favorite cranberry pecan tassies
directions: Blend cheese and 1/2 cup butter; stir in flour.
Chill about 1 hour.
Shape into 2 dozen 1-inch balls.
Place in ungreased 1 3/4-inch muffin pans.
Press dough evenly against bottom and sides of each.
Blend together egg, sugar, 1 tablespoon butter, vanilla and dash of salt just until smooth.
Stir in berries and pecans.
Spoon into pastry lined muffin cups.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until filling is set.
Cool in pans. Makes 24.

title: good coffee cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar and add eggs to blend. Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Set aside.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars in large bowl.
Beat vanilla and eggs.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together.
Add to sugar and egg mixture; blend well.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's or chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate with M&Ms, five or six for each cookie.
Bake at 375° for ten minutes or until golden brown.

title: beef paprika
directions: Melt shortening in skillet.
Add meat, onion and garlic; cook until brown and onion tender.
Stir in catsup, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, salt, paprika, mustard, pepper and 1 1/2 cups water. Cover and simmer 2 1/2 hours.

title: bean soup
directions: Saute onion and cabbage.
Add sausage.
Add navy beans and tomatoes.
Mix well.
Do not overcook, but heat thoroughly.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook hen; remove bones.
Cook celery, onions and pepper in broth until tender.
Cook spaghetti in broth.
Cut chicken up and add to spaghetti.
Then add other ingredients.
Pour into oblong dish and add cheese on top.
Place in oven and heat to melt cheese.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut zucchini lengthwise and remove seeds.
Peel and dice. Cook sausage and onions; drain. Add seasonings and remaining ingredients.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° or until zucchini is tender.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Add water to liquid to make 1 1/3 cups.
Saute celery, pepper and onion in butter.
Add shrimp, cook until pink.
Add measured liquid, tomatoes, sugar, salt, pepper, bay leaf and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer 3 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Cover and simmer until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients with mixer thoroughly.
Pour into greased and floured pan (Baker's Joy is great).
Cook for 1 hour or until middle is done.
Top may be soft.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Pour into casserole dish and cover with Velveeta cheese.
Make brown gravy and pour over cheese.
Cover with Tater Tots and bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and layer with stuffing mix in a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup water if vegetables seem dry.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, soup, lemon juice, mayonnaise, salt, celery, rice and onion.
Put half of mixture in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Cover with sliced eggs.
Add remaining chicken mixture, then sprinkle grated cheese over it.
Add chopped almonds, then crushed potato chips.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 400° oven or until heated through.
Serves 12.

title: southern chicken casserole
directions: In a skillet, fry bacon until crisp and remove.
Add chicken, browning well on all sides.
Remove to a 2-quart casserole dish as pieces brown.
Add vegetables, if desired, on top of chicken.
Cut potatoes into slices or chunks.
Add to bacon fat and brown. Remove.
Add as next layer in the casserole dish.
Top potatoes with onions.
Sprinkle with seasoning, salt, pepper, green onions and parsley.
Top with bacon.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: oyster-seafood and noodle casserole
directions: Put shrimp in boiling water for 15 seconds.
Drain.
Peel shrimp when cool. Shuck oysters; reserve liquor.
Flake the leftover fish, removing any breading if they were fried.
In a large bowl, combine the seafood with the macaroni, onions and peas.
Stir the nutmeg into the white sauce (or cream soup) and add to the seafood and pasta.
Sprinkle the bread crumbs on top and drizzle with reserved oyster liquor. Bake in oven preheated to 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Sift flour; make hole in center.
Add oil to milk.
Pour liquid into flour.
Mix briskly until nearly all flour is wet. Knead, adding a little flour as needed.
Remove from bowl.
Knead until not sticky.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick (with floured roller). Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: pom pom balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into small balls.
Chill thoroughly.
Melt 1 (12 ounce) package of chocolate chips and 1 block paraffin wax in top of a double boiler.
With toothpicks, dip chilled balls into the chocolate mixture.

title: pineapple zucchini cake
directions: Cream eggs; add sugar and oil.
Sift flour, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and soda together and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, zucchini, nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
(Use toothpick test for doneness.)

title: lemon broccoli chicken
directions: Cut 4 thin lemon slices; squeeze 2 teaspoon juice from remaining lemon.
Set aside.
In skillet, in hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned.
Remove; set aside.
Spoon off fat.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift together flour and salt into bowl.
With fork, cut shortening into flour until pea size lumps form.
Gradually add milk.
Add as little liquid as possible to hold the dough together.
Divide into 2 portions for 2 different crusts.
Roll out onto floured surface 1/8-inch thick.
Place in pie pan and fill with filling.
Cut off excess dough and mash edges with fork.

title: mom's pumpkin muffins
directions: Cream the sugar, molasses and butter together. Add egg and pumpkin.
Blend well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Fold in the chopped pecans or you may use raisins or walnuts. Put into a well-greased muffin tin.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Makes 1 1/4 dozen.

title: fried okra
directions: Put okra and onion in a large plastic bowl.
Toss with flour and cornmeal.
Cook in microwave for 5 minutes, stirring halfway. Put enough oil in iron skillet to coat bottom.
When oil is hot, add okra mixture.
Fry about 5 minutes, stirring often.
Salt to taste before serving.

title: terrific turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into a loaf.
Bake for 1 hour, 15 minutes at 350°.

title: ambrosia
directions: Chop apple in pieces.
Mix and chill.
Put a little coconut and cherries on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix all together; may need a little more flour to roll out. For chocolate chip cookies, reduce flour by 1 cup.
Very versatile recipe.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cottage cheese jello
directions: In bowl, mix cottage cheese and dry jello powder (mix well with a spoon).
Add Cool Whip and mandarin oranges.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli separately.
Add other ingredients and mix with the cooked rice and broccoli.
Put in a baking dish and bake in oven at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: quick summer dessert
directions: Tear up cake into bite-sized pieces and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with fruit.
Make pudding according to package directions.
Pour over fruit.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: squash puppies
directions: Cook squash until tender, drain.
Mash and drain again. Combine
squash
with
other
ingredients.	Drop by tablespoon into hot oil, fry until golden brown, approximately 5 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured pan.
It needs to be at least 8-inches.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hurry up fried corn
directions: Fry bacon crisp; drain, cool and crumble.
In a large skillet, cook onion and green pepper until soft.
Add corns, sugar, onion powder and black pepper.
Stir well and let "fry" 30 minutes on low heat.
Add bacon pieces.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and put half of crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cream cheese and margarine until smooth.
Fold in sugar and then Cool Whip.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Melt 2 packages yeast in 2 cups hot water. Let cool. Then add salt, sugar and beaten eggs. Add 3 cups flour and stir until well mixed.
Then add the shortening and mix well. Add remaining flour and more if needed to knead well.
Put in greased bowl and let rise about 2 hours. Be sure it is in warm place.
Then refrigerate until ready to use. Take out and let rise again and then roll out and make into your favorite rolls until double in size. Bake in 400° oven until brown.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Combine rhubarb, sugar and pineapple; bring to a boil.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin; mix well.
Pour into small glasses or jars; seal with hot, melted paraffin.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon of the margarine in a small saucepan.
Add flour; cook 2 minutes.
Stir in milk; cook until mixture boils and is thick.
Cool.
Heat remaining margarine in a small skillet; cook and stir eggs until soft scrambled.
Cool.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Bring cider to boil, add lemon peel cut into spirals, cinnamon and honey.
Simmer 30 minutes. Serve hot in mugs.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.
Thin crisp cookies are nice with this.

title: filled hamburgers
directions: Fry meat (drain grease).
Melt butter over meat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Spoon mixture into hamburger buns. Wrap in foil and heat in oven for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken waldorf salad
directions: About 45 minutes before
serving or early in day or day before:

title: macaroni salad
directions: Toss cooked macaroni, bacon drippings (optional), salad dressing, salt and pepper in large bowl. Add crumbled bacon, pickles, cheese, celery and sliced eggs. Use a garnish along with pimento (parsley or paprika). Makes a huge salad and is good served with lettuce.

title: my favorite snack:  ants on a log
directions: You get celery and slice it up. Put the peanut butter on it. And put some raisins on it.

title: gelatin glue(nice warm glue)
directions: Will need saucepan, potholder and spoon.

title: orange sherbet cake
directions: Combine ingredients using mixer.
Pour into 2 greased layer cake pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.	Cook, then split layers, making 4 layers.

title: quick cakes
directions: Mix together and bake in a cake pan at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Really good and low calories too.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate about 1 hour or until chilled.
Makes about 1 cup sauce.

title: twin meat loaves
directions: Mix meat well.
Stir in next 6 ingredients.
Soak bread in milk, add eggs and beat with beater.
Combine meat and eggs mixture.
Form two loaves.
Roll in crumbs.
Place in greased shallow baking dish.
Spread 1/2 cup chili sauce over each loaf. Pour 1/2 cup boiling water around loaves.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: spaghetti i o u
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain, leaving small amount of water.
Cook garlic, oil and cheese in pan and brown.
Add to spaghetti and serve.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl and stir until well blended.
Fry on hot lightly greased griddle.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Brown beef cubes with onions and mushrooms in a little oil. Add soup and wine.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Can be made ahead and reheated.
Serves 4.

title: wagon wheel layered dip
directions: Spread bean dip on a pie plate.
Pour picante sauce over bean dip.
Sprinkle chopped onions over mixture.
Blend together mayonnaise and sour cream.

title: mom's made from scratch biscuits
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine flour and Crisco with a pastry mixer. Mix until all Crisco is completely blended. Add milk and stir with a spoon. Roll out onto a floured surface about 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick. Use a biscuit cutter until all dough has been used. Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown meat;
add onion, celery, pepper and saute.
Then add remainder of ingredients.
Mix well; bake in 300° oven for 1 hour or until brown and bubbly.

title: chocolate peanut butter brickle
directions: Cover cookie tray with foil.
Put crackers on tray bumper to bumper.
Melt butter and sugar.
Boil together for 2 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake in 400° oven for 7 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate and peanut butter morsels on top.
Spread evenly to melt. Add nuts and coconut if desired to top.
Put in refrigerator for 1/2 hour.
Break into pieces.

title: okra patties
directions: Combine all ingredients, drop by tablespoons in hot oil.
Cook until golden brown at 400°.
Drain well on paper towel.

title: chicken and fluffy dumplings
directions: Place chicken, which has been previously cooked, in a large pot with the diced onion, celery and parsley. Add 4 cups water and cook until tender.

title: yum yum cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal and oil.
Add eggs and stir.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter sheet cake
directions: Boil milk, sugar and oleo for 2 minutes.
Remove and add remaining ingredients.
Blend and pour over warm cake.

title: wild rice and chicken
directions: Pour rice in bottom of casserole.
Drain all mushrooms.
Place chicken over rice.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over all.
Dilute soup with 1/2 cup water and spoon over chicken.
Cook uncovered at 350° for 1 hour, then cook covered 1/2 hour longer.

title: cheese and pasta in a pot
directions: Cook beef in oil. Add onions, garlic, sauce, tomatoes and undrained mushrooms. Simmer 20 minutes.

title: blue cheese chicken cutlets
directions: Pound chicken to 1/4-inch thickness.
Brush with lemon juice and sprinkle with salt and 1/16 teaspoon of pepper.
In large frypan, place unsalted butter; melt over medium heat.
Cook chicken about 3 minutes on each side (until fork can be inserted easily). Remove from heat and set aside.

title: rockefeller meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly in a large bowl. Pat down in a baking dish. Bake at 325° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes. Can be topped with ketchup. Spread on top before baking.
Tender and tasty!

title: deluxe meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Mold into rounded flat loaf; place in greased and floured 9-inch glass pie plate.
Spread 2 tablespoons catsup over top.
Cover with plastic wrap, leaving 1 1/2-inch vent.
Cook on High power (10) for 15 minutes, turning half turn after 10 minutes.
When done, remove from microwave and let set 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: sour cream and raisin pie
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Mix raisins, sour cream and eggs.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix together.
Sprinkle over top of muffins or bread.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes for bread, or 20 minutes for muffins.

title: shrimp and orzo salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir well and set aside.
Cook orzo and drain well.
Add orzo, tomato and next 4 ingredients to vinegar mixture.
Toss well.
Cover and chill. Serve in lettuce-lined bowl.
Makes 4 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: nut and coconut club crackers
directions: Melt margarine; add brown sugar, nuts and coconut.
Mix until spreadable.
Spread on unsalted club crackers.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet while still hot. Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: pineapple jello salad
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Dissolve jello in hot water and add to mixture.
Add Marshmallow Creme and let chill thoroughly.
Add cheese and nuts (can be left out).
Whip Dream Whip into milk.
Fold into ingredients and chill.
Serves 15 to 20 people.

title: crandall bread
directions: Slice bread almost through crust.
Place a slice of cheese between each slice of bread.
Melt butter with onion and poppy seed.
Pour over bread, wrapped loosely in foil.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Heat for 20 to 25 minutes at 325°, until cheese melts. May top with crumbled bacon before baking.

title: salsa
directions: Put all in a roast pan and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Stir every 30 to 45 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine and pour into shell.

title: hunter's venison steak
directions: Pound steaks to tenderize, then roll in flour and fry in a large skillet until well done. Remove from skillet and place in baking dish. Use skillet to brown onion. Pour water over the onions and blend in flour. Stir until thick. Season to taste with salt, pepper and cayenne. Pour over steaks in baking dish. Bake in 350° oven 30 to 45 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: recipe for friendship
directions: Cream ingredients together with a pinch of tenderness, lightly beaten in a bowl of loyalty.
Add faith, hope and charity.

title: kiss cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Dip in sugar. Cook at 350° for about 4 minutes.
Take out and put chocolate kiss in the center.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a baking dish.
Cook at 325° until firm, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lasagna with mushrooms(serves 8)
directions: In large saucepan, brown meat; pour off fat.
Add onion and garlic; cook and stir until onion is tender.
Stir in tomato juice, mushrooms, tomato paste and seasonings.
Cover.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: mushroom and orange salad
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Lightly dry and finely slice.
Squeeze juice of an orange over them.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and leave while you peel 2 oranges.
Remove all orange pits and slice oranges thinly.
Lay crisp lettuce leaves in bottom of dish.
Put a layer of oranges and a layer of mushrooms, more oranges and a sprinkle of mushrooms on top.
Pour over a French dressing and sprinkle with very fine chopped walnuts.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers, drain and cut unpeeled cucumbers into 1/4-inch slices.
Put in a large bowl.
Combine the cucumber slices, onion, garlic and salt; cover with ice cubes or crushed ice.
Mix thoroughly and let stand for 3 hours.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine Bran
Buds,
water
and sugar.	Let stand for 1 hour, then
add
remaining
ingredients.	Fill pans 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.	Batter keeps in refrigerator for 2 weeks.
Raisins optional.

title: homemade bread
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and let stand for 5 minutes.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Let raise until double. Knead and let raise again.
Make rolls.
Let raise. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute garlic, chili and bay leaves in olive oil; once the garlic "opens up" add all the tomato products and simmer stirring for about 45 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Spread rice in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Brown beef with chili mix.
Stir in 1 can of tomatoes.
Stir in beans and pour over rice.
Heat Cheddar cheese soup with evaporated milk.
Pour over meat mixture and heat in oven until hot.
Before serving, top with lettuce, tomatoes, onions, grated cheese and crushed Fritos.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: In medium microwave-safe bowl, place chocolate candy bar pieces.
Microwave at High (100%) for 1 minute or until melted and smooth when stirred.
Cool slightly.
Fold whipped topping into melted chocolate and spoon into pie crust.
Refrigerate several hours or until firm.

title: fresh strawberry sherbet(low calorie)
directions: Combine sugar and water in small pan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Before sugar comes to a boil, remove and chill until syrupy.
In blender, add syrup to remaining ingredients and blend well.
Turn mixture into freezing tray and freeze until firm.
Makes 8 servings.
One serving equals 90 calories or 2 1/2 fruit exchanges.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Sift together all ingredients.
Keep in an air tight container.

title: raisin jumbles
directions: Cream oleo and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add sour cream, salt, lemon juice, vanilla, cinnamon and eggs.
Beat until well blended.
Add raisins.
Blend.
Mix together flour and baking soda and add to batter, mixing in well.
Drop from spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: guinea grinder sandwiches
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, cook and drain fat.
Add rest of ingredients, put in French bread and cover with cheese, cover with foil and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Layer sauerkraut and corned beef in bottom of 9 x 13 pan and put dressing on top.
Put however much bread it takes to cover top of casserole dish.
Cube the bread and coat with the melted butter and then put on top of cheese and Thousand Island dressing and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice and broccoli. Saut onion

and pepper in butter until tender. Add mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz. Blend with onion and pepper. Add rice and broccoli to mixture. Add mushrooms (with juice) and chestnuts. Mix and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; do not overcook.
Wash broccoli; cut into bite-size pieces and cook, uncovered in boiling salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Make cheese sauce by combining milk, cornstarch, 1/2 stick margarine, salt and pepper in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, with a wire whisk.
When mixture thickens, add cheese, mayonnaise and onions and blend until the cheese is melted. Remove from heat; add macaroni, broccoli and ham.
Pour mixture into casserole dish.
Melt remaining 1/2 stick margarine; add to cracker crumbs and stir until moistened.
Spoon crumbs over top of casserole.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Freezes well!

title: holiday pecan cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Grease bottom of 10-inch tube pan.
Separate eggs; beat yolks well.
Beat whites until stiff.
In large mixing bowl, cream together butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks, mixing well.
Combine milk, vanilla and dissolved coffee.
Add alternately with dry ingredients.
Fold in egg whites and pecans.
Pour into pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool in pan.

title: light fluffy hot cakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in bowl.
Beat eggs; add buttermilk and oil.
Add to dry ingredients gradually until smooth.
Bake on hot griddle.

title: egg flower soup
directions: Boil
chicken
broth.
Add peas and mushrooms.	Stir in egg. Keep
stirring
to	separate eggs.	Season to taste with salt. Makes 5 servings.

title: angel cake dessert
directions: Combine in medium saucepan the juice, sugar, 3 eggs, beaten, and cook over medium heat.
Add the gelatin that has been dissolved in cold water.
Set aside to cool.
Tear angel food cake into pieces and dip in sauce.
Put in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan (smaller for higher dessert).
Refrigerate overnight or at least 4 to 6 hours.
Top with whipped cream and grated orange rind.

title: coconut date cookies
directions: In heavy saucepan, cook over low heat for 10 minutes the butter, dates, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Let cool.
Put into large bowl the nuts and Rice Krispies.
Pour cooked sauce over and mix, forming the balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: dumplings
directions: Pour broth over butter until melted.
Add salt and pepper. Add plain flour to mixture.
Mix as you would biscuit; roll out.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix all together.
May be baked in Bundt pan or skillet in 400° to 425° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until as brown as you want.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Cream ingredients.
Then spread over unrolled cake and re-roll.
Chill and serve with whipped cream.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix well and bake in greased, wax paper lined cake pans at 325°
until
done.
Makes 2 layers.
While layers are still warm, ice with the following:

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Rinse thoroughly with cold water. Add green peppers, carrots and celery.
Toss gently.
Mix in mayonnaise, salt and pepper to taste.
Chill thoroughly.

title: swiss chicken
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place chicken breasts.
Cover with cheese slices.
Mix well in a bowl the soup and 1/2 can of water. Pour over chicken.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and add to 1 small package of stuffing.
Mix well and sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook chicken bouillon, water, carrots, celery and onion for 20 minutes.
Add potatoes and mixed, frozen vegetables.
Cook 30 minutes.
Add cream of mushroom soup and water.
Add Velveeta cheese.
Heat until cheese melts (do not add any salt).

title: dilly dip
directions: In a food processor or blender, place the cottage cheese, sour cream, dill pickle and pepper.
Process until smooth, about 1 minute.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix well.
Add nuts, chocolate chips or raisins.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: shepherd's casserole
directions: Mix ground beef, vegetables and soup in 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with mashed potatoes and cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted and casserole is heated through.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add taco seasoning and beans. When heated through, combine sour cream and green taco seasoning and spread over meat.
Top with generous amount of cheese. Pop into oven at 350° to melt cheese.
Serve right in the skillet. Serve with tortilla or corn chips.
Also good over baked potatoes.

title: baked potato soup
directions: In a large soup pot, saute onion and red pepper over medium heat in 2 tablespoons butter until onions are clear. Add bacon, potatoes and whipping cream to desired consistency. Skim milk or chicken stock may be used to reduce calories. Salt and pepper to taste. Serve with a garnish of a dollop of sour cream, grated cheese and chives.

title: seafood salad
directions: Cur crab flakes or shrimp.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour before serving. Makes 2 cups.

title: lumpia (egg roll)
directions: Cook ground hamburger meat.
May substitute other meat.
Mix in bowl with chopped vegetables.
May purchase slaw ingredients in place of chopping own vegetables.
Place mixture in a separated wrapper and roll, wetting ends to stick.
Rolls may be frozen until needed.
Deep fry until golden brown.
May serve with sweet and sour sauce.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets until tender.
Peel and cut into quarters or smaller.
Mix all ingredients to dissolved sugar.
Put in cut beets and bring to boil.
Put your jars, lids and rings in pan and get hot.
Add hot beets and be sure to wipe rims so the lids will seal.

title: baked fruit
directions: Drain fruit and arrange in casserole dish with apple rings on top.
Mix and pour sauce over fruit,
cover and put in refrigerator
overnight.
Just before serving put in hot oven 375° until bubbling.
Yield: 14 servings.

title: easy scalloped ham casserole
directions: Combine soup, onion, and seasonings in a 2-quart casserole. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45-50 minutes, or until bubbly.
If desired, sprinkle with French-fried onions and bake an additional 2-4 minutes.
Makes 6-8 servings.

title: oriental steak salad
directions: In medium bowl combine steak, broccoli, tomato and onions.
In jar with tight fitting lid, combine rest of ingredients, cover and shake well.
Pour over salad; toss to combine.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Toss again before serving.
Makes 2 servings; contains 277 calories per serving.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Prepare the night before:
Combine ingredients and refrigerate in a covered container.

title: cranberry yogurt sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Make a puree. Serve with pancakes.

title: quick mexican casserole
directions: Heat chili and tomatoes.
Layer in a 2-quart dish, starting with tortillas, chili and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat and top with cheese. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Boil noodles and drain.
Mix hamburger, Prego sauce and Ricotta cheese.
Do not heat.
Mix together both kinds of cheese in large mixing bowl.
Layer noodles in baking pan.
Spread some sauce mixture.
Top with cheese. Repeat with each layer you use.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: easy company bars
directions: Coat the bottom of an 8-inch square baking pan with melted butter.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Gradually beat in brown sugar and vanilla just until combined.
Combine flour and baking soda; stir into the egg mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Pour batter evenly over butter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bars test done with a wooden pick.
Cool slightly; dust with confectioners sugar and cut.
Cool completely.
Yield:
1 1/2 dozen.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix bran with water.
Let stand for 5 minutes.	Stir in other ingredients.
Bake	for
20 minutes at 400°.
This keeps for 6 weeks in refrigerator and bake as needed.

title: chicken macaroni and cheese
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, melt butter or margarine. Add green pepper and celery. Cook until tender, stirring occasionally. Stir in flour, salt and pepper until blended.
Gradually stir in milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens slightly. Stir in chicken and shredded cheese just until cheese is melted.
Remove from heat. Stir cooked, hot macaroni into cheese mixture until well blended. Serve with salad and crackers or hot bread.
Kids will love this.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: barbecue chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil in a large skillet.
Stir in barbecue sauce and water.
Cover, cook over medium-low heat for 20 minutes or until tender.
Stir in rice and corn.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Garnish with red and green peppers, if desired. Serves 4 or more.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix rice, veggies, chicken and soup.
Place in casserole dish. Mix mayo, sour cream and cheese; spread on top of rice mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place layer of graham crackers in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan, covering bottom. Break in sections to fit well.
Layer pudding and graham crackers, ending with graham crackers.

title: burger bundles
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package; add onion.
Combine meat and milk; mix well.
Make into 6 to 8 (5 to 6-inch) patties. Put stuffing in center of each one; fold up side to make a bundle. Mix soup, Worcestershire sauce and catsup in bowl.
Spoon over burgers.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: mushroom logs
directions: Blend cream cheese, mushrooms and herbs and spices well. Press two sections of crescent rolls together to make a square. Make four of these squares.
Spread on cream cheese mixture.
Roll tightly.
Cut each square into four pieces with kitchen shears. Brush pieces with beaten egg; then sprinkle with sesame or poppy seed.
Bake according to directions on package of crescent rolls. Makes 16 logs.

title: milky way cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs, salt and vanilla. Add milk and flour; add water and soda last.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes in greased and floured pans.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Microwave the green peas until just defrosted, not cooked, or run under hot water and drain.

title: cauliflower broccoli salad
directions: Finely chop the cauliflower, broccoli, green onions and fried bacon. Mix well in large bowl.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Set casserole in a shallow pan with about 1-inch of hot water. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: potato soup for hot weather (vichyssoise)
directions: Melt butter and add green onions and cook until soft. Add potatoes, water and salt. Cover and cook slowly for 30 minutes until potatoes are done. Add milk, cream and 1 tablespoon butter. Bring to boil but stir to prevent scorching. Puree in food processor or blender. Serve cold with a dollop of sour cream for garnish.

title: pigs in blankets
directions: Heat oven to 450.
Stir together with a fork in bowl to form a soft dough, the Bisquick Baking Mix and Water.
Gently smooth dough into a ball on floured cloth-covered board.
Knead 5 times.
Roll dough with lightly floured stockinet-covered rolling pin into square 12 x 12 inches.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown ground beef in shortening and onions together.
Then mix all ingredients.
Cook for a while.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in pan.
Mix next 3 ingredients well and pour over oleo.
Pour pie filling over batter.
Bake 50 minutes at 325°.

title: santa fe chicken and dressing
directions: Stir together first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; stir in soup and next 3 ingredients. Spread in a lightly greased, 2-quart, shallow baking dish. Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Uncover and sprinkle evenly with cheese. Bake 5 more minutes or until cheese melts. Serve with tortilla chips and pico de gallo or chunky salsa, if desired. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in a boiler; bring to a boil.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Use with chicken on the grill, serve on ham or use with any barbecue dishes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in a shallow baking dish.
Pour the water over them and sprinkle with the cinnamon.
Using a fork, work together the flour, shortening and sugar.
It will have a crumbly consistency.
Sprinkle
over
the	apples.
Bake
in preheated oven and serve hot.
Can serve with whipped cream or ice cream. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat until creamy butter, Crisco and sugar.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Beat 5 egg yolks and buttermilk. Alternately add buttermilk mixture and dry ingredients to Crisco and sugar mixture.	Fold in egg whites stiffly beaten.
Bake in 3 greased and floured cake pans at 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in the chicken stock with the onion and butter until soft.
Puree in food processor or blender (both broccoli and the stock).
Put back into large pot.
Whip eggs and cream together in large bowl.
Add 1 ladle of soup to egg/cream mixture, whisking nonstop.
Continue adding soup and whisking until temperature of soup and egg mixture are the same.
Blend mixture into rest of soup.
Heat through, but do not boil.
Serve with almonds and chives as garnish.

title: hamburger hot pot
directions: Fry grease out of ground meat and drain.
In a casserole dish layer sliced potatoes, sliced onions, ground beef, potatoes and onions.
Pour soups over top layer.
Cover casserole.
Bake at 400° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: homemade bubbles
directions: Combine ingredients.
Shake and let settle for 4 hours before using.
Store, covered, in refrigerator, to extend bubbles shelf life.
Allow to warm before using.
Blow bubbles to your hearts content.

title: canned okra or squash
directions: Mix and cover with water.
Cook until it changes color.
Pack in jars and seal.
Rinse well when opened to fry.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cut up potatoes and onions, cover with water, salt to taste and cook until mushy.
Do not drain off water.
Add next 3 ingredients.
To the completed chowder, add the oleo.

title: white chocolate party mix
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together in large bowl.
Melt white chocolate; pour over dry ingredients and mix well.
Lay mixture on wax paper until hard.
Break up and store.

title: corn souffle
directions: Melt enough of the butter to grease a 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Drain corn.
Mix all ingredients, including remaining butter. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, put in loaf pan (7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 60 minutes.

title: one dish meal
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Put oil, vegex, water, broth and soup into saucepan and cook for 3 minutes. Pour sauce over casserole and mix gently.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Pour popcorn in ungreased baking pan. Heat next four ingredients together until bubbly around edges. Cook 5

more minutes over medium heat. Remove from heat. Stir in soda. Pour over popped corn. Stir till well coated. Bake 1 hour at 250. Stir every 15 minutes. Pour onto wax paper and separate into bite size pieces.

title: sunday corn bread
directions: Combine flour, meal, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Stir in eggs, margarine and milk.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 10-inch iron skillet.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple squares
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and salad oil.
Sift flour, nutmeg, salt, baking soda and cinnamon into first mixture.
Add apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together; let set overnight.
Serve with vegetables.

title: winter apples
directions: Quarter and peel apples.
Put about 1 cup water, butter, sugar and cinnamon drops in pan with apples.
Cook until apples are tender.
Let set in pan awhile before putting in a bowl.

title: best broccoli soup
directions: In Dutch oven or soup kettle, bring water to boil.
Add broccoli, celery and carrot.
Boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain, set vegetables aside in same kettle.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour to form a paste.
Gradually add the broth and milk, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Add vegetables and remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: joy's baked italian spaghetti
directions: Saute the onion and beef in salad oil in a Dutch oven until brown.
Add tomato sauce, herbs, sugar, seasonings and wine. Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, for one hour.
Meanwhile, cook spaghetti as directed on package and drain.
Add to sauce with 1/2 cup of grated cheese.
Turn into a 3-quart casserole and sprinkle top with the other 1/2 cup of cheese.
You may use a full cup of cheese for topping if you like.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes in a 325° oven.
Then uncover and bake an additional 30 minutes.
Total baking time is one hour and 15 minutes.
Serves six.

title: baked chicken parisian
directions: Place chicken in 11x7 baking dish. Season with salt and pepper. Combine soup, sour cream, mushrooms and wine. Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 1 1\2 hours. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar until well blended.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and banana.
Then add chocolate and beat well.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to mixture with the water.
Mix well, then turn into 2 greased and lightly floured 9-inch layer cake pans.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes, or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand on wire rack for about 5 minutes.
Then turn out on racks.
Turn right sides up and cool.
Put layers together.
Spread top and sides of cake with frosting.
Garnish with sliced bananas and almonds, if desired.

title: shrimp etouffee(microwave)
directions: In a 2-quart dish, melt butter.
Add seasonings and saute on high for 15 minutes.
Stir in flour and Bloody Mary mix, add cream of celery soup and salt.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes. Add shrimp and microwave on High for 8 minutes or until shrimp are pink and tender.
Stir once or twice.
Squeeze a small amount of lemon juice over etouffee and serve over rice.

title: crockpot lasagna
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain. Mix with spaghetti sauce and tomatoes. Reserve 1/2 c. spaghetti sauce for later use. Spread 1/2 of the reserved sauce on bottom of crockpot. Break up the lasagna noodles to fit in your crockpot and place on top of sauce into the bottom of the crockpot, then put a layer of meat mixture, then cottage cheese, sprinkle with parmesan cheese and spices then a layer of mozzarella cheese. Put a layer of broken up noodles, meat etc. If you have enough ingredients make 1 more layer. Finish with a layer of noodles and the reminder of reserved sauce and 1 last layer of mozzarella cheese. Cook on low for a few (3-4) hours.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips and margarine with Eagle Brand and vanilla.
Remove from heat.
In large bowl, combine marshmallows and peanuts.
Stir in chocolate mixture. Spread in aluminum foil-lined 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Remove from pan.
Peel off foil and cut into squares.
Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.

title: chow chow
directions: Chop tomatoes, onions and peppers together; cover with the salt and let stand overnight.
Drain and add the hot peppers, which have been chopped, vinegar and spices.
(Spices should be tied loosely in cheesecloth bag.)
Add sugar.
Allow to boil slowly until tender (about 15 minutes).

title: white seafood pasta sauce
directions: Melt butter in large frying pan.
Add olive oil and garlic. Bring to a slow boil.
Add all the rest of the ingredients except parsley.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Add parsley.
Serve over spinach fettucini.
Serves 6.

title: happy day cake
directions: Sift flour before measuring. Measure into sifter the cake flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Measure into mixing bowl the shortening. Measure into cup the milk, butter and eggs. Stir shortening to soften. Sift in dry ingredients. Add about 3/4 cup milk and mix until flour is dampened. Beat 2 full minutes. Add eggs and remaining milk. Beat 1 minute longer. Bake at 375° about 25 minutes for layers (35 minutes for loaf cake).

title: nutty caramel corn
directions: Cook sugar, butter and corn syrup; bring to a boil.
Boil for 10 to 12 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Pour over popcorn.
Break in small pieces.

title: rice krispie-peanut butter no bake cookies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Remove from fire and add peanut butter.
Mix well and add Rice Krispies.
Dip with spoon and drop on waxed paper that has been sprayed with Pam.

title: lo mein (beef or chicken)
directions: Slice chicken or beef in thin strips.
Stir-fry in 1 tablespoon oil until done.
Remove from pan.
Stir-fry vegetables in remaining oil.
When done, add chicken or beef to pan along with Yoshida sauce.
Simmer for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a buttered dish.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo; stir in 1 cup crushed cornflakes.
Spread on top of casserole and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: scripture cake(mary ann runyan)
directions: Cream sugar, butter and honey.	Beat eggs until frothy, add milk to eggs, add to creamed mixture and beat thoroughly.

title: chewy oatmeal and chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Combine butter flavored Crisco, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Then combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into the creamed mixture at low speed, just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.

title: reese's balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Put into fridge to cool for about 30 minutes, then make into balls.
Melt 1/2 cake paraffin and chocolate chips.
Dip peanut butter balls into chocolate and then let cool.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix and cook in microwave for 8 minutes on High, stirring twice.
Remove and stir in vanilla and margarine.
Microwave 2 more minutes.
Remove; sprinkle soda over.
Stir well.
Spread on buttered cookie sheet.

title: lenelle's pizza omelette
directions: Lightly saute bell pepper, olives, mushrooms and onion in frying pan a couple of minutes.
Beat eggs with milk and pour into omelette pan with fried mixture.
Make sure the pan isn't too hot. Halfway through cooking the omelette, sprinkle the shredded cheese and Parmesan cheese (before turning omelette).
To add extra flavor, you may add a slice of tomato on top when finished.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix the ingredients and bake in long cake pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pink lady(gelatin salad)
directions: Put pineapple in boiler and bring to a boil.
Take off heat and add jello.
Put in refrigerator and cool.
Mix in other ingredients and congeal.

title: cranberry orange butter
directions: Beat butter well until fluffy.
Beat in cranberry sauce and marmalade.
Make 1 1/3 cups.
Keeps in fridge for up to 3 weeks. Great with toast, hot rolls, cranberry bread or bagels.
Enjoy.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and melted margarine together to make dough.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs, powdered sugar and vanilla; spread on top of dough.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
(Watch carefully; sides will burn easily.)
Cool; cut into small bars.

title: quick skillet pizza
directions: Add tomato sauce to browned hamburger meat.
Simmer until hot. Press out biscuits into glass round pan or 9 x 13-inch pan to form crust.
Form biscuits to cover sides of pan, also.
Pour in meat mixture.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until crust is brown.
Cut into serving pieces.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese cake(club member: clint hudson)
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup hot water; put in refrigerator. Let it begin to jell. Mix sugar and cheese; beat milk until stands in peaks. Combine all together; beat good and put in freezer until firm. Keep refrigerated. Use a graham cracker crust.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix everything but cheese.
Put into casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Add cheese and cook until cheese melts. Serves 6.

title: pineapple jello salad
directions: Spread a can of crushed pineapple in bottom of oblong dish. Mix about 1/3 cup Miracle Whip with enough milk to make fairly thin sauce.
Pour over pineapple.
Grate Cheddar cheese over top. Cover with small marshmallows.
Dissolve package of lime jello in 2 cups of boiling water and pour over marshmallows.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Dice onions finely. Mix remaining ingredients. Use for fish or seafood.

title: play dough
directions: Mix everything together.
Heat on low flame until mixture lumps together.
Stir to thick "mashed potato" thickness.
Store in plastic bags or airtight containers. Will freeze well.

title: chicken and escarole soup
directions: Boil 1 chicken or stewing hen.
Squeeze 1/2 lemon into stock. Use 2 or 3 cubes chicken bouillon or 2 tablespoons chicken soup base.
Boil with celery, onion and garlic.
Remove chicken and pick meat off bones.
Return meat to stock.
The fat needs to be skimmed off.
(It's easier to refrigerate and then skim off and re-cook the next day.)
Heat stock.
Add meatballs and cook about 2 hours. Just before serving, add one bunch escarole (spinach), chopped up. Heat and serve.

title: special "k" bars
directions: Place brown sugar and syrup in a large saucepan.
Cook and stir until it comes to a rolling boil.
Add peanut butter and mix. Add Special "K" and spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: microwave roux
directions: In uncovered 2 or 2 1/2-quart glass dish, blend together flour and oil and microwave on High for 10 minutes.
The color of the roux should be a deep caramel.
Roux does not look good at this point.
The flour is still gritty and the fat still a little separated.
Add seasoning (onions, celery or bell pepper) if desired.
Microwave another 3 minutes on High.
The color should deepen and the roux be shiny.
Stir and microwave on High another 2 minutes.
Roux is basis for brown gravies and most Creole gravies.

title: sweet potato custard pie(pie shell must be 9-inch or 10-inch)
directions: Beat butter until creamy.
Add sugar and milk.
Separate eggs. Beat yolks lightly and add to butter mixture along with yams, spices and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into butter mixture.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all together.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: *Use broccoli, red and green bell peppers, celery, carrots, cauliflower, sweet onion and/or zucchini.

title: pepper steak
directions: Slice beef in 1-inch strips, about 4-inches long.
Mix soy sauce, ginger and garlic.
Coat meat with flour and soy sauce mixture.
Brown in skillet with small amount of oil.
Add water. Cook until meat is tender.
Add vegetables.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Add cornstarch to mixture.
Serve over rice or noodles. This recipe will serve 5 people.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Put biscuits in greased 9 x 13-inch pan to form crust.
Brown meat and drain on paper towels.
Cover crust with meat.
Add your choice of toppings.
Cover with a layer of Cheddar cheese and then a layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Beat eggs and pour over pizza.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes until eggs are set.

title: bacon and tomato spread
directions: Stir together cream cheese, mustard and celery salt.
Stir in bacon, tomato and green pepper.
Cover and chill.
Serve with vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Serve immediately or chill first.

title: sonya's caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup milk.
Set aside.
Mix melted butter, 1/3 cup milk and dry cake mix.
Press 1/2 of mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Spread with chocolate chips and caramel.
Add nuts.
Crumble remaining cake dough on top to make almost another layer.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until done.
Cut when cool!

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Butter a casserole dish. Mix all ingredients together and pour into casserole dish. Bake 1 hour at 350° and lightly browned.

title: reduced fat citrus cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray bottom and sides of a 9 inch springform pan with Pam.
Sprinkle crumbs in bottom of pan.
In a mixing bowl. Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Add egg whites, lemon juice and orange rind.
Mix well, pour into prepared pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until center is set.
Chill.

title: lima beans in tomato sauce
directions: Fry chopped bacon, remove from pan.
Put remaining ingredients into fat; simmer for 25 minutes, or until thickened. Sprinkle beans with bacon before serving.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Very slowly, add oil, and beat well. Add vinegar and celery seed.
Beat at least 5 minutes, so it doesn't separate.

title: whipped topping(diabetic recipe)
directions: Combine dry milk and water; refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Beat at high speed for 4 minutes.
Add lemon juice to whipped milk; beat at high speed for 4 minutes.
Stir the sugar and sugar substitute together; add gradually to the whipped milk while it is being beaten.
Add vanilla to whipped topping; refrigerate until used.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all together and pour into a greased and floured 9 X 13 cake pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350.

title: christmas butter cookies
directions: Sift flour and baking powder.
Cream butter and sugar in separate bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well and add dry ingredients.
Chill dough for 4 hours.
Roll on floured board and cut.
May be brushed with beaten egg whites and sprinkled with colored sugar.

title: corned beef sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread on rye bread.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies as directed and set aside to cool completely. With a hammer, crush candy bars (finely).
Prepare mousse as directed and set aside.
In a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish, layer crumbled brownies, mousse, Cool Whip and top with crushed candy bars.
Continue to layer ingredients until all used up.
(You should end up with the Skor bar topping.)
Chill in fridge for 3 hours and serve.

title: angel dream cake
directions: Cut angel food cake horizontally.
Separate.
Mix yogurt and 1/2 Cool Whip together.
Spread mixture on bottom of cake and fill in the hole.
Replace top of cake.
Put other 1/2 of Cool Whip on top of the cake and if there is enough, around the sides.
Put into freezer for 1/2 hour to set.

title: maura's pizza
directions: Open Boboli package and put dough on cookie sheet.
Cover with olive oil, then pizza sauce, then cheese.
Top with parsley and basil.
Can put on any other meat or vegetable toppings too.
Bake in oven at 400° for 8 to 12 minutes until cheese is bubbling up.

title: chocolate sandwich cookies
directions: Mix all in order given.
Drop by teaspoon on greased sheets. Bake 6 or 7 minutes at 350°.
Yield:
6 dozen.

title: lemon amonia cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks and beat.
Add lemon oil; dissolve amonia in milk and add to mixture.
Use enough flour to make batter the consistency of cake.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg white.
Add remainder of flour to make a stiff dough. Roll on floured board and cut with cookie cutter into desired shape.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes or to a light brown.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Combine jello, pineapple and water.
Bring to a boil and cool. Add cottage cheese and Dream Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: ham dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add mayonnaise to make this to dip consistency.
Serve with chips.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
In a small bowl, combine cottage cheese, egg and pepper.

Cover bottom of 11 1/2 x 7-inch baking dish with 1 cup of spaghetti sauce mixture. Layer on noodles (3 lengthwise and break one in half to fit end). Add half of the cottage cheese mixture on top along with half of the Mozzarella cheese.
Make another layer of noodles, remaining spaghetti sauce mixture and the rest of the cottage cheese mixture and Mozzarella.
Sprinkle top with the Parmesan cheese.
Cover with Saran Wrap and cook 8 minutes on High.
Set power on Medium-low and cook 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: pizza rice salad
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package; cool.
Toss rice with remaining ingredients in a large bowl; use 1/2 cup salad dressing. Chill. Just before serving, add remaining salad dressing. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: mini sour cream bread
directions: Soften butter and add sour cream.
Mix until smooth.
Add flour a little at a time; mix well.
Drop 1 teaspoon in each mini muffin cup.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: grammy's grape-nut pudding
directions: In a double boiler, heat milk and add sugar, salt, flour and butter.
Stir constantly over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add Grape-Nuts and continue cooking 5 plus minutes, stirring occasionally.
(Mixture should be moderately thick.)

title: corn flake candy
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil; remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Mix well and add corn flakes, stirring until well coated.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool until firm.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Cook and stir evaporated milk, marshmallows and orange juice concentrate (undiluted) in a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat until marshmallows melt.
Take off heat and stir in dates, raisin, walnuts and candied fruit and cherries.

title: cream puffs
directions: Put one cup water in pan.
When the water is boiling add 1 stick of margarine, when melted add 1 cup of flour; mix together. Turn flame off.
When cooled, add one egg at a time, mixing it into batter thoroughly.
It will get a little hard to turn, but keep mixing until all eggs are absorbed.
Put flour on the bottom of pan.
Put one teaspoon in preheated oven at 400° for 30 minutes.
Shut oven off and leave them in for another 30 minutes. Don't open oven for any reason once they went in.
When cooled you can fill them with vanilla pudding and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: broccoli with lemon-butter sauce
directions: Wash broccoli, and trim tough stems.
Cut each stalk of broccoli into several pieces.
Place broccoli into a vegetable steamer basket over boiling water.
Cover and simmer for about 10 minutes until broccoli is tender.
In a small skillet, melt butter, then add lemon juice.
Drizzle lemon-butter over broccoli, and serve with lemon wedges.

title: bisquick fun dough
