directions: In a microwave-safe dish, combine baking mix, salt and cream of tartar.
Mix water and food coloring together and stir into dry mix, a little at a time, until all liquid is added.
Microwave, uncovered, at High (100%) for 1 minute.
Scrape the mixture from the side of the bowl and stir.
Microwave 2 to 3 minutes longer, pausing to stir every minute, until the mixture forms sort of a ball.
Use as "modeling clay" for children's play.
Inedible.

title: spinach-ricotta filling
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the fresh spinach with a small amount of water.
Simmer, covered, for 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Squeeze the spinach to remove excess moisture.
Chop spinach.

title: beef-potato pie
directions: Press uncooked ground beef into 9-inch square baking dish. Place cut onion over beef.
Next, put frozen hash browns evenly. Spread soup evenly and top with grated cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: party chicken
directions: Cover bottom of flat greased baking dish with chipped beef. Wrap each chicken breast with a slice of bacon.
Arrange on chipped beef.
Mix together soup and sour cream.
Pour over all. Refrigerate until ready to bake.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours, uncovered.

title: yam casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add next 6 ingredients, cooking until thick. Combine with yams, pineapple chunks and apples.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until apples are cooked.

title: beef patties consomme
directions: In skillet, cook beef patties until browned on both sides; drain excess fat.
Add consomme, parsley, margarine and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer for about 15 minutes. Combine cornstarch and water, then pour into skillet.
Stir while cooking, to thicken the gravy.
Remove from heat.
Serve over hot rice or creamed potatoes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: best ever lima bake
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove and break into small pieces. Cook onion and celery gently in bacon fat until golden, but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients and cooked bacon bits.
Pour into greased shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or more.

title: great pumpkin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Cream butter; gradually add sugars.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well; add ingredients and pumpkin, mixing well.
Stir in morsels.
Grease cookie sheet slightly.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: happy day cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together with mixer.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or make 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in apple and add dry ingredients and the sour milk.
Put in a loaf pan.
Mix together 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon. Sprinkle over the top and bake at 375° until done.

title: quick and easy cheese enchilada casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and add onions on low heat.
Chop tortillas into hamburger.
Add oil and let tortillas soften.
Add chili to taste; and 1/2 cup water to casserole.
Add both cheeses and let melt.

title: hazel and gordon's peanut brittle
directions: Prepare greased heavy-duty foil (can use the same piece more than once, just spray with
Pam after used).
Heat sugar, syrup and butter over low
heat
in
boiler,
stirring
often. When starts to bubble,
add
peanuts, using candy thermometer, and boil until a little above hard crack level.
Turn heat off and add baking soda and
salt,
stirring
very
quickly;
will bubble up. Pour immediately
onto
greased
foil;
spread out evenly.
Let cool completely; break into pieces.

title: bacon, lettuce, and tomato salad
directions: Combine the first five ingredients to prepare dressing.
Mix well and chill until ready to use.
Tear lettuce into bite size pieces.
Place in bowl.
Top with tomatoes, eggs, bacon and cheese.
When ready to serve, add dressing and toss.
It may not be necessary to use all of the dressing.
Serves 8.

title: 5 cup fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Yields 6 servings.

title: honey glaze ham
directions: For glaze, combine brown sugar, honey and allspice in a small bowl.
Place ham on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Insert meat thermometer into thickest part of ham, not touching bone or fat. Add 1/2 cup water to pan.
Cover.
Cook in a preheated 325° oven 19 to 23 minutes per pound or until thermometer registers 135°. Remove cover.
Spread glaze over ham; cook an additional 15 to 20 minutes.
Allow ham to stand, covered, about 10 minutes or until thermometer registers 140°.

title: sugar-free pumpkin cookies
directions: Beat oil and eggs with rotary beater until well emulsified. Add sugar substitute and beat until light and fluffy.
Add pumpkin, then dry ingredients.
Add raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
May be frozen after baking.
Yield:
4 dozen cookies.

title: beefy baked beans
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper.
Put in greased casserole dish. Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake
at
350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Measure sugar, oleo, salt, corn syrup and whipping cream into saucepan with straight sides. Stir gently to mix and start heating.
Keep the heat moderate.
Put the other 1/2 c. sugar into iron skillet.
Heat over moderate heat until caramelized.
Pour into the boiling mixture.
Cook 7 minutes or until it forms a soft ball in cold water.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown meat and sausage. Melt cheese. Blend together.
Let cook over warm heat until ready to serve.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake at 250° to 300° for 2 hours.

title: wacky cake
directions: Boil this until dissolved and thickened well.
Set aside to cool and then beat.
Spread on cake while warm.

title: stuffed artichokes
directions: Wash and trim artichokes; turn upside-down on paper towel to drain.
Mix bread crumbs, garlic and cheese together.
Separate leaves just enough to fill with mixture.
Salt and pepper artichokes; spoon mixture between leaves.
Drizzle olive oil generously over the stuffing.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish, add other ingredients.
Cover with tinfoil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cajun roast
directions: Make small slits in roast (over all sides of roast).
Stuff into each small pocket a sliver of garlic and a piece of green onion.
Rub butter over roast, then rub Dijon mustard over roast (all sides).
Sprinkle spices over roast, then pat down.
Bake in 500° oven uncovered for 15 minutes.
Then bake in 325° oven, covered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, depending on size of roast and cut of meat.

title: autumn apple
directions: In a saucepan, cook pineapple and sugar about 3 minutes. Add Jell-O and cream cheese; mix well. Fold in rest of ingredients. Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish and chill overnight.

title: julie's punch
directions: Make grape juice according to directions on can.
Add ginger ale.

title: quick vegetable soup
directions: In a Dutch oven,
brown meat and onion.
Drain any fat. Stir in remaining ingredients
and
simmer
to 20 minutes, until noodles are tender.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Combine and simmer 20 minutes over medium heat.
Cool.
Stir in Sweet 'N Low, 2 packages (1/2 to 3/4 teaspoon).
Place 2 cups sliced strawberries in pie shell.
Pour jello over berries in pie shell.
Chill.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip if sugar is allowed.

title: oreo cookies dessert
directions: Mix cookie crumbs and margarine, saving some crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and milk.
Add pudding and mix well.
Pour into crust.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Top with remaining crumbs.

title: french fish soup
directions: Saute onions, garlic, thyme and saffron.
Add fish, salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce and cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in tomato paste, wine and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add brandy and cream, then serve immediately.

title: kari's karamels
directions: Melt butter in a heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Add sugar and salt. Stir thoroughly.
Stir in corn syrup.
Mix well.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir over medium heat to firm ball stage (245°).
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pur into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares; wrap in wax paper.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut thin slice from stem end of pepper.
Remove seeds and membranes; rinse peppers.
Cook peppers in boiling water to cover, for about 5 minutes; drain.
Cook ground beef and onion until beef is browned.
Drain excess fat.
Stir in rice, salt, garlic salt and 1 cup of the tomato sauce; heat until hot.
Stuff peppers with beef mixture.
Stand upright in square baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over peppers.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes at 350°. Uncover and bake for 15 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: special kansas salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables and mix in a large mixing bowl. Combine vinegar, oil, salt and sugar.
Mix all fresh vegetables with cooked vegetables.
Add mixture of vinegar, oil and sugar to vegetables in bowl.
Chill several hours or overnight before serving.
Toss ingredients together well and drain, if desired.

title: homemade shrimp butter
directions: In a small mixer bowl, combine butter, mayonnaise and cream cheese; beat at medium speed until light and fluffy, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add onion, shrimp and lemon juice; continue beating until well mixed, 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve with crackers.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 2 cups.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix well and roll out onto floured board.
Cut with small cutter and place in heated, well-greased pan or dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: quick lasagne
directions: Brown meat in a large skillet; drain well.
Stir in next 5 ingredients; simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Layer noodles and then sauce and cottage cheese until all are used up.
Finish up with Mozzarella on top.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish at 350° for 30 minutes, until well heated.
Let stand about 10 minutes, then serve.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: homemade yeast rolls
directions: Sift flour.
Mix buttermilk, sugar, shortening and soda.
Add to flour.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to mixture, mixing well.
Store in a tightly covered bowl in refrigerator.
Use as needed; no rising period is necessary.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.
Turn oven on broil and finish baking until golden brown. Approximate cooking time is 12 to 15 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar.
Add flavoring, flour, salt, milk and yolks of eggs; mix well.
Lightly fold in whites of eggs and pour into pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° to 375° oven.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix milk, lemonade (thawed) and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill.
Add remaining Cool Whip for topping before serving.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream together with mixer the butter and sugar.
Beat in baking powder and flour.
Take 1/4 cup of mixture and set aside. Add cinnamon to this 1/4 cup of mixture. To remainder of mixture add egg, milk, sour cream and vanilla.
Beat well.
Fold in blueberries. Line 12 muffin tins with foil liners.
Fill tins; sprinkle with reserved mixture over top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: lisa's italian chicken
directions: Add onion, soup, bell pepper and spices to chicken.
Cover and cook at 300° for 1 hour.
Melt cheese on top the last 10 minutes. Serve with spaghetti.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and margarine in a heavy saucepan.
Heat over medium heat to boiling. Stir constantly about 5 minutes over medium heat or until mixture reaches soft ball stage (238° per candy thermometer). Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients; stir vigorously until well blended.
Pour into greased pan. Cool and cut into squares. Makes approximately 3 pounds of fudge.

title: ham spread
directions: Mix together and spread on crackers or bread.

title: almond chicken
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in a bowl and let stand for 1 hour. In a wok put 3 tablespoons cooking oil and stir-fry the vegetables.
Set aside.
Toss vegetables with garlic juice, water and salt.
In another pan fry chicken in small amount of cooking oil.
Add vegetables and chicken to wok.
Make a well in chicken and vegetable mixture and pour in 2 teaspoons cornstarch blended with 3 teaspoons water.
Keep stirring until the sauce thickens. Add almonds just before serving.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix and spread filling onto tortillas.
Roll up and chill. When ready to serve, cut into slices.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Sift flour and measure it.
Then sift 3 times with the sugar, baking powder and salt.
Work into this with a fork the peanut butter and beaten egg.
Add milk and mix well.

title: cowboy casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Add meat.
Cook until brown; add seasonings.
Boil and drain spaghetti.
Mix all together and pour into baking dish.
Top with grated cheese and melt in oven.

title: lasagne
directions: In hot oil in heavy pan, fry garlic and onion until soft.
Add beef; cook and stir until crumbly.
Mix in salt, pepper, rosemary and tomato paste, blended with hot water.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

In shallow baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch, put a thin layer of sauce, then layer of 1/2 the noodles, layer of cottage cheese, dotted over noodles, then thin slices of Swiss cheese; more sauce, noodles, Swiss cheese and remaining sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until sauce bubbles.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream together butter or margarine and confectioners sugar (1 3/4 cup); add vanilla and mix well.
Add flour and pecans, finely chopped.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
While still warm, dust with confectioners sugar.

title: souper cheese potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes and water in a microwave-safe casserole. Cover with lid and microwave on High 12 to 14 minutes. Stir once. Stir in soup, sour cream, half and half, chives and garlic salt. Microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes (uncovered).
Stir once. Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Let stand, covered, about 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Sprinkle with parsley and pepper.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Heat oil and brown meat until just done.
Add onion, garlic, green pepper, celery, tomatoes, bay leaves, oregano and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer 3 hours.
During the last half hour, add the olives and mushrooms.
Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Rinse and drain.
Place spaghetti in a large shallow baking dish or casserole.
Cover with sauce and bake at 325° about 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 14.

title: white bread
directions: Scald milk; add lard, sugar and salt and let cool.
When lukewarm, crumble yeast in and let rise.
Take 4 cups flour; make well in center and pour in milk mixture; beat smooth.
Add rest of flour and knead until smooth and elastic; knead about 10 to 15 minutes.
Put in greased bowl; cover and set in warm place to rise until doubled in bulk.
Then, put on floured board and cut in half.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Put in greased pans; let rise to double again and bake 10 minutes at 375°, then turn down to 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream the butter until light and fluffy.
Beat in the sugar. Add the egg or egg yolks and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly. Add the cream or milk.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder and stir in.
Mix well and arrange by teaspoonfuls on a buttered cookie sheet 1-inch apart. Bake about 8 minutes at 375°.
Makes 50 to 60 cookies.

title: dried beef casserole(serves 6)
directions: Saute onion, celery and beef in hot oil until onions are golden.
Stir in flour and add milk gradually and stir until slightly thickened.
Add macaroni, seasonings and parsley.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: rio grande pea salad
directions: Mix all vegetables together. Combine sugar, salad oil, cider vinegar and water. Mix well and pour over veggies. Toss well. Cover and chill overnight. Drain well before serving.

title: crisp golden corn points
directions: Beat eggs in a
mixing bowl. Add milk, butter and corn meal. Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Mix just to blend.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, until edges are browned.
Cool and cut into diamond shapes.
Split and spread cut surfaces with butter.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze in ice cream freezer. Makes 2 quarts. Make different varieties by adding chocolate syrup, nuts or fresh fruit.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into 1 deep pie shell or 2 (9-inch) shells. Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: robert redford dessert
directions: Mix flour, butter, sugar and pecans.
Press in a 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix broth, margarine, onion soup and mushrooms in a pan and heat.
Add rice and mix.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish. Cover and bake in preheated oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Remove lid; reduce heat to 350° and bake another 30 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.

title: whole wheat raisin bread
directions: In large bowl, stir together the flour, wheat germ, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.

In a separate bowl, combine the buttermilk, honey, and oil; pour all at once into the flour mixture, stirring just until all the ingredients are combined. Add raisins and nuts, being careful not to overmix the batter. Pour batter into greased 5 1/2x9 1/2- inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° about 1 1/4 hours or until a pick inserted in center comes out clean.
The top should be slightly pebbled and evenly browned. Let cool in pan 10 minutes, then turn out on rack.
Cool thoroughly. Makes 1 loaf.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Combine margarine, tarragon and lemon juice; combine bread crumbs, parsley, sesame seed, salt and onion powder.
Pour buttermilk over chicken, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Discard buttermilk and pat chicken dry.
Dip chicken in margarine mixture, then bread crumbs and arrange on a baking sheet.
Cover and refrigerate until 1 to 1 1/2 hours before dinner.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Combine meat, onion, seasonings, carrots and soup.
Cook for 2 hours.
Add mixed vegetables, potatoes and ketchup.
Cook until meat and vegetables are ready.

title: * tuna tulips *
directions: Combine ingredients (except biscuit dough).
Preheat oven to 425°.
Make biscuit dough and roll dough to 18 x 12-inch oblong. Cut into 6 x 6-inch squares.
Place in muffin tins and spoon filling into shells.
Fold tips over slightly to resemble a tulip. Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: christmas cookies(fruit cake)
directions: Mix butter and sugar together.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add flour, cinnamon, soda and cooking wine; mix well.
Add nuts, pineapple and cherries that have been chopped well.
Add raisins, mixing well.
Batter will be stiff.
Cook on cookie sheet at 275° for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes a lot.
Will keep well in a Tupperware container.

title: stuffed zucchini squash
directions: Wash zucchini:
cut off ends; don't pare.
Cook in boiling water with salt for 5 min.
Halve lengthwise; remove pulp with spoon and combine with bread crumbs, cheese, onion, salt, pepper, and eggs.
Fill zucchini shells.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle more cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 mins.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add egg whites, beating well.
In separate bowl, combine flour, spices and salt.
Add dry mixture, vanilla and water to creamed mixture.
Blend well and stir in apples and pecans.
Spoon into well-greased and floured 9 or 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: beef turnovers
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in cornstarch, salt and ketchup.
Brush biscuits with egg and water mixture.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spread bite size pieces of chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix soup and sour cream and spread over chicken.
Mix crushed crackers and seed and spread over the soup mixture.
Drizzle with melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, wafer crumbs, milk, coconut and nuts. Blend well.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in tube pan.

title: apple bars
directions: Bake about 30 minutes at 350 degrees.
(optional)
While hot sprinkle with powdered sugar or frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: kaiser rolls
directions: In a small bowl, sprinkle the yeast and sugar over the warm water.
Stir to mix, then let stand until foamy, 5 to 10 minutes.

title: cherry wink cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Add pecans, dates and 1/3 cup chopped cherries. Mix.
Shape dough into tablespoon size balls.
Roll each ball in cornflake crumbs. Place on a greased baking sheet.
Top each cookie with 1/4 of a maraschino cherry.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Wash and cut the fruit into bite size pieces.
Mix fruit with sour cream and apple juice.

title: louisiana pralines
directions: Place sugar and milk in medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often.
When a firm ball forms (drop in water to test), remove from heat.
Add vanilla, pecans and butter.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper or buttered cookie sheet.
Let stand until hard.

title: easy cherry pie
directions: Put cherry pie filling into an 8-inch square dish.
Cut bread into strips (3 strips per slice) and cover cherries.
Mix together melted margarine, sugar and beaten egg.
Pour over bread evenly to cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple harvest cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease the bottom and sides of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan with the butter.
Line bottom with baker's parchment or brown bag paper.
Set aside.
Toss the apples with the nuts and sugar in a large bowl.
In another bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Beat in eggs, oil and vanilla until batter is thoroughly moistened.
Pour the batter over the apples.
Stir with a wooden spoon to evenly distribute the fruit (do not overmix).
Pour into pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes, or until cake tester is clean.
Just before serving, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Store at room temperature.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Set aside.
Cream the margarine and sugar together. Add eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add the flour mixture to the creamed mixture.
Chill dough.
Roll dough out about 1/4-inch thick and cut out with cookie cutters. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes on an ungreased baking sheet. Add more flour for cutting out.

title: bread dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Hollow out round bread; pour dip into bread. Use the remaining bread to dip.

title: 1956 bangor club barbecue sauce
directions: Fry onions and celery in oil until slightly brown.
Add to other ingredients and bring to a boil, then simmer 20 minutes. Seal in sterilized jars.
Makes 12 to 14 quarts.

title: easy chili con queso
directions: Cut cheese into small blocks to make melting easier.
Melt cheese in small saucepan.
Add mushroom soup.
Keep heat low and stir so cheese mixture does not burn.
When melted, add chilies; stir to combine.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Serves a crowd easily!

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients well and set aside.
Cook rotini and drain.
Put in a large bowl.
Add vegetables and meat.
Mix well.
Add sauce mixture and mix.
Serve warm or cold.

title: broccoli and rice no. 1
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Mix all ingredients and place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Beat well juice, yolks and milk.
Pour into pie crust.

title: 40 cloves of garlic chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt butter and oil in dutch oven.
Add chicken, turning it brown for 10-15 minutes.
Add garlic and stir in the oil/butter mixture.
After chicken is browned, add 1/2 c of water, salt, and pepper (add thyme if desired). Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350° in dutch oven.

title: exquisite pie
directions: Blend
eggs,
sugar
and
butter well; stir in coconut, pecans and
raisins.
Mix
well.	Add vinegar or lemon juice. Pour into 9-inch pie crusts and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan(microwave)
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Set aside.
In shallow baking dish, blend egg and water together.
Dip chicken breast in egg mixture and then in bread crumb mixture.
In 3-quart oblong glass baking dish, arrange chicken.
Pour spaghetti sauce over top and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave at High 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pineapple refrigerator cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to package directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Spread pineapple with juice over cake.
Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Spread pudding over pineapple.
Spread topping over pudding mixture.
Cover cake with plastic wrap and refrigerate.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Do not preheat oven.

title: apricot slush
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large plastic container. Freeze until firm.
Remove punch from freezer 1 1/2 hours before serving.
Place mixture in punch bowl and break into chunks.
Add ginger ale; stir until slushy.
Yield:
about 7 quarts.

title: goulash
directions: Boil elbow macaroni according to directions on box until almost done.
Drain.
Brown ground beef, add onion.
Drain off fat.
Combine ground beef mixture with tomatoes and macaroni. Season to taste with salt and pepper and garlic salt if desired. Simmer 5 - 10 minutes. Serve with garlic bread. Better than Hamburger Helper.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and mix.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder, 1/3 at a time, and mix.
Add vanilla and mix well. Mold into round log and refrigerate until needed, then slice and bake at 350° until lightly tan, about 10 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook rice in oil until browned.
Add onion, green pepper, tomatoes and sugar.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and cook for 25 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir in meat and cook 5 minutes more.

title: french roll appetizers
directions: Chop green peppers and tomatoes.
Mix with rest of ingredients.
Cut off ends of rolls.
Hollow out centers.
Pack with cream cheese mixture.
Wrap each in foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice into rounds before serving.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, but cheese, in a bowl.
Pour in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: okra pickles
directions: Thoroughly wash okra.
Drain.
Pack into hot clean pint jars, leaving 1/2-inch of headspace.
In saucepan, combine water, vinegar, pickling salt, dill seed and red pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Pour hot liquid over okra in jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace. Wipe rims and adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes. Start timing when water starts to boil. Makes 4 pints.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 hour. Serve over spaghetti.

title: chinese egg rolls
directions: Brown meat in butter.
Combine with vegetables and drain well. Add 2 tablespoons soy sauce, 1 teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon sugar and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Mixture should be moist, but not wet. Roll in egg roll skins.
Lightly brown several egg rolls at a time (1 minute) in 1-inch of hot peanut oil, 375°, in electric skillet or deep fat fryer.

title: fresh uncooked strawberry pie
directions: Cap, wash and sweeten to taste fresh berries.
Pour in prebaked pie shell.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: no fail fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and salt in saucepan for 10 minutes.
Add butter.
Continue to boil until
mixture forms soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Beat until mixture starts to set.
Pour quickly into buttered pan.

title: grandma grimes' sugar cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, nutmeg, vanilla and sugar in a bowl.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Add eggs, shortening and buttermilk with soda to other ingredients.
Knead as for biscuits. Sprinkle with flour if necessary.
Roll thin on pastry sheet. Cut with cookie cutter.
Sprinkle each cookie with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: beef or deer jerky
directions: Remove all fat from meat.
Freeze partially, then cut into 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick strips.
Marinate overnight in quart jars.
Lay jars in refrigerator on their sides.
Turn occasionally.
Remove from jars and lay strips on racks in the oven.
Turn oven to lowest oven setting for about 10 to 12 hours.
If oven is still too warm, leave door ajar.

title: e.z. nachos
directions: In a microwave dish, layer chips, beans and cheese. Add meat, if desired.
Cook in microwave until cheese is melted. Add salsa, sour cream and guacamole to taste.
(Can be made in conventional oven at 350° using an oven-safe baking pan.)

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill before serving.

title: light strawberry preserves
directions: Mix Sure-Jell and 1/4 cup sugar.
Add pectin mixture gradually to fruit, stirring vigorously.
Set aside for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir remaining sugar gradually into fruit mixture until sugar is completely dissolved, about 3 minutes.
Pour into pint containers and cover.
Let stand at room temperature for 24 hours.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.
Thaw in refrigerator. Makes about 6 (1 cup) containers.

title: bread pudding
directions: Melt butter in baking pan.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Pour about 1/2 melted margarine into mix and stir.
Pour mix into baking pan and bake until brown, 1/2 hour at 500°.

title: date bars
directions: Mix dates, sugar, egg and margarine in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, Rice Krispies and nuts.
Pour into buttered pie pan. Refrigerate.

title: potato salad
directions: Wash thoroughly and boil potatoes with jackets on until done. Boil
eggs and peel.
After potatoes have cooled for 10 to 15 minutes,
rinse
in
cool
water and peel.
In large mixing bowl, mash
potatoes
and
begin adding mayonnaise and mustard (use more or less according to taste).
Pour in pickle juice, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Add chopped eggs, pickles and onion.
If too thick, add more mayonnaise.

title: my sister doris' scottish oven scones
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour 3 times and cut in butter. Add sugar, baking powder and soda.
Add milk.
Form dough; dough should be light but not too wet.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness on a floured board.
Do not overhandle dough.
Cut with a 2 1/2-inch cutter.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes on nonstick sheet.

title: all-in-one casserole
directions: Grease 2-quart casserole.
Measure rice and spread in even layer on bottom.
Mix flour, chili powder, salt and pepper in small dish.
Sprinkle 1/3 of this mixture over rice.
Dot with 1/2 tablespoon butter.
Mix hamburg with onion and spread over rice. Repeat flour mixture and butter as above.
Make a layer of tomatoes with liquid and repeat flour and butter.
Drain corn and spread on top.
Dot with remaining butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: filet mignon a la cajun
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; add rest of ingredients, except bacon and onion.
Shape into 6 or 7 patties; wrap each patty in bacon, secure with toothpick.
Brown on both sides in small amount of oil.
Add chopped onion and 3/4 cup water.
Cover and cook 30 to 45 minutes, adding water if necessary.

title: butterhorns
directions: Mix flour, shortening, sugar and salt like a pie dough.
Add beaten eggs.
Add yeast that has been dissolved in lukewarm milk. Store dough in refrigerator overnight or at least 4 hours in a cold place.
Roll out dough and shape into butterhorns.
Let rise. Bake 30 minutes in 375° oven.
Frost with powdered sugar and milk frosting while warm and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: banana split
directions: Mix and pack down in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: orange salad(makes 8 to 10 servings)
directions: Add water to the juices from the oranges and pineapple to make 2 cups.
Bring to a boil and pour over the gelatin; dissolve gelatin.
Add sherbet; stir until dissolved.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in fruit.
Pour into oiled 6-cup mold; chill.

title: baked creamed chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts
in baking dish and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place slices of Swiss cheese over breasts to cover. Mix soup
and
wine
together;
pour over cheese, then sprinkle bread crumbs over top (use generous amount).
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: flan
directions: Heat sugar in Teflon pan until melted; stir constantly. Drizzle melted caramelized sugar in metal Bundt pan. Swirl to coat pan. Set aside.
In heavy saucepot, heat remaining ingredients until warm and blended. Avoid bubbling and frothing.
Cool slightly.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Cover with foil.
Steam in water bath on low heat slowly to maintain creaminess, 45 minutes. Remove from heat. Chill. When cold, turn out onto platter and serve 15.

title: lazy apple pie
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter in a 9 or 10-inch pie plate and then drain in a separate bowl.
Empty one can of apple pie filling into pie plate.
Then sprinkle the cake mix over apple pie filling. Pour the melted butter over the cake mix.
Sprinkle cinnamon over butter.
Bake at 425° until brown (20 minutes).

title: never fail chocolate icing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan; bring to hard boil, then cook 2 minutes.
Let cool until you can stand your hand on the bottom of pan.
Beat to right consistency (begins to thicken and loses gloss).
If it happens to get too hard, just add a few drops of milk.

title: stuffed pepper soup
directions: Brown ground beef and mix everything together either 1/2 hour on stove top or in crock-pot on low for a few hours until peppers are soft.

title: artichoke heart dip
directions: Drain and coarsely chop the artichoke hearts.
Mix with mayonnaise and Monterey Jack.
Place in small casserole dish. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: old fashioned jelly roll
directions: Line greased jelly roll pan with waxed paper, grease and set aside.
Beat egg yolks about 5 minutes or until very thick. Gradually add sugar.
On low speed, blend in lemon juice and lemon peel.

title: marshmallow creme fudge
directions: Mix sugar, Milnot and margarine together.
Cook until mixture comes to a boil, stirring frequently.
Boil this mixture for 5 minutes, stirring.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in chocolate chips and marshmallow cream.
Stir until smooth and creamy.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Allow to cool and cut.
Yield:

title: home-canned spaghetti sauce
directions: Saut onion rings and minced garlic in olive oil. Add spices. Cook down while preparing tomatoes.

title: honeyed ham
directions: Remove skin and fat.
Place ham on rack in pan.
Combine mustard and honey; spread on ham.
Mix brown sugar, vanilla and almond flavoring.
Pat over entire ham.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes per pound.
Baste often.
Let set overnight.
Slice and serve.

title: chocolate easter eggs
directions: Pour liquids over sugar and mix.
Add fruit and nuts, then shape into egg form and dip into chocolate.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Knead with warm water and make into large ball.
Cover and let it stand for 30 minutes.
Later, make into small patties and roll them out with a rolling pin.
Cook on hot grill on both sides until they are light brown.

title: wheat free raisin spice cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and cook 15 minutes, until raisins swell.
Cool.
When cool, add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour in sheet pan.

title: easy rice dish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt the butter in a large casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and place in the casserole dish.
Cook until the liquid has been absorbed.

title: shrimp luncheon dish
directions: Mix well and add 1 1/2 pounds of shrimp, cut up.
Refrigerate until next day.
Heap on 2 halves hot dog rolls.
Broil until bubbly and brown.
Supply knives and forks.
Serves 12.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Hard-boil eggs, half and remove yolks. Mix egg yolks with all ingredients. Stir until smooth.
Spoon mixture into halved egg whites.
Refrigerate before serving.
Sprinkle small amount of paprika over finished eggs.

title: mashed sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with chili sauce or barbecue sauce.
Serve with crackers.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: aunt bill's candy
directions: Heat 1/2 cup of the sugar in heavy skillet.
Stir until melted (light brown syrup).
Do not let it smoke.
While sugar is melting combine remaining sugar and cream and heat to boiling.
Pour melting sugar into boiling sugar and cream, adding it in a slow, thin stream and stirring constantly.
Rub the margarine around the inside of the pan, allowing it to melt, and wash down crystals that have formed.
Add soda when candy reaches 114° to 115° and stir vigorously as it forms.
Continue cooking and stirring occasionally until it forms a soft ball and reaches 116° (237° to 240°).

title: turkey dressing
directions: Combine bread cubes, salt, pepper, poultry seasoning, onion and celery.
Melt margarine and pour over bread mixture.
Add eggs.
Moisten with turkey broth.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake slow at 325° for 1 hour.
This is the secret of good dressing, to bake slow.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute mushrooms in a little butter.
Set aside and saute onion and peppers.
Add soup, milk, wine and chicken.
Mix lightly with cooked spaghetti.
Turn into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.
Serves a good 10 people.

title: fudge batter pudding
directions: This pudding, when baked, has a chocolate sauce on bottom and cake on top.

title: old fashioned jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add remaining ingredients.
Bake in layer pans at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: pork chops and rice-a-roni
directions: Using a large skillet, put enough cooking oil in skillet to cover the bottom.
Bread pork chops as you would to fry.
When chops are done, remove from skillet and drain grease.
In same skillet, prepare Rice-A-Roni.
While rice is boiling, place pork chops back in skillet with rice.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
If desired, you may add tomato juice to rice before adding pork chops.

title: cheese puffs(makes 12)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
In quart saucepan, heat water and margarine to boiling.
Stir in baking mix all at once.
Stir in vigorously over low heat about 1 minute or until mixture leaves side of pan and forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs thoroughly.
Continue beating until mixture is smooth.
Mix in cheese and Italian seasoning.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until puffed and golden brown.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Blend in eggs and sour milk. Sift together the flour, soda and baking powder.
Add creamed mixture, along with bananas.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Shape into 2 logs.
Roll in finely chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
